अतीसारकिन् m. f. n. (-की-किनी-कि). See अतिसारकिन्.

अतुङ्ग
अतुङ्ग Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ङ्गः-ङ्गा-ङ्गम्) <BR>	1 Short of stature, <BR>dwarfish. <BR>	2 Low. E. अ neg. and तुङ्ग.

अतुर
अतुर Tatpur. m. (-रः) (ved.) Not liberal. E. अ neg. and तुर.

अतुल
अतुल Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Unequalled. <BR>II. m. (-लः) A plant bearing an oily seed (Sesamum <BR>orientale). See तिल. E. अ priv. and तुला.

अतुल्य
अतुल्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ल्यः-ल्या-ल्यम्) Unequalled, unpa<BR>ralleled. E. अ neg. and तुल्य.

अतुषारकर
अतुषारकर Bahuvr. m. (-रः) The sun. E. अ-तुषार (not cold) <BR>and कर ‘whose rays are not cold’.

अतुष्टि
अतुष्टि Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) Dissatisfaction, displeasure. E. अ <BR>neg. and तुष्टि.

अतुहिनधामन्
अतुहिनधामन् Bahuvr. m. (-मा) The sun. E. अ-तुहिन and <BR>धामन्. See the following.

अतुहिनरश्मि
अतुहिनरश्मि Bahuvr. m. (-श्मिः) The sun. E. अ-तुहिन and <BR>रश्मि ‘whose rays are not cold’, also analogous com<BR>pounds, as अतुहिनरुचि &c.

अतूतुजि
अतूतुजि Tatpur. m. (-जिः) (ved.) Not fast, slow. E. अ neg. <BR>and तूतुजि.

अतूर्त
अतूर्त Tatpur. (ved.) I. m. f. n. (-र्तः-र्ता-र्तम्) <BR>	1 Unhurt, unin<BR>jured. <BR>	2 Not hastening, not going speedily. <BR>II. n. (-र्तम्) The illimited space. E. अ neg. and तूर्त.

अतूर्तदक्ष
अतूर्तदक्ष Bahuvr. m. (-क्षः) (ved.) Of unhurt power, irresistible; <BR>an epithet of the Aśvins. E. अतूर्त and दक्ष.

अतूर्तपथिन्
अतूर्तपथिन् Bahuvr. m. (-न्थाः) (ved.) Whose path is unhurt <BR>or without obstacles; an epithet of Vāyu and of Aryaman, <BR>one of the Ādityas. E. अतूर्त and पथिन्.

अतृणाद
अतृणाद Tatpur. m. (-दः) A recently born calf. E. अ neg. <BR>and तृणाद ‘not or not yet eating grass’.

अतृण्या
अतृण्या Tatpur. f. (-ण्या) A small quantity of grass. E. अ <BR>neg. and तृण्या (a quantity of grass).

अतृदिल
अतृदिल Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) (ved.) Not brittle, <BR>solid. E. अ neg. and तृदिल.

अतृप
अतृप Bahuvr. m. (-पः) (ved.) Not satisfied. E. अ priv. and तृपा(?).

अतृष्य
अतृष्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) (ved.) Not suffering <BR>thirst. E. अ neg. and तृष्य.

अतेजस्
अतेजस् I. Tatpur. n. (-जः) <BR>	1 Shade, shadow. <BR>	2 Insignificance, <BR>feebleness, imbecility. E. अ neg. and तेजस्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-जाः-जाः-जः) Dark, dim, dull. E. <BR>अ priv. and तेजस्.

अतेजस्क
अतेजस्क Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्कः-स्का-स्कम्) Dark, dim, dull. <BR>E. अ priv. and तेजस्, samāsānta aff. कप्.

अतेजस्विन्
अतेजस्विन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्वी-स्विनी-स्वि) Void of splen<BR>dour or energy. E. अ neg. and तेजस्विन्.

अतोषणीय
अतोषणीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Implacable, not <BR>to be appeased. E. अ neg. and तोषणीय.

अत्क
अत्क I. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) A traveller. <BR>II. m. (-कः) <BR>	1 A limb, a member of the body. <BR>	2 (ved.) <BR>Moisture, fluid. <BR>	3 (ved.) Armour, mail. <BR>	4 (ved.) Thunderbolt. <BR>lightning(?). <BR>	5 (ved.) The name of an Asura, a synonyme <BR>of Vṛtra. E. अत्, uṇ. aff. कन्.

अत्कील
अत्कील m. (-लः) See उत्कील, the more correct reading of <BR>this word.

अत्ता
अत्ता f. (-त्ता) <BR>	1 A mother. <BR>	2 An elder sister. <BR>	3 A mother's <BR>elder sister. (In Prākṛt: a mother in law.) E. unknown. <BR>See also अत्ति, अत्तिका.

अत्ति
अत्ति I. f. (-त्तिः) (In theatrical language.) An elder sister. <BR>E. unknown. See the preceding. <BR>II. m. (-त्तिः) (ved.) An eater, one who eats. E. अद्, uṇ. aff. ति.

अत्तिका
अत्तिका f. (-का) (In theatrical language.) An elder sister. <BR>E. अत्ता a mother, and कन् affix, ‘who is, as it were, a <BR>mother’. Also written अन्तिका and अर्तिका.

अत्तृ
अत्तृ m. f. n. (-त्ता-त्त्री-त्तृ) An eater, one who eats. See <BR>अत्त्रिन्. E. अद्, kṛt aff. तृच्.

अत्त्र
अत्त्र I. m. (-त्त्रः) and II. n. (-त्त्रम्). See अत्र III. and IV., <BR>the less correct, but more usual reading of this vaidik word.

अत्त्रि
अत्त्रि m. (-त्त्रिः). See अत्रि the less correct, but more usual <BR>reading of this word. E. अद्, uṇ. aff. त्रिप्. See the following.

अत्त्रिन्
अत्त्रिन् m. (-त्त्री). See अत्रिन्, the less correct, but more <BR>usual reading of this vaidik word. E. अद्, uṇ. aff. त्रिनि; <BR>or according to others, अत्त्र (food), taddh. aff. इनि. The <BR>plur. अत्त्रिणः is also explained, as an irregul. plural of <BR>अत्तृ, with āgama इनुङ्.

अत्न
अत्न m. (-त्नः) The sun. E. अत्, uṇ. aff. न. See the following.

अत्नु
अत्नु m. (-त्नुः) The sun. E. अत्, uṇ. aff. क्नु.

अत्य
अत्य m. (-त्यः) (ved.) A horse. E. अत्, uṇ. aff. य.

अत्यंहस्
अत्यंहस् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-हाः-हाः-हः) (ved.) Beyond sin, free <BR>from sin. E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and अंहस् (in the sense of <BR>the accusative).

अत्यग्नि
अत्यग्नि Tatpur. I. m. (-ग्निः) Too quick digestion, described as <BR>‘followed by burning heat in throat, palate and lips’. E. <BR>अति and अग्नि. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-ग्निः-ग्निः-ग्नि) Surpassing fire (f. i. in bril<BR>liancy). E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and अग्नि (in the sense of the accus.).

अत्यग्निष्टोम
अत्यग्निष्टोम Tatpur. m. (-मः) <BR>	1 The name of the second part <BR>or Somasansthā of the Jyotiṣṭoma sacrifice, for the complete <BR>performance of which, however, it is not considered nitya, <BR>essential or obligatory, as the Agniṣṭoma (q. v.), but kāmya, <BR>voluntary and therefore anitya, supererogatory. <BR>	2 The name <BR>of the Sāmaveda verse which closes the ceremonies of this sa<BR>crifice. E. अति (sc. क्रान्तः) and अग्निष्टोम (in the sense of <BR>the accus.), ‘going beyond, coming after the Agniṣṭoma’.

अत्यङ्कुश
अत्यङ्कुश Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) No more controllable <BR>by a hook, unmanageable, vicious (as an elephant). E. <BR>अति (sc. क्रान्त) and अङ्कुश (in the sense of the accusative).

अत्यङ्गुल
अत्यङ्गुल Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Surpassing, going <BR>beyond a finger or an angula-incasure. (See अङ्गुलि.) E. <BR>अति (sc. क्रान्त) and अङ्गुलि (in the sense of the accusative), <BR>samāsānta aff. अच्.

अत्यध्वन्
अत्यध्वन् Tatpur. m. (-ध्वा) <BR>	1 A very great way or road. <BR>	2 Travelling very or too much. E. अति and अध्वन्.

अत्यनिल
अत्यनिल Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Surpassing the wind <BR>(in quickness &c.). E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and अनिल (in the <BR>sense of the accusative).

अत्यन्त
अत्यन्त I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) <BR>	1 Excessive, very much, <BR>very far. <BR>	2 Complete, thorough. <BR>	3 Uninterrupted, continual (in <BR>space or time). II. Avyayībh. (-न्तम्) <BR>	1 Excessively. <BR>	2 Com<BR>pletely. <BR>	3 Always, continually. E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and अन्त <BR>(in the sense of the accusative).

अत्यन्तकोपन
अत्यन्तकोपन Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Very passionate, <BR>fierce, violent. E. अत्यन्त and कोपन.

अत्यन्तग
अत्यन्तग Tatpur. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) What goes very much <BR>or quickly. E. अत्यन्त and ग.

अत्यन्तगत
अत्यन्तगत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Completely established <BR>or pertinent, always applicable (as a rule). E. अत्यन्त and गत.

अत्यन्तगति
अत्यन्तगति Tatpur. f. (-तिः) (In grammar.) The sense of ‘com<BR>pletely, thoroughly’ (opposed to the sense of ‘diminutive’). <BR>See अनत्यन्तगति. E. अत्यन्त (complete, thorough) and गति <BR>(sense, understanding).

अत्यन्तगामिन्
अत्यन्तगामिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि) Going very <BR>much or quickly, going very far. E. अत्यन्त and गामिन्.

अत्यन्तगुणिन्
अत्यन्तगुणिन् m. f. n. (-णी-णिनी-णि) Having highly good <BR>qualities. E. अत्यन्त-गुण (highly good quality), taddh. aff. इनि.

अत्यन्ततिरस्कृतवाच्यध्वनि
अत्यन्ततिरस्कृतवाच्यध्वनि Karmadh. m. (-निः) (In rhetoric.) <BR>A metaphorical expression, when the word expressing the fi<BR>gure or comparison drops its literal sense in order to be<BR>come appropriate for the comparison; f. i. in the sentence <BR>‘the moon does not shine, like a mirror which has become <BR>blind by breathing upon it’--the word ‘blind’ loses its <BR>literal meaning, to serve as a comparison for ‘the not shin<BR>ing’ of the moon with which it has no common quality. <BR>E. अत्यन्त, तिरस्कृत, वाच्य (these three words forming a <BR>Bahuvr.) and ध्वनि.

अत्यन्तपीडन
अत्यन्तपीडन Karmadh. n. (-नम्) Causing excessive pain or <BR>agony. E. अत्यन्त and पीडन.

अत्यन्तवासिन्
अत्यन्तवासिन् Karmadh. m. (-सी) The Brahman who con <BR>tinues to live with his spiritual preceptor and always re<BR>mains in the condition of a religious student. See नैष्ठिक. <BR>E. अत्यन्त and वासिन्.

अत्यन्तसंयोग
अत्यन्तसंयोग Karmadh. m. (-गः) (In grammar.) The intimate <BR>proximity (of two words), the connexion of two words without <BR>any other word standing between them. E. अत्यन्त and संयोग.

अत्यन्तसम्पर्क
अत्यन्तसम्पर्क Karmadh. m. (-र्कः) Too frequent sexual inter<BR>course. E. अत्यन्त and सम्पर्क.

अत्यन्तसुकुमार
अत्यन्तसुकुमार Tatpur. m. (-रः) A species of grain (Panicum <BR>Italicum). E. अत्यन्त and सुकुमार ‘extremely soft’.

अत्यन्ताभाव
अत्यन्ताभाव Karmadh. m. (-वः) (In the Vaiśeṣika philosophy.) <BR>Absolute negation or non-existence, one of the four kinds <BR>of अभाव q. v. E. अत्यन्त and अभाव.

अत्यन्तिक
अत्यन्तिक m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) I. Tatpur. Very near, very <BR>proximate. E. अति and अन्तिक. <BR>II. Going much or quickly, going very far. E. अत्यन्त, <BR>taddh. aff. ठन्.

अत्यन्तीन
अत्यन्तीन m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Going much or quickly, go<BR>ing very far. E. अत्यन्त, taddh. aff. ख.

अत्यन्तीनत्व
अत्यन्तीनत्व n. (-त्वम्) The condition or property of going <BR>very far, of being distant or exalted, a high degree. E. <BR>अत्यन्तीन, taddh. aff. त्व.

अत्यम्ल
अत्यम्ल Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-म्लः-म्ला-म्लम्) Very sour. <BR>II. m. (-म्लः) A tree (Spondias mangifera). See वृक्षाम्ल. <BR>III. f. (-म्ला) Another plant and fruit; a species of citron. <BR>See मातुलुङ्गी. E. अति and अम्ल.

अत्यम्लपर्णी
अत्यम्लपर्णी Bahuvr. f. (-र्णी) A creeper and medicinal plant, <BR>‘of pungent and astringent properties, employed as a sto<BR>machic and against pains and enlargement of the spleen, <BR>rheumatism and diseases coming from disorders of the <BR>phlegmatic humour.’ See तीक्ष्णा, कण्डुरा, वयस्था. E. अत्यम्ल <BR>and पर्ण, with the fem. aff. ङीष्.

अत्यय
अत्यय m. (-यः) <BR>	1 Going over or beyond. <BR>	2 Surpassing. <BR>	3 Go<BR>ing or passing away. <BR>	4 Death. <BR>	5 Loss, destruction, end. <BR>	6 Transgression, sin, offence, guilt. <BR>	7 Vice, fault. <BR>	8 Distress. <BR>	9 Punishment. E. इ with अति, kṛt aff. अण्.

अत्ययिन्
अत्ययिन् m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Exceeding, excessive. E. <BR>इ with अति, kṛt aff. इनि (implying here nature, disposition).

अत्यराति
अत्यराति Tatpur. m. (-तिः) A proper name, the son of Ja<BR>nantapa. E. अति (sc. क्रान्तः) and अराति (in the sense of <BR>the accusative) ‘overcoming his enemies’.

अत्यर्थ
अत्यर्थ I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्थः-र्था-र्थम्) Very much, excessive. <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-र्थम्) Excessively. E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) <BR>and अर्थ (in the sense of the accusative).

अत्यल्प
अत्यल्प Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ल्पः-ल्पा-ल्पम्) Very small, very <BR>little. E. अति and अल्प.

अत्यवि
अत्यवि Tatpur. m. (-विः) (ved.) Going beyond the sheep, running <BR>beyond the sheep's tail serving as a filtre for sacrificial pur<BR>poses (an epithet of Soma in the Vedas). E. अति (sc. क्रान्तः) <BR>and अवि (in the sense of the accusative).

अत्यशन
अत्यशन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Eating too much, excess of eating. <BR>E. अति and अशन.

अत्यष्टि
अत्यष्टि Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) <BR>	1 The name of a class of metres re<BR>gulated by number and quantity. See अतिच्छन्दस्. It con<BR>sists of four lines with seventeen syllables to each line and <BR>comprises twelve varieties. (See <BR>	1 शिखरिणी, <BR>	2 पृथ्वी, <BR>	3 वं- <BR>शपत्रपतित or वंशपत्र, <BR>	4 हरिणी, <BR>	5 मन्दाक्रान्ता, <BR>	6 नर्कुटक or <BR>नर्धटक or अवितथ, <BR>	7 कोकिलक, <BR>	8 हरि, <BR>	9 कान्ता or क्रान्ता, <BR>	10 चित्रलेखा or अतिशयनी, <BR>	11 मालाधर or वनमालाधर, <BR>	12 हा- <BR>रिणी.) <BR>	2 (In arithmetic sometimes used to denote) the <BR>numeral 17. E. अति (sc. क्रान्ता) and अष्टि, another metre <BR>(in the sense of the accusative).

अत्यस्त
अत्यस्त m. f. n. (-स्तः-स्ता-स्तम्) Having overcome, having sur<BR>passed. (This word may form a compound with a word <BR>depending upon it in the accusative; f. i. तुहिनमत्यस्त or <BR>तुहिनात्यस्त.) E. अस् (to throw &c.) with अति, kṛt aff. क्त.

अत्यहम्
अत्यहम् Tatpur. m. Surpassing me. E. अति (sc. क्रान्तः) and <BR>अहम् (in the sense of माम्). This word seems to be only <BR>one of grammatical coinage and scarcely to occur in the <BR>real language. See also अतिमान्, अतिमाम्, अतिवयम्; <BR>and अतित्वम्.

अत्यह्न
अत्यह्न Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ह्नः-ह्ना-ह्नम्) Passing beyond one <BR>day, lasting more than one day. E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and <BR>अहन् (in the sense of the accusative), samāsānta aff. टच्.

अत्याकार
अत्याकार m. (-रः) Censure, blame, contempt. E. कृ with <BR>आ and अति, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अत्याचार
अत्याचार Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Deviating from <BR>prescribed observances, contemning religious and moral laws. <BR>E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and आचार (in the sense of the accusative). <BR>II. m. (-रः) Observance of uncommanded and unnecessary <BR>rites or practices. E. अति and आचार.

अत्यादान
अत्यादान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Taking away too much. E. अति <BR>and आदान.

अत्यादित्य
अत्यादित्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) Surpassing the sun. <BR>E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and आदित्य (in the sense of the accus.).

अत्याधान
अत्याधान n. (-नम्) <BR>	1 Putting over, placing over or beyond. <BR>	2 A groundless demand, an imposition. E. धा with आ and <BR>अति, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अत्यानन्दा
अत्यानन्दा Tatpur. f. (-न्दा) A morbid affection of the female or<BR>gans of generation, described as ‘when the woman has no pleas<BR>ure in the embraces of her husband’. See योनिव्यापद्. E. अति <BR>(sc. क्रान्ता) and आनन्द (the sense of the accus.), sc. योनि.

अत्याय
अत्याय m. (-यः) Exceeding, transgressing. E. इ with अति, <BR>kṛt aff. ण.

अत्याल
अत्याल Tatpur. m. (-लः) The name of a plant (Plumbago <BR>rosea). See रक्तचित्रक. E. अति and आल.

अत्याशा
अत्याशा Tatpur. f. (-शा) Unreasonable hope or desire. E. <BR>अति and आशा.

अत्याश्रमिन्
अत्याश्रमिन् m. (-मी) An ascetic of the highest degree, one <BR>who is above the four orders or āśramas. E. अत्याश्रम <BR>(अति and आश्रम), taddh. aff. इनि.

अत्यासम्
अत्यासम् ind. After the lapse of; only used in composition, <BR>f. i. द्व्यहात्यासम्, ‘after the lapse of two days’. E. अस् <BR>with अति, kṛt aff. णमुल्.

अत्याहार
अत्याहार Tatpur. m. (-रः) Excessive food. E. अति and आहार.

अत्याहारिन्
अत्याहारिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Eating ex<BR>cessively, a glutton, a gormandizer. E. अति and आहारिन्.

अत्याहित
अत्याहित Tatpur. n. (-तम्) <BR>	1 Great dread. <BR>	2 Desperate or <BR>daring action. E. अति and आहित.

अत्युक्ता
अत्युक्ता Tatpur. f. (-क्ता) The name of a class of metres, regulated <BR>by number and quantity; it consists of a stanza of four lines <BR>with two syllables in each line and comprises four varieties. <BR>(See <BR>	1 स्त्री or काम, <BR>	2 रति or मही, <BR>	3 सारु, <BR>	4 मधु.) Also called <BR>अत्युक्था. E. अति (sc. क्रान्ता) and उक्ता, another class of <BR>metres (in the sense of the accusative).

अत्युक्ति
अत्युक्ति Tatpur. f. (-क्तिः) <BR>	1 Idle or excessive talk. <BR>	2 A figure <BR>of rhetoric, description of any thing surprising or extra<BR>ordinary, hyperbole. E. अति and उक्ति.

अत्युक्था
अत्युक्था Tatpur. f. (-क्था). See अत्युक्ता. E. अति (sc. क्रान्ता) <BR>and उक्था (in the sense of the accusative).

अत्युग्र
अत्युग्र Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ग्रः-ग्रा-ग्रम्) <BR>	1 Very hot, very <BR>sharp or pungent. <BR>	2 Very formidable. <BR>II. n. (-ग्रम्) Asa foetida. E. अति and उग्र.

अत्युच्चैर्ध्वनि
अत्युच्चैर्ध्वनि Tatpur. m. (-नि) A very loud sound, a very high <BR>note. E. अत्युच्चैस् and ध्वनि.

अत्युच्चैस्
अत्युच्चैस् Tatpur. ind. Very loud, very high (as a sound, a <BR>note). E. अति and उच्चैस्.

अत्युत्कट
अत्युत्कट Tatpur. m. f. n. (-टः-टा-टम्) Exceedingly great. <BR>E. अति and उत्कट.

अत्युपध
अत्युपध Tatpur. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्) Above trial, proved, <BR>sincere, upright. E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and उपधा (in the <BR>sense of the accusative).

अत्युल्वण
अत्युल्वण Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Excessive, very <BR>much. E. अति and उल्वण.

अत्युष्ण
अत्युष्ण Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्णः-ष्णा-ष्णम्) Very hot. E. अति <BR>and उष्ण.

अत्यूमशा
अत्यूमशा ind. A particle of abuse or reproach(?), used only <BR>in composition with अस्, भू, कृ. E. unknown; comp. ऊम.

अत्यूर्मि
अत्यूर्मि m. f. n. (-र्मिः-र्मिः-र्मि) (ved.) Overflowing. E. ऋ with <BR>अति, uṇ. aff. मि and ऊ substituted for the initial अ.

अत्यूह
अत्यूह Bahuvr. I. m. (-हः) A gallinule. <BR>II. f. (-हा) A plant (Jasminum villosum, Rox. or in <BR>Bengal, Nyctanthes tristis). See नीलिका or शेफालिका. <BR>E. अति and ऊह.

अत्र
अत्र I. ind. <BR>	1 In this place, here, herein. <BR>	2 In conjunction <BR>with nouns used in the same sense as एतस्मिन्, the locat. <BR>of एतद्; f. i. अत्राह्नि = एतस्मिन्नह्नि, ‘on that day’.--In <BR>the Vedas also written अत्रा which seems to be the more <BR>original form of this word. E. अश् (i. e. अ which, in <BR>this instance, is considered as a substitute of एतद् (and <BR>not of इदम्), because अत्र points always to what pre<BR>cedes), taddh. aff. त्रल्. <BR>II. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Not protecting. E. अ <BR>neg. and त्र. <BR>III. m. (-त्रः) (ved.) A demon, a Rākṣasa. E. अद्, uṇ. <BR>aff. त्र (literally: ‘one who eats or devours’). See अत्त्र. <BR>IV. n. (-त्रम्) (ved.) Food. E. अद्, uṇ. aff. ष्ट्रन्. See अत्त्र.

अत्रदघ्न
अत्रदघ्न m. f. n. (-घ्नः-घ्नी-घ्नम्) Having that size, being of <BR>that height. E. अत्र, taddh. aff. दघ्नच्, in the fem. with <BR>aff. ङीप्; or more correctly, a Bahuvr. consisting of अत्र <BR>and an obsolete noun दघ्न q. v.

अत्रप
अत्रप Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Shameless, immodest. <BR>E. अ priv. and त्रपा.

अत्रभवत्
अत्रभवत् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Respectable, ve<BR>nerable (especially in theatrical language used as a respect<BR>ful mode of address). E. अत्र and भवत्. See also तत्रभवत्.

अत्रवस्
अत्रवस् ind. The last year but one. E. अत्र, taddh. aff. वस्(?). <BR>This word is of doubtful authority.

अत्रस्नु
अत्रस्नु Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्नुः-स्नुः-स्नु) Not timid, fearless. <BR>E. अ neg. and त्रस्नु.

अत्रास
अत्रास Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-सः-सा-सम्) Fearless. E. अ priv. and त्रास.

अत्रि
अत्रि m. (-त्रिः) <BR>	1 Eater, devourer (in the Vedas especially as <BR>an epithet of Agni, the divinity of fire). <BR>	2 The name of a <BR>Maharshi or a great Saint, who in the Vedas occurs especi<BR>ally in hymns composed for the praise of Agni, Indra, the <BR>Aśvins and the Viśvadevas; and who in the epic period <BR>is considered as one of the ten Prajāpatis or lords of crea<BR>tion engendered by Manu for the purpose of creating the <BR>universe; at a later period he appears as a mindborn son <BR>of Brahmā and as one of the seven Ṛṣis who preside <BR>over the reign of Svāyambhuva, the first, or according to <BR>others of Svārochiṣa, the second, or of Vaivaswata, the <BR>seventh Manu; he is married to Anasūyā, the daughter of <BR>Daksha and their son is Durvāsas. Produced by a flash of <BR>light from his eye which was received by Space, the via <BR>lactea personified, or according to a more recent legend, <BR>by his penitence, is Soma or the moon. See अत्रिजात, <BR>अत्रिदृग्ज, अत्रिनेत्रज &c. As sons of his are also named <BR>the Manes Barhishads and Udamaya; a daughter of his is <BR>Apālā. The name of Atri occurs also as that of the author <BR>of several vaidik hymns, as that of an inspired legislator, <BR>of the author of an astronomical and medical work and, <BR>in astronomy, as one of the seven Ṛṣis in the constel<BR>lation of the great bear.--An Atri, son of Sāṅkhya, but <BR>probably a different personage, is the author of a hymn in <BR>the Ṛgveda.--Amongst the authors of vaidik hymns we <BR>find as sons or descendants of Atri the following: Archa<BR>nāna, Avasyu, Bāhuvṛkta, Bhauma, Budha, Dvita, Ga<BR>viṣṭhira, Gaya, Gopavana, Isha, Paura, Pratibhānu, Pra<BR>tiprabha, the Prayaswats, Purīṣa, Ratahavya, Sadāpṛṇa, <BR>Saptavadhri, Śaśa, Satyaśravas, Śrutavid, Sutambhara, <BR>Śyāvāśva, Vasuśruta, the Vasūyus, Viśvasāman, Yajata; <BR>and as daughters of Atri, Apālā, Gātu, Viśvavārā. <BR>	3 m. <BR>pl. (अत्रयः) The descendants (see गोत्र) of Atri collectively. <BR>(The masc. plur. अत्रयः is considered as the plur. of the <BR>patronymic आत्रेय (q. v.) with luk of the taddh. aff. ढक्; <BR>the plural of the fem., however, remaining regular, viz. <BR>आत्रेय्यः; but there is no necessity to adopt this artificial <BR>etymology which is given to connect the sense of the pa<BR>tronymic with that of the plur. of the original form.) E. <BR>See अत्त्रि.

अत्रिचतुरह
अत्रिचतुरह Tatpur. m. (-हः) The name of a sacrifice, be<BR>longing to the class of those called अहीन q. v. E. अत्रि <BR>and चतुरह.

अत्रिजात
अत्रिजात Tatpur. m. (-तः) <BR>	1 The moon. <BR>	2 A man of the three <BR>first classes. E. <BR>	1 अत्रि and जात. See for the meaning under <BR>अत्रि. <BR>	2 अ neg., त्रि and जात ‘not thrice born, i. e. born <BR>twice’; see द्विज.

अत्रिदृग्ज
अत्रिदृग्ज Tatpur. m. (-जः) <BR>	1 The moon. <BR>	2 (In arithmetic <BR>sometimes used to denote) the numeral one. E. अत्रि-दृश् <BR>(eye) and ज. See for the meaning of this word and of its <BR>synonymes under अत्रि.

अत्रिन्
अत्रिन् m. (-त्री) (ved.) A Rākṣasa, a demon. (Literally: one <BR>who eats or devours.) E. See अत्त्रिन्.

अत्रिनेत्रज
अत्रिनेत्रज Tatpur. m. (-जः). See अत्रिदृग्ज. E. अत्रि-नेत्र and ज.

अत्रिनेत्रप्रसूत
अत्रिनेत्रप्रसूत Tatpur. m. (-तः). See अत्रिदृग्ज. E. अत्रि-नेत्र <BR>and प्रसूत.

अत्रिनेत्रभव
अत्रिनेत्रभव Tatpur. m. (-वः). See अत्रिदृग्ज. E. अत्रि-नेत्र <BR>and भव.

अत्रिनेत्रभू
अत्रिनेत्रभू Tatpur. m. (-भूः). See अत्रिदृग्ज. E. अत्रि-नेत्र <BR>and भू.

अत्रिनेत्रसूत
अत्रिनेत्रसूत Tatpur. m. (-तः). See अत्रिदृग्ज. E. अत्रि-नेत्र <BR>and सूत.

अत्रिभारद्वाजिका
अत्रिभारद्वाजिका f. (-का) The marriage union of Atri and <BR>Bhāradvājī. E. अत्रि and भारद्वाजी (as Dwandwa), taddh. <BR>aff. वुञ् implying in this and similar Dwandwa compounds <BR>condition or action. The more correct form of this word <BR>seems to be आत्रिभारद्वाजिका.

अत्रिवत्
अत्रिवत् ind. Like Atri of like the descendants of Atri. E. <BR>अत्रि, taddh. aff. वति.

अत्रिसंहिता
अत्रिसंहिता Tatpur. f. (-ता) The name of a law-book ascribed <BR>to Atri. E. अत्रि and संहिता.

अत्रिस्मृति
अत्रिस्मृति Tatpur. f. (-तिः) The same as the preceding. E. <BR>अत्रि and स्मृति.

अत्वरा
अत्वरा Tatpur. f. (-रा) Want of haste or precipitation. E. <BR>अ neg. and त्वरा.

अथ
अथ ind. An inceptive and auspicious particle. It serves to <BR>introduce the beginning of a work, a chapter, a sentence <BR>and with respect to the latter may imply doubt or inter<BR>rogation or may serve as a conjunctive or disjunctive par<BR>ticle. It may be accompanied by those particles or words <BR>which themselves are used in the same sense, giving them <BR>greater emphasis, especially by उ, अतस्, अनन्तरम्, किम्, <BR>तु, पुनर्, वा, किमु, अपि. Without or with these particles <BR>अथ corresponds therefore with: <BR>	1 Now (inceptive or pre<BR>mising); in the same sense but with greater emphasis अथो <BR>(अथ and उ), अथातस्, अथानन्तरम्. <BR>	2 Why? what? (in<BR>terrogatively and doubtingly); (likewise अथवा.) <BR>	3 How <BR>else? certainly; (in the same sense अथकिम्.) <BR>	4 But, on the <BR>contrary; (in the same sense अथ तु, अथ पुनर्.) <BR>	5 Or, or <BR>rather; (likewise अथवा, अथवापि, अथापि वा &c.) <BR>	6 More<BR>over, so much the more, therefore, thus; (likewise अथच, <BR>अथापि, अथो अपि, अथ किमु.) In the Vedas there occurs <BR>also the protracted form अथा which seems to be the more <BR>original one; (cf. तथा and यथा). E. According to the native <BR>authorities from अर्थ्, kṛt aff. ड with र् being dropped; <BR>but it is more probably derived from अ, the pron. theme <BR>which is considered as a substitute for इदम् (pointing to <BR>what follows), taddh. aff. थ.

अथकिम्
अथकिम् ind. A particle of assent, how else, what else, as<BR>suredly. (Better to be considered as two words. See अथ.) <BR>E. अथ and किम्.

अथकिमु
अथकिमु ind. So much the more. (Better to be considered as <BR>two separate words and also written अथ किमु. See अथ.) <BR>E. अथ and किमु.

अथच
अथच ind. Also, moreover. (Better to be considered as two <BR>words. See अथ.) E. अथ and च.

अथतु
अथतु ind. But, on the contrary. (More properly to be con<BR>sidered as two distinct words and also written अथ तु. See <BR>अथ.) E. अथ and तु.

अथरी
अथरी f. (occurs only as a plural in the Vedas; -र्यः) The <BR>finger. E. This word is given as an irregular derivation <BR>from अत् ‘to go constantly’; but it is more probable that <BR>it is derived, with aff. अरि, from an obsolete rad. अथ् <BR>which seems to have had the same meaning as अत् (cf. <BR>अट् and अठ्), but is found only in अथरी, अथर्वन् and their <BR>derivatives, implying quickness or agility. The same etymo<BR>logical connexion between words meaning ‘finger’ and ‘fire’ <BR>may be perceived in other derivations from a radical in the <BR>sense of ‘to go’ f. i. in अङ्गुलि or अङ्गुरि, अग्रू and अग्नि, अङ्गिरस्, <BR>from अङ्ग्. It reappears distinctly in the denom. अथर्य् and <BR>its derivatives अथर्य, अथर्यु qq. vv.

अथर्य्
अथर्य् par. (-र्यति) To go, to move. (Only in the Vedas.) <BR>Probably a denominative from अथरी or अथर् with aff. यक्.

अथर्य
अथर्य m. (-र्यः) Moving constantly; an epithet of Agni in the <BR>Vedas. See also the following. E. अथर्य्, kṛt aff. अच्(?). <BR>A commentary explains, that अथर्य is an epithet of दक्षि- <BR>णाग्नि, because the sacred fire ‘goes always’ from the Gār<BR>hapatya (q. v.) to his proper place; the epithet may be con<BR>sidered, however, as one of a more general bearing.

अथर्यु
अथर्यु m. (-युः) Moving constantly; an epithet of Agni in the <BR>Vedas. See the preceding. E. अथर्य्, kṛt aff. उ.

अथर्व
अथर्व m. (-र्वः) A proper name of the eldest son of Brahmā, <BR>to whom Brahmā revealed the Brahmavidyā (q. v.) or know<BR>ledge of God. See अथर्वन्. E. See अथर्वन् of which it is <BR>an abbreviated form.

अथर्वण
अथर्वण m. (-णः) A name of Śiva. E. अथर्वन्, taddh. aff. अ(?).

अथर्वणि
अथर्वणि m. (-णिः) <BR>	1 A Brahman versed in the Atharvaveda. <BR>	2 A family priest. E. See आथर्वणि which is the better <BR>reading of this word.

अथर्वन्
अथर्वन् 1. m. (-र्वा) <BR>	1 A Brāhmaṇa, a priest (probably one <BR>connected with offerings to fire or the attendance on the <BR>holy fire). <BR>	2 The proper name of a priest who is considered <BR>to have obtained the fire from heaven and who in the course <BR>of mythological personification appears as a Prajāpati or <BR>father of all beings, as the inspired author of the fourth <BR>or Atharvaveda, as the eldest son of Brahmā to whom <BR>Brahmā revealed the Brahmavidyā (q. v.) or knowledge of <BR>God (see also अथर्व) and, at a later period, as the same <BR>as Angiras (q. v.). Sons of his are Agni (see also अङ्गिरस्), <BR>Dadhyanch, Bhishaj, Bṛhaddiva, Kabandha. <BR>	3 An epithet of <BR>	a. Vasiṣṭha q. v., <BR>	b. Soma q. v., <BR>	c. प्राण q. v., <BR>	d. Śiva (the god being <BR>supposed to carry into effect the charms of the Atharvaveda). <BR>2. m. n. (-र्वा-र्व) The fourth or Atharvaveda q. v. (see <BR>also m. pl. अथर्वाणः). <BR>3. m. pl. (-र्वाणः) <BR>	1 The descendants of Atharvan; they <BR>appear sometimes coupled with the descendants of Bhṛgu <BR>and of Angiras (see अथर्वाङ्गिरसः). <BR>	2 The hymns of the <BR>fourth or Atharvaveda collectively (considered as the descen<BR>dants of Atharvan); the Atharvaveda (see also अथर्वाङ्गि- <BR>रसः). E. From an obsolete theme अथर्, fire, with taddh. <BR>aff. वनिप्. See the E. of अथरी. The oldest etym. which <BR>derives अथर्वन् from अ neg. and थर्वन् (from थर्व् ‘to go’), <BR>is without any probability. A similar etym. is given of <BR>अथर्वी q. v.

अथर्वभूत
अथर्वभूत Tatpur. m. pl. (-ताः) An epithet of the twelve Maharshis: <BR>धर्म, दक्ष, मरीचि, अत्रि, पुलस्त्य, पुलह, क्रतु, वसिष्ठ, गौ- <BR>तम, भृगु, अङ्गिरस्, मनु and (according to a commentary) <BR>of ‘Rudra, the Lord of the Universe’. E. अथर्वन् and भूत <BR>(according to a commentary from भू, to obtain, ‘having <BR>obtained i. e. versed in the Atharvaveda, the same as अ- <BR>थर्वविद्’).

अथर्ववत्
अथर्ववत् ind. Like Atharvan or the descendants of Atharvan. <BR>E. अथर्वन्, taddh. aff. वति.

अथर्वविद्
अथर्वविद् Tatpur. m. (-वित्) One versed in the Atharvaveda. <BR>See अथर्वभूत. According to the Pariśiṣṭa of this Veda esp. <BR>an epithet of the priest called Brahman q. v. See ब्रह्मवेद. <BR>E. अथर्वन् and विद्.

अथर्ववेद
अथर्ववेद Tatpur. m. (-दः) The fourth or Atharvaveda (see <BR>ऋच्, यजुस्, सामन्), the Veda revealed by Atharvan or <BR>Angiras and sometimes considered, therefore, personified <BR>as a son of Angiras. See अथर्वन्, अथर्वाङ्गिरस्, प्रत्यङ्गिरस्, <BR>ब्रह्मवेद. E. अथर्वन् and वेद.

अथर्वशिखा
अथर्वशिखा Tatpur. f. (-खा) The name of one of the Upani<BR>shads of the Atharvaveda. E. अथर्वन् and शिखा ‘the crest’ <BR>i. e. (according to the comm.) the essence of the Atharvaveda.

अथर्वशिरस्
अथर्वशिरस् Tatpur. n. (-रः) The name of an Upanishad of <BR>the Atharvaveda. E. अथर्वन् and शिरस् ‘the head’ i. e. <BR>the principal Upanishad of the A. V.

अथर्वहृदय
अथर्वहृदय Tatpur. n. (-यम्) The name of a Pariśiṣṭa of the <BR>Atharvaveda. E. अथर्वन् and हृदय.

अथर्वाङ्गिरस्
अथर्वाङ्गिरस् I. Tatpur. m. (-राः) The Angiras of the Athar<BR>vaveda. This use of the word, as a Tatpur. in the sing., <BR>is of later origin than that of the Dwandwa in the plur., <BR>and, as it seems, adopted to explain the form अथर्वाङ्गि- <BR>रस q. v. <BR>II. Dwandwa. m. pl. (-रसः) <BR>	1 The descendants of Athar<BR>van and of Angiras. <BR>	2 The Atharvaveda hymns of both <BR>collectively; the Atharvaveda (q. v.), one part (or parvan) <BR>of which is considered to have been revealed by the descen<BR>dants of Atharvan and another by the descendants of An<BR>giras. According to another explanation, however, this <BR>name of the Atharvaveda would merely refer to Atharvan <BR>(q. v.) being the inspired author of one part and Angiras <BR>(q. v.) of the other. E. अथर्वन् and अङ्गिरस्.

अथर्वाङ्गिरस
अथर्वाङ्गिरस I. m. f. n. (-सः-सी-सम्) Referring or belonging <BR>to the अथर्वाङ्गिरसः q. v. <BR>II. n. (-सम्) The religious observances (कर्मन्) connected <BR>with the ritual of the Atharvaveda. <BR>III. m. pl. (-साः) The mantras or hymns of the Athar<BR>vaveda. E. अथर्वाङ्गिरस्, taddh. aff. टच्.

अथर्वाण
अथर्वाण n. (-णम्) The religious observances (कर्मन्) connected <BR>with the ritual of the Atharvaveda. E. Irregular derivation <BR>from अथर्वन्, taddh. aff. अण्(?).

अथर्वाणविद्
अथर्वाणविद् Tatpur. m. (-त्) One versed in the rites of the <BR>Atharvaveda. E. अथर्वाण and विद्.

अथर्वी
अथर्वी Tatpur. f. (-वी). This word occurs only in the Veda <BR>and is explained ‘not going, unable to move’, from अ <BR>neg. and थर्वी (from थर्व्, to go). It would seem, how<BR>ever, that it is a Tatpur. composed of the obsolete word <BR>अथर्, fire, and वी, ‘surrounded by fire’(?). See the E. <BR>of अथर्वन् and अथरी.

अथवा
अथवा ind. <BR>	1 Why? what? <BR>	2 Or, or rather. See अथ. E. अथ <BR>and वा.

अथवापि
अथवापि ind. Or, or rather. More properly to be considered <BR>as two separate words, अथवा and अपि. See अथ. E. अथ- <BR>वा and अपि.

अथातस्
अथातस् ind. Now (inceptive or premising). More properly to <BR>be considered as two distinct words. See अथ. E. अथ and <BR>अतस्.

अथानन्तरम्
अथानन्तरम् ind. The same as the preceding; better considered <BR>as two separate words. See अथ. E. अथ and अनन्तरम्.

अथापि
अथापि ind. Moreover, so much the more, therefore, thus; better <BR>considered as two distinct words. See अथ. E. अथ and अपि.

अथो
अथो ind. Now (inceptive or premising). (According to some <BR>it has the same meanings as अथ.) अथो अपि, moreover &c. <BR>See अथ. E. अथ and उ.

अद्
अद् I. (अद-अदादि-अनुदात्त-उदात्तेत्) r. 2d cl. par. <BR>(अत्ति- imperf. आदत्- imper. अद्धि, ep. अदस्व- perf. आद, <BR>2d pers. आदिथ- fut. 1. अत्स्यति, 2. अत्ता- inf. अत्तुम्- p. p. <BR>अदित (अन्न only used as subst.). Pass. अद्यते. Caus. आद- <BR>यति-ते.--For the tenses which are not formed of अद्, <BR>see घस् which is then considered as a substitute of it.) <BR>To eat. (Caus. To feed.)--With अव(?)-आ-प्र-सम् <BR>to eat, to devour; वि- to gnaw, to nibble. <BR>II. m. f. n. (अत्) Eating. This word occurs only as the <BR>latter part of a Tatpur., the former part of which may be <BR>any word but अन्न (which forms अन्नाद and not अन्नाद्). <BR>See f. i. अहुताद्, आमाद्, क्रव्याद्. E. अद्, kṛt aff. विट्.

अद
अद m. f. n. (-दः-दी-दम्) Eating; (occurs only as the latter <BR>part of Tatpur. compounds). See f. i. अजाद, अतृणाद, अ- <BR>न्नाद. E. अद्, kṛt aff. अण्.

अदक्ष
अदक्ष Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) Awkward, unskilful. <BR>E. अ neg. and दक्ष.

अदक्षिण
अदक्षिण m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) I. Tatpur. <BR>	1 Not right, left. <BR>	2 Not clever, unskilful. E. अ neg. and दक्षिण. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Being or being performed without the presents <BR>usually given to Brahmans (see दक्षिणा), as a sacrifice &c. <BR>The celebration of a sacrifice without the Dakṣiṇā oc<BR>curs for instance under the following circumstances: at <BR>the Prātaḥsavana of the Jyotiṣṭoma, when about to sing <BR>the Vahiṣpavamāna stotra, the priests step out from the <BR>house where the sacred fire is kept, one going after the <BR>other and holding the one who precedes by the hem of his <BR>garment: if it so happens, at this procession, that the <BR>Udgātṛ inadvertently drops the hem, the sacrifice goes on <BR>without the Dakṣiṇā; once accomplished, however, it is <BR>to be repeated and then the Udgātṛ has to pay the Dakṣiṇā <BR>which should have been given at the first performance; if <BR>the Pratihartṛ meets with a similar accident, he has to pay <BR>his whole property at the renewal of the ceremony, which <BR>then is called सर्वस्वदक्षिण. E. अ priv. and दक्षिणा.

अदक्षिणत्व
अदक्षिणत्व n. (-त्वम्) <BR>	1 Leftness, unskilfulness &c. <BR>	2 The state <BR>of a sacrifice performed without the Dakṣiṇā. See the pre<BR>ceding. E. अदक्षिण, taddh. aff. त्व.

अदक्षिणीय
अदक्षिणीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not worth <BR>the sacrificial gift or दक्षिणा q. v. E. अ neg. and दक्षि- <BR>णीय.

अदक्षिण्य
अदक्षिण्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) The same as the <BR>preceding. E. अ neg. and दक्षिण्य.

अदग्ध
अदग्ध Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्धः-ग्धा-ग्धम्) Not burnt, un<BR>scorched. E. अ neg. and दग्ध.

अदण्ड
अदण्ड I. Tatpur. n. (-ण्डम्) Impunity. E. अ neg. and दण्ड. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ण्डः-ण्डा-ण्डम्) Unpunished. E. <BR>अ priv. and दण्ड.

अदण्ड्य
अदण्ड्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ण्ड्यः-ण्ड्या-ण्ड्यम्) <BR>	1 Unpunishable, <BR>exempt from punishment. <BR>	2 Not deserving punishment. E. <BR>अ neg. and दण्ड्य.

अदण्डनीय
अदण्डनीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Unpunishable, un<BR>fit to be punished, exempt from punishment. E. अ neg. <BR>and दण्डनीय.

अदत्
अदत् I. m. f. n. (-दन्-दन्ती-दत्) Eating. E. अद्, kṛt <BR>aff. शतृ. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-दन्-दती-दत्) Having no teeth, <BR>toothless. E. अ priv. and दत्, considered as a substitute <BR>of दन्त.

अदत्क
अदत्क Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Toothless. E. अदत् II. <BR>q. v., samāsānta aff. कप्.

अदत्त
अदत्त I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Not given. 2. f. <BR>(-त्ता) An unmarried girl. 3. n. (-त्तम्) (In law.) A void <BR>and resumable donation (see दत्त, देय, अदेय). E. अ neg. <BR>and दत्त. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Not having given. <BR>E. अ priv. and दत्त.

अदद्र्यञ्च्
अदद्र्यञ्च् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्र्यङ्-द्रीची-द्र्यक्) Going to that. <BR>(This word is probably one of a mere grammatical coinage, <BR>to illustrate a rule concerning the pronom. theme अदस्. <BR>According to some it would have the same meaning as अ- <BR>दमुयञ्च्, अमुद्र्यञ्च् and अमुमुयञ्च् to which others add अद- <BR>मुद्र्यञ्च्, अमुमूयञ्च्, अदमूयञ्च् qq. vv., but it might also be <BR>that अदद्र्यञ्च् (as well as अदमुयञ्च्, अदमुद्र्यञ्च्, अदमूयञ्च्) <BR>is formed to show that its first part represents not the <BR>whole theme, but merely the neuter of अदस्, while the <BR>first part of अमुद्र्यञ्च्, अमुमुयञ्च् and अमुमूयञ्च् refer to its <BR>masc. and femin. For the declension of this word, see <BR>अञ्च् II. E. अदस् and अञ्च् (II. 1.), with अद्रि instead of <BR>the final अस् of अदस्.

अदन
अदन n. (-नम्) <BR>	1 Eating. <BR>	2 Food. E. अद्, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अदन्त
अदन्त Bahuvr. I. 1. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Toothless. See <BR>the preceding. <BR>2. m. (-न्तः) A leech. E. अ priv. and दन्त. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) (In grammar.) Ending in <BR>the short vowel ‘a’. E. अत् (the grammatical designation <BR>of short ‘a’ and अन्त.

अदन्तक
अदन्तक Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Toothless. E. अदन्त, <BR>samāsānta aff. कप्.

अदन्त्य
अदन्त्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्त्यः-न्त्या-न्त्यम्) <BR>	1 Prejudicial to the <BR>teeth. <BR>	2 Different from or other than what is fit for the teeth. <BR>E. अ neg. and दन्त्य; in the first meaning which is the usual <BR>one, the word is an oxytonon, in the latter a proparoxytonon.

अदब्ध
अदब्ध Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ब्धः-ब्धा-ब्धम्) (ved.) Unhurt, un<BR>injured, entire, pure &c. E. अ neg. and दब्ध.

अदब्धव्रत
अदब्धव्रत Bahuvr. m. (-तः) (ved.) One whose devotions or <BR>religious observances are unbroken. E. अदब्ध and व्रत.

अदब्धव्रतप्रमति
अदब्धव्रतप्रमति m. (-तिः) (ved.) I. Bahuvr. One whose mind is <BR>superior in having his devotions or observances unbroken, <BR>or II. Dwandwa. One whose devotions or observances are <BR>unbroken and whose mind is superior (an epithet of Agni). <BR>E. अदब्धव्रत and प्रमति. If a Bahuvr., the former part <BR>stands in the sense of the locative.

अदब्धायु
अदब्धायु m. (-युः) Having uninjured or pure food, an epithet <BR>of Agni in the Vedas. (According to a commentary: leaving <BR>uninjured the man who institutes the sacrifice. E. अदब्ध <BR>and आयु.)

अदभ्र
अदभ्र Tatpur. m. f. n. (-भ्रः-भ्रा-भ्रम्) Not little, much. E. अ <BR>neg. and दभ्र.

अदमुद्र्यञ्च्
अदमुद्र्यञ्च् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्र्यङ्-द्रीची-द्र्यक्) Going to that. <BR>See अदद्र्यञ्च् and the forms mentioned there. For the de<BR>clension of this word see अञ्च् II. E. Irreg. composition of <BR>अदस् and अञ्च् II. 1. See the following.

अदमुयञ्च्
अदमुयञ्च् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यङ्-ईची-यक्) Going to that. <BR>See the preceding and अदद्र्यञ्च्; for the declension see अञ्च् II. <BR>E. Irreg. compos. of अदस् and अञ्च्. Also read अदमूयञ्च्.

अदमूयञ्च्
अदमूयञ्च् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यङ्-ईची-यक्). See the preceding.

अदम्भ
अदम्भ I. Tatpur. m. (-म्भः) Want of hypocrisy or deceit, <BR>straightforwardness, sincerity. E. अ neg. and दम्भ. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-म्भः-म्भा-म्भम्) Without deceit, <BR>upright, straightforward, sincere. 2. m. (-म्भः) A name <BR>of Śiva. E. अ priv. and दम्भ.

अदम्य
अदम्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-म्यः-म्या-म्यम्) Uncontrollable, un<BR>tamable. E. अ neg. and दम्य.

अदय
अदय Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Unfeeling, unmerciful, <BR>destitute of pity. अदयम् used adverbially. E. अ priv. <BR>and दया.

अदर
अदर Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not little, much. E. अ <BR>neg. and दर.

अदरक
अदरक m. (-कः) A proper name(?). E. unknown.

अदर्श
अदर्श m. (-र्शः) <BR>	1 Day of the new moon. See दर्श. <BR>	2 A mirror. <BR>See आदर्श. E. This word seems to be an incorrect reading <BR>of दर्श or आदर्श; but in the former sense it may be a <BR>Tatpur. composed of अ neg. and दर्श.

अदर्शन
अदर्शन I. Tatpur. n. (-नम्) <BR>	1 Not seeing. <BR>	2 Disappearance, <BR>not being visible or present (in grammar f. i. of a letter, <BR>an affix &c.). E. अ neg. and दर्शन. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Invisible, disappear<BR>ing. E. अ priv. and दर्शन.

अदर्शनीय
अदर्शनीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Invisible. E. अ <BR>neg. and दर्शनीय.

अदल
अदल Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Leafless. <BR>II. m. (-लः) A plant (Eugenia acutangula). See हिज्जल. <BR>III. f. (-ला) Socotrine aloe (Aloe perfoliata). See घृ- <BR>तकुमारी. E. अ priv. and दल.

अदस्
अदस् I. m. f. n. (असौ-असौ-अदस्). The pronoun (see सर्व- <BR>नामन्) which generally points to what is absent, remote <BR>or uncertain (differently from इदम् q. v.) and which cor<BR>responds with <BR>	1 That. <BR>	2 A certain (so and so). In correlative <BR>phrases it stands therefore usually in the prior sentence, <BR>imparting greater emphasis. Its declension is defective in <BR>as far as most of its cases are supplied by the themes असु <BR>or अस, अमु (अमू) and अमि (अमी). The theme which ap <BR>pears in composition is अदस् (except in the forms अद- <BR>द्र्यञ्च् &c. q. v. See also अद्धा). In some derivations of rare <BR>occurrence we meet also with the themes असु, अस and अमु; <BR>see असुक, असक, अमुक. <BR>II. ind. (esp. in composition with radicals (see गति), <BR>when employed reflectively). So, in such a manner, f. i. <BR>अदःकृत्य having done so &c.--In conjunction with a re<BR>lative pronoun or particle it has the effect of giving em<BR>phasis or of generalising, e. g. यददस् whatever, यत्रादस् <BR>wherever, यथादस् howsoever. E. unknown; but it is pro<BR>bably derived from the theme अद् which occurs in अद- <BR>द्र्यञ्च् and अद्धा.

अदस्य्
अदस्य् denom. par. (-स्यति) To become that. E. अदस्, de<BR>nom. aff. यक्.

अदातृ
अदातृ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ता-त्री-तृ) <BR>	1 Not giving. <BR>	2 Not liberal, <BR>miserly. <BR>	3 Not paying (a debt &c.). <BR>	4 Not giving in mar<BR>riage (a daughter, as a father). E. अ neg. and दातृ.

अदादि
अदादि Bahuvr. m. (-दिः) (In grammar.) The verbs of the <BR>second class, the list of which in the native dictionaries <BR>begins with अद्, to eat. E. अद् and आदि, sc. धातु.

अदान
अदान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Not giving, withholding. E. अ neg. <BR>and दान.

अदान्त
अदान्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Untamed, unsubdued, <BR>undaunted. E. अ neg. and दान्त.

अदाभ्य
अदाभ्य Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-भ्यः-भ्या-भ्यम्) Unhurtable, un<BR>injurable, irreproachable. <BR>II. m. (-भ्यः) The name of a Graha (q. v.) in the Jyo<BR>tiṣṭoma sacrifice. E. अ neg. and दाभ्य.

अदायाद
अदायाद m. f. n. (-दः-दा-दम्) I. Tatpur. Not being an heir, <BR>having no claim to be an heir. E. अ neg. and दायाद. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Being without an heir, unclaimed as in<BR>heritance. See the following. E. अ priv. and दायाद.

अदायिक
अदायिक Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) <BR>	1 Unclaimed, as in<BR>heritance, lapsed. <BR>	2 Not relating to inheritance. E. अ neg. <BR>and दायिक.

अदार
अदार Bahuvr. m. (-रः) Having no wife, unmarried. E. अ <BR>priv. and दार.

अदाशु
अदाशु Tatpur. m. (-शुः) (ved.) Not liberal, not pious. E. <BR>अ neg. and दाशु.

अदाशुरि
अदाशुरि Tatpur. m. (-रिः) (ved.) Not liberal, not pious. <BR>E. अ neg. and दाशुरि.

अदाश्वस्
अदाश्वस् Tatpur. m. (-श्वान्) (ved.) Not liberal, not pious. <BR>E. अ neg. and दाश्वस्.

अदास
अदास Tatpur. m. (-सः) Not a slave, a free man. E. अ neg. <BR>and दास.

अदाह्य
अदाह्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ह्यः-ह्या-ह्यम्) Inconsumable by <BR>fire, incombustible. E. अ neg. and दाह्य.

अदिक्क
अदिक्क Bahuvr. m. (-क्कः) Having no quarters, driven from <BR>all heavenly regions (an epithet of the Asuras in the Vedas). <BR>E. अ priv. and दिश्, samāsānta aff. कप्.

अदिति
अदिति I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः) <BR>	1 Entireness, the being unbroken <BR>or unhurt. <BR>	2 Exemption from defect or misery. <BR>	3 The full <BR>or unbroken creative power of the Prajāpati. E. अ neg. <BR>and दिति. <BR>II. Bahuvr. I. m. f. (-तिः-तिः) <BR>	1 Unbroken, unhurt. <BR>	2 Free from misery, happy. <BR>	3 Pious, holy. As Bahuvr.

अदिति
अदिति is in the Vedas often used as an epithet of Indra, <BR>the Maruts and Agni, but it becomes personified especially in <BR>2. f. (-तिः) which in the Vedas means <BR>	1 the earth, <BR>	2 a <BR>cow, <BR>	3 speech; but especially <BR>	4 Aditi, the first goddess of <BR>the intermediate space or air, the mother of the Gods, who <BR>at a later period was considered as the daughter of Daksha <BR>and wife of Kaśyapa, as the sister of Agastya and as the <BR>mother of the twelve Ādityas, of the eight Vasus, eleven <BR>Rudras and two Aśvins, besides of the thirty-six Tushitas. <BR>--Aditi is in a still later time also an appellative of Durgā. <BR>3. f. du. (-ती) (In the Vedas.) Heaven and earth. <BR>E. अ priv. and दिति. <BR>III. m. (-तिः) A name of Mṛtyu, the god of Death; <BR>literally: the eater or devourer. (This meaning of the word <BR>occurs only in a commentary of an Upanishad and is rather <BR>doubtful.) E. अद् (uṇ. aff. ति?).

अदितिज
अदितिज Tatpur. m. (-जः) A son of Aditi, a deity, a god. <BR>See अदितिनन्दन. E. अदिति and ज.

अदितित्व
अदितित्व n. (-त्वम्) <BR>	1 Unbrokenness, entireness, fullness of <BR>power. <BR>	2 The being Aditi (in the sense of Mṛtyu; see <BR>अदिति III). E. अदिति, taddh. aff. त्व.

अदितिनन्दन
अदितिनन्दन Tatpur. m. (-नः) The same as अदितिज. E. <BR>अदिति and नन्दन.

अदित्सत्
अदित्सत् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्सन्-त्सन्ती-त्सत्) Not willing to <BR>give. E. अ neg. and दित्सत्.

अदित्सु
अदित्सु Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्सुः-त्सुः-त्सु) Not willing to give. <BR>E. अ neg. and दित्सु.

अदिप्रभृति
अदिप्रभृति Bahuvr. m. (-तिः) The same as अदादि q. v. E. <BR>अदि i. e. अद् with a mute इ, and प्रभृति.

अदीक्षित
अदीक्षित Tatpur. m. (-तः) One who has not received or <BR>performed the दीक्षा q. v. E. अ neg. and दीक्षित.

अदीन
अदीन Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) <BR>	1 Not distressed. <BR>	2 Not vile, not mean. <BR>	3 Virtuous. <BR>II. m. (-नः) The name of a prince, a descendant of Āyus <BR>and son of Sahadeva. According to others his name is अ- <BR>हीन. E. अ neg. and दीन.

अदीनसत्त्व
अदीनसत्त्व Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्त्वः-त्त्वा-त्त्वम्) One whose na<BR>tural goodness has remained unaltered or unbroken. E. <BR>अदीन and सत्त्व.

अदीर्घ
अदीर्घ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्घः-र्घा-र्घम्) Not long. E. अ neg. <BR>and दीर्घ.

अदीर्घसूत्र
अदीर्घसूत्र Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Not dilatory, ‘prompt <BR>in beginning what must be done and in accomplishing what <BR>has been begun’. E. अ neg. and दीर्घसूत्र.

अदीर्घसूत्रता
अदीर्घसूत्रता f. (-ता) Dispatch. promptness. E. अदीर्घसूत्र, <BR>taddh. aff. ता.

अदुःख
अदुःख Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-खः-खा-खम्) Without pain or evil, <BR>propitious. E. अ priv. and दुःख.

अदुःखनवमी
अदुःखनवमी Karmadh. f. (-मी) A particular lunar day; the <BR>ninth of the first fortnight of the month Bhādrapada. On <BR>this day Devī is worshipped by women, that all evil may <BR>be averted during the ensuing year. E. अदुःख and नवमी.

अदुच्छुन
अदुच्छुन Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) (ved.) Without evil. <BR>E. अ priv. and दुच्छुना.

अदुर्ग
अदुर्ग m. f. n. (-र्गः-र्गा-र्गम्) I. Tatpur. Easy of access. E. <BR>अ neg. and दुर्ग. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Having no fortress. E. अ priv. and दुर्ग.

अदुष्ट
अदुष्ट Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) <BR>	1 Unspoiled, unvitiated. <BR>	2 Not very sinful, not wicked. <BR>	3 Good, virtuous. E. अ neg. <BR>and दुष्ट.

अदूर
अदूर Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not distant, not remote; <BR> अदूरे and अदूरात् or अदूरतः are used in the sense of ‘not <BR>far from’. With numerals this word forms Bahuvr. compounds <BR>which, according to some, are generally used in the plur. <BR>and without the samāsānta aff. कप्; f. i. अदूरत्रिंशाः = त्रिं- <BR>शतोऽदूरे, almost thirty. E. अ neg. and दूर.

अदूरभव
अदूरभव Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Being not far from. <BR>E. अदूर and भव.

अदूषित
अदूषित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Undefiled, unvitiated. <BR>	2 Virtuous, good. E. अ neg. and दूषित.

अदृपित
अदृपित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Not humiliated, <BR>not treated with arrogance or pride. E. अ neg. and दृपित.

अदृप्त
अदृप्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्) (ved.) Not arrogant, not <BR>proud, not overbearing. E. अ neg. and दृप्त.

अदृप्यत्
अदृप्यत् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्यन्-प्यन्ती-प्यत्) (ved.) Not arrogant, <BR>not haughty or overbearing. E. अ neg. and दृप्यत्.

अदृश्
अदृश् Bahvur. m. f. n. (-दृक्) Blind. E. अ priv. and दृश्.

अदृश्य
अदृश्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्) <BR>	1 Invisible, not to be <BR>seen. <BR>	2 Improper to be beheld. E. अ neg. and दृश्य.

अदृश्यकरण
अदृश्यकरण Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Making invisible. E. अदृश्य <BR>and करण.

अदृश्यत्
अदृश्यत् Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-न्-न्ती-त्) Invisible. <BR>II. f. (-न्ती) The name of the wife of Śakti, the son of <BR>Vaśiṣṭha, and mother of Parāśara. E. अ neg. and दृश्यत्.

अदृष्ट
अदृष्ट Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) <BR>	1 Unseen, unfore<BR>seen. <BR>	2 Unknown, unfelt, not experienced. <BR>	3 Invisible. <BR>II. n. (-ष्टम्) <BR>	1 Casual and unseen danger (as from con<BR>flagration, inundation &c.). <BR>	2 Fortune, destiny, fate. <BR>	3 (In <BR>philosophy.) <BR>	a. Virtue or vice (धर्म or अधर्म), as the even<BR>tual cause of pleasure or pain. <BR>	b. The remote or unforeseen <BR>consequence of an act, e. g. heaven as that of religious <BR>rites &c. See अपूर्व. <BR>III. m. (-ष्टः) A kind of poison or poisonous reptile (in <BR>the Vedas). E. अ neg. and दृष्ट.

अदृष्टज
अदृष्टज Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Produced by destiny &c. <BR>See अदृष्ट. E. अदृष्ट and ज.

अदृष्टनर
अदृष्टनर Bahuvr. m. (-रः) The same as the following q. v. <BR>E. अदृष्ट and नर.

अदृष्टपुरुष
अदृष्टपुरुष Bahuvr. m. (-षः) A form of treaty, in which the <BR>parties treat direct, without any mediator or surety. Also <BR>अदृष्टनर and similar compounds. E. अदृष्ट and पुरुष, sc. <BR>सन्धि.

अदृष्टपूर्व
अदृष्टपूर्व Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्वः-र्वा-र्वम्) Unseen previously, <BR>unseen till now. E. अदृष्ट and पूर्व.

अदृष्टवत्
अदृष्टवत् m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) <BR>	1 Enjoying or undergoing <BR>good or bad fortune, more usually the former, fortunate. <BR>E. अदृष्ट, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

अदृष्टि
अदृष्टि Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) A look of displeasure, evil eye. E. <BR>अ deter. and दृष्टि.

अदृष्टिका
अदृष्टिका f. (-का) An angry or displeased look, evil eye. E. <BR>अदृष्टि, taddh. aff. कन्.

अदेय
अदेय Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Improper or unfit to <BR>be given. II. n. (-यम्) (In law.) An object not fit to be <BR>given away, either because it does not belong to the person <BR>who would give it, or because law forbids its being dis<BR>posed of. See अदत्त, दत्त, देय. E. अ neg. and देय.

अदेयदान
अदेयदान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Giving what ought not to be <BR>given, what is not one's own &c. See the preceding. E. <BR>अदेय and दान.

अदेव
अदेव Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-वः-वी-वम्) <BR>	1 Not referring to <BR>the gods, not divine. <BR>	2 Godless, impious. <BR>II. m. (-वः) One who is not a god. E. अ neg. and देव. <BR>I. would more probably be a Bahuvr., if it were not ac<BR>centuated in the Vedas as a Tatpur. See the following.

अदेवक
अदेवक Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Having no god or <BR>divinity, referring to no god or divinity (as an offering &c.). <BR>E. अ priv. and देव, samāsānta aff. कप्.

अदेवता
अदेवता Tatpur. f. (-ता) One who is not a divinity. E. अ <BR>neg. and देवता.

अदेवत्रा
अदेवत्रा Tatpur. ind. (ved.) Not towards or amongst the gods. <BR>E. अ and देवत्रा.

अदेवयत्
अदेवयत् Tatpur. m. (-न्) (ved.) One who does not care for the <BR>gods, not devout, impious. E. अ neg. and देवयत्.

अदेवयु
अदेवयु Tatpur. m. (-युः) (ved.) The same as the preceding. <BR>E. अ neg. and देवयु.

अदेश
अदेश Tatpur. m. (-शः) <BR>	1 An improper place, a wrong place, <BR>one not congenial with one's nature &c. E. अ deter. and देश.

अदेशस्थ
अदेशस्थ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) Being not in the <BR>proper place, being in the wrong place. E. अदेश and स्थ.

अदेश्य
अदेश्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्) <BR>	1 What is not proper <BR>to be ordered. <BR>	2 Not present on the spot, not present at a <BR>transaction. E. अ neg. and देश्य.

अदोमय
अदोमय m. f. n. (-यः-यी-यम्) Made of that, consisting of <BR>that, containing that. E. अदस्, taddh. aff. मयट्.

अदोमूल
अदोमूल Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Rooted in that, <BR>founded upon that. E. अदस् and मूल.

अद्ग
अद्ग m. (-द्गः) The same as पुरोडाश q. v. E. अद्, uṇ. aff. गन्.

अद्धा
अद्धा ind. (निपात) Tatpur.(?) <BR>	1 Indeed, truly, verily. <BR>	2 Clearly. <BR>It may enter into composition with कृ (as a गति q. v.). E. <BR>अद् ind. and धा (from धा, kṛt aff. विच्); or according to <BR>others, but without probability, अद् (to eat), kṛt aff. क्विप्, <BR>and हन् (to kill), taddh. aff. डाच्.

अद्धातमाम्
अद्धातमाम् ind. (ved.) Most truly, most certainly, most to be <BR>relied upon. E. अद्धा, taddh. aff. तमप् (i. e. the superl. of <BR>अद्धा in the acc. of the femin.).

अद्धाति
अद्धाति m. (-तिः) (ved.) A wise man. E. अद्धा, taddh. aff. तिल्(?).

अद्धापुरुष
अद्धापुरुष Tatpur. m. (-षः) (ved.) A true man, one deserv<BR>ing the name of a man. E. अद्धा and पुरुष.

अद्धाबोधेय
अद्धाबोधेय Tatpur. m. pl. (-याः) The name of a Śākhā of <BR>the white Yajurveda. E. अद्धा and बोधेय(?).

अद्ध्यालोहकर्ण
अद्ध्यालोहकर्ण Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा or -र्णी-र्णम्) (ved.) Hav<BR>ing red ears (as a goat). E. अद्ध्यालोह (very red? see लोह) <BR>and कर्ण, in the fem. with aff. टाप् or ङीष्.

अद्भुत
अद्भुत Tatpur.(?) I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Surprising, wonderful (ac<BR>cording to a vaidik interpretation: not having existed before). <BR>II. m. (-तः) <BR>	1 Surprise, astonishment. See अद्भुतरस. <BR>	2 The <BR>name of the Indra or chief of the ninth Manwantara. <BR>III. n. (-तम्) <BR>	1 A prodigy, a wonder, any portentous <BR>or marvellous phenomenon. <BR>	2 (In architecture.) A kind of <BR>temple or vimāna, the breadth of which is divided into <BR>four parts, seven such parts being given to its height. E. <BR>(doubtful) अद् ind. and भू, uṇ. aff. डुतच्. Compare अन- <BR>तिद्भुत.

अद्भुतगन्ध
अद्भुतगन्ध Bahvur. m. f. n. (-न्धः-न्धा-न्धम्) Having a wonder<BR>ful smell. E. अद्भुत and गन्ध.

अद्भुतत्व
अद्भुतत्व n. (-त्वम्) Wonderfulness. E. अद्भुत, taddh. aff. त्व.

अद्भुतब्राह्मण
अद्भुतब्राह्मण Karmadh. n. (-णम्) The name of a Brāhmaṇa <BR>belonging to the Sāmaveda; more properly the last portion <BR>of the Shaḍvinśabrāhmaṇa of the same Veda. E. अद्भुत and <BR>ब्राह्मण.

अद्भुतरस
अद्भुतरस Tatpur. m. (-सः) (In rhetoric.) The marvellous, as <BR>a prevailing sentiment in poetical composition, one of the <BR>nine rasas or characteristic sentiments of poetical compo<BR>sition as described in Hindu works on rhetoric or poetry. <BR>See रस. E. अद्भुत and रस.

अद्भुतरामायण
अद्भुतरामायण Karmadh. n. (-णम्) The name of a work <BR>ascribed to Vālmīki. E. अद्भुत and रामायण.

अद्भुतरूप
अद्भुतरूप Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Having a wonderful <BR>shape or figure. E. अद्भुत and रूप.

अद्भुतसार
अद्भुतसार Karmadh. m. (-रः) The resin of the खदिर q. v. <BR>E. अद्भुत and सार.

अद्भुतस्वन
अद्भुतस्वन Bahuvr. m. (-नः) A name of Śiva. Another read<BR>ing of this word is अद्भुतश्वन. E. अद्भुत and स्वन ‘producing <BR>a wonderful sound’.

अद्मन्
अद्मन् n. (-द्म) (ved.) <BR>	1 Food in general. <BR>	2 A house. E. अद्, <BR>kṛt (or uṇ.) aff. मनिन्.

अद्मनि
अद्मनि m. (-निः) Fire. E. अद्, uṇ. aff. अनि and āgama मुट्.

अद्मर
अद्मर m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Gluttonous. E. अद्, kṛt aff. क्मरच्.

अद्मसद्
अद्मसद् Tatpur. f. (-द्) (ved.) <BR>	1 A cook. <BR>	2 A mother. E. अद्मन् <BR>and सद्; according to the comm. ‘sitting by the food, to <BR>cook it; or sitting in the house; or spending food’.

अद्मसद्य
अद्मसद्य n. (-द्यम्) (ved.) Being a cook, the condition of a <BR>cook. See the preceding. E. अद्मसद्, taddh. aff. य.

अद्य
अद्य I. ind. <BR>	1 To-day. <BR>	2 Now, at present. In the Vedas also <BR>written अद्या which seems to be the more original form of <BR>this word. अद्यापि Even now, still. अद्यपूर्वम् before to<BR>day, before now. E. अश्, considered as a substitute of <BR>इदम्, taddh. aff. द्य; but more probably a Karmadh. com<BR>pound of अ (the pronom. theme in इदम्) and द्य or द्या <BR>(from द्यु or दिव्) = अस्मिन्द्यवि. <BR>II. 1. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) Fit to be eaten, eatable. <BR>2. n. (-द्यम्) Food in general. E. अद्, kṛtya aff. यत्.

अद्यतन
अद्यतन I. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Of or belonging to the <BR>current day, of to-day. <BR>II. m. (-नः) The period of a current day, from mid<BR>night to midnight in the usual acceptation, but sometimes <BR>considered to begin and to end with sun-set or to begin <BR>with the proper time of rising and to end with the proper <BR>time of going to rest. <BR>III. f. (-नी) (In grammar.) The aorist (or लुङ्), as the <BR>tense employed in relating what has happened during the <BR>current day. E. अद्य, taddh. aff. ट्युल् and āgama तुट्.

अद्यतनीय
अद्यतनीय m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Of to-day, belonging to <BR>the current day. E. अद्यतन, taddh. aff. छ.

अद्यप्रभृति
अद्यप्रभृति Bahuvr. ind. From to-day. E. अद्य and प्रभृति.

अद्यश्वीन
अद्यश्वीन I. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) What may happen to-day <BR>or to-morrow, near to any event, at the point of death &c. <BR>II. f. (-ना) A woman or any female animal near the time <BR>of delivery. E. अद्य and श्वस्, taddh. aff. ख.

अद्यावधि
अद्यावधि Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धिः-धिः-धि) Beginning or end<BR>ing with the current day; from or till to-day. E. अद्य and <BR>अवधि.

अद्यूत्य
अद्यूत्य (ved.) Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) Not gained by <BR>playing, not gained improperly, obtained honestly. E. अ <BR>neg. and द्यूत्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. n. (-त्यम्) The last watch of the night, that <BR>preceding the dawn, at which time the Aśvins are espe<BR>cially to be worshipped. E. अ and द्यूत्य (from द्युत्, kṛt <BR>aff. ण्यत् and ऊ instead of उ) ‘without light’. Both ex<BR>planations of this word belong to different commentaries <BR>but refer to the same passage in which it occurs.

अद्रव
अद्रव Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Not liquid, solid. E. <BR>अ neg. and द्रव.

अद्रव्य
अद्रव्य Tatpur. n. (-व्यम्) A worthless or good-for-nothing <BR>object. E. अ deter. and द्रव्य.

अद्रि
अद्रि m. (-द्रिः) <BR>	1 A stone. <BR>	2 The thunderbolt. <BR>	3 A mountain. <BR>	4 A cloud. <BR>	5 A tree. <BR>	6 The sun. <BR>	7 The name of a measure. <BR>	8 A proper name of the son of Viśvagaśva and father of <BR>Yuvanāśva. <BR>	9 (In arithmetic sometimes used to denote) the <BR>numeral 7. E. अद्, uṇ. aff. क्रिन्; but more probably, a <BR>Tatpur. composed of अ and द्रि (from दॄ or द्रा?). Compare <BR>अग. The meanings 1. 2. 4. belong exclusively to the Vedas.

अद्रिकर्णी
अद्रिकर्णी Bahuvr. f. (-र्णी) The name of a plant (Clitoria <BR>ternatea). See अपराजिता or गिरिकर्णी. E. अद्रि and कर्ण, <BR>fem. aff. ङीष्.

अद्रिका
अद्रिका f. (-का) An Apsaras or heavenly nymph, the wife <BR>of Amāvasu and mother of Satyavatī. E. अद्रि, taddh. aff. <BR>कन् and fem. aff. टाप्.

अद्रिकीला
अद्रिकीला Bahuvr. f. (-ला) The earth. E. अद्रि and कील.

अद्रिकृतस्थली
अद्रिकृतस्थली Bahuvr. f. (-ली) The name of an Apsaras. E. <BR>अद्रि-कृत and स्थल, fem. aff. ङीष्.

अद्रिज
अद्रिज Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Produced or found <BR>in the hills. <BR>II. f. (-जा) <BR>	1 A name of Pārvatī or Durgā, the daughter <BR>of Himālaya, the ruler of the Himālaya mountain, and <BR>hence this her appellation, mountain-born. <BR>	2 The name of <BR>a plant. See सैंहली. <BR>III. n. (-जम्) Red chalk. See शिलाजतु. E. अद्रि and ज.

अद्रिजा
अद्रिजा Tatpur. m. (-जाः) (ved.) Produced by the (friction <BR>of) stones (an epithet of Agni and हंस q. v.). E. अद्रि <BR>and जा.

अद्रिजूत
अद्रिजूत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Moved or hastened <BR>by the stones (the sound of the stones); an epithet of the <BR>chariot of the Aśvins. E. अद्रि and जूत.

अद्रितनया
अद्रितनया Tatpur. f. (-या) <BR>	1 A name of Pārvatī, the daughter <BR>of the mountain Himālaya. <BR>	2 A metre regulated by number <BR>and quantity; a variety of the class called विकृति q. v. It con<BR>sists of four lines, with the following twenty-three syllables <BR>to each: ˘˘˘˘¯˘¯˘˘˘¯ । ˘¯˘˘˘¯˘¯˘˘˘¯. <BR>Also called अश्वललित. E. अद्रि and तनया.

अद्रिदुग्ध
अद्रिदुग्ध Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्धः-ग्धा-ग्धम्) (ved.) Extracted <BR>or expressed with stones. E. अद्रि and दुग्ध; literally: <BR>milked with stones.

अद्रिद्विष्
अद्रिद्विष् Tatpur. m. (-ट्) A name of Indra. E. अद्रि and <BR>द्विष्, lit. the enemy of the mountains.

अद्रिनन्दिनी
अद्रिनन्दिनी Tatpur. f. (-नी) Pārvatī. See अद्रितनया. E. <BR>अद्रि and नन्दिनी.

अद्रिपति
अद्रिपति Tatpur. m. (-तिः) Hima, lord of mountains: also <BR>similar compounds, as अद्रिराज्, अद्रीन्द्र &c.

अद्रिबुध्न
अद्रिबुध्न Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ध्नः-ध्ना-ध्नम्) (ved.) Produced or <BR>originating in mountains. E. अद्रि and बुध्न.

अद्रिभिद्
अद्रिभिद् Tatpur. m. (-भित्) A name of Indra. E. अद्रि and <BR>भिद्, lit. the splitter of mountains (with his thunderbolt).

अद्रिभू
अद्रिभू Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-भूः-भूः-भु) Mountaineer, moun<BR>tain-born. <BR>II. f. (-भूः) A plant (Salvinea cucullata). See आखुकर्णी. <BR>E. अद्रि and भू.

अद्रिमूर्धन्
अद्रिमूर्धन् Tatpur. m. (-र्धा) The summit or peak of a moun<BR>tain. E. अद्रि and मूर्धन्.

अद्रिराज्
अद्रिराज् Tatpur. m. (-राट्) The king of mountains, the <BR>Himālaya mountains; the snowy range on the north of <BR>Hindustan, confounded with the mythological ruler of them, <BR>and the father of Pārvatī. E. अद्रि and राज्.

अद्रिराज
अद्रिराज Tatpur. m. (-जः). The same as the preceding. E. <BR>अद्रि and राजन्, samāsānta aff. टच्.

अद्रिवत्
अद्रिवत् m. (-वान्, voc. in the Vedas -वः) (ved.) Having <BR>stones, armed with stones or with the thunderbolt, an epithet <BR>of Indra, Soma, Varuṇa. E. अद्रि, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

अद्रिवह्नि
अद्रिवह्नि Tatpur. m. (-ह्निः) Fire on or in a mountain. E. <BR>अद्रि and वह्नि.

अद्रिशय्य
अद्रिशय्य Bahuvr. m. (-य्यः) A name of Śiva. E. अद्रि and <BR>शय्या; literally: whose couch is the mountain (Himālaya).

अद्रिशृङ्ग
अद्रिशृङ्ग Tatpur. n. (-ङ्गम्) A peak, the horn or summit of <BR>a mountain. E. अद्रि and शृङ्ग.

अद्रिसंहत
अद्रिसंहत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Struck or ex<BR>tracted with stones, pressed with stones (an epithet of Soma). <BR>E. अद्रि and संहत.

अद्रिसार
अद्रिसार Tatpur. m. (-रः) Iron. E. अद्रि and सार.

अद्रिसारमय
अद्रिसारमय m. f. n. (-यः-यी-यम्) Made of iron. E. अद्रि- <BR>सार, taddh. aff. मयट्.

अद्रीन्द्र
अद्रीन्द्र Tatpur. m. (-न्द्रः). The same as the following. E. <BR>अद्रि and इन्द्र.

अद्रीश
अद्रीश Tatpur. m. (-शः) <BR>	1 A name of Śiva. <BR>	2 A name of <BR>Himālaya, as king of mountains. E. अद्रि and ईश.

अद्रुह्
अद्रुह् Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ध्रुक्) (ved.) Harmless, innocuous, <BR>void of guile, kind, mild (an epithet of the gods, of heaven <BR>and earth &c.) E. अ priv. and द्रुह्.

अद्रुह्वन्
अद्रुह्वन् Tatpur. m. (-ह्वा) (ved.) The same as the preceding <BR>(an epithet of Mitra and Varuṇa). E. अ neg. and द्रुह्वन्.

अद्रोघ
अद्रोघ Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-घः-घा-घम्) (ved.) Having no guile, <BR>free from deceit, true. E. अ priv. and द्रोघ.

अद्रोह
अद्रोह Tatpur. m. (-हः) Mildness, moderation, the absence <BR>of tyranny or oppression. E. अ neg. and द्रोह.

अद्रोहिन्
अद्रोहिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ही-हिणी-हि) Innocuous, mild. <BR>E. अ neg. and द्रोहिन्.

अद्वय
अद्वय I. Tatpur. n. (-यम्) <BR>	1 Not duality, unity. <BR>	2 The <BR>identity of Brahman (n.) and the Universe or of the divine <BR>essence and the human soul; the real truth. E. अ neg. <BR>and द्वय. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Without a second, <BR>only, alone; esp. in the neuter as an epithet of Brahman (n.) <BR>which is not distinct from the Universe. <BR>2. m. (-यः) A name of Buddha (acc. to a commentary, <BR>because wisdom and object of wisdom are identical with <BR>him). E. अ priv. and द्वय.

अद्वयत्
अद्वयत् Tatpur. m. (-यन्) (ved.) Free from duplicity, one <BR>whose acts are not different from his words and thoughts, <BR>upright, honest. E. अ neg. and द्वयत्.

अद्वयवादिन्
अद्वयवादिन् Tatpur. m. (-दी) A Jina or Buddha. E. अद्वय <BR>and वादिन्: one who acknowledges but one principle; <BR>or who teaches the real truth. See अद्वैतवादिन्.

अद्वयस्
अद्वयस् Tatpur. m. (-याः) (ved.) The same as अद्वयत्. E. <BR>अ neg. and द्वयस्.

अद्वयानन्द
अद्वयानन्द Bahuvr. m. (-न्दः) The same as अद्वैतानन्द. E. <BR>अद्वय and आनन्द.

अद्वयाविन्
अद्वयाविन् Tatpur. m. (-वी) (ved.) The same as अद्वयत्. <BR>E. अ neg. and द्वयाविन्.

अद्वयु
अद्वयु Tatpur. m. (-युः) (ved.) The same as अद्वयत्. E. अ <BR>neg. and द्वयु.

अद्वार
अद्वार Tatpur. n. (-रम्) An entrance to a house which is <BR>other than the door. E. अ neg. and द्वार.

अद्वितीय
अद्वितीय Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) <BR>	1 Only, sole, with<BR>out a second. See अद्वय. <BR>	2 Unparalleled, unequalled. E. अ <BR>priv. and द्वितीय.

अद्विषेण्य
अद्विषेण्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ण्यः-ण्या-ण्यम्) (ved.) Not detestable <BR>or hateful, agreeable, desired. E. अ neg. and द्विषेण्य.

अद्वेष
अद्वेष Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्) Harmless, not malicious, <BR>kind. E. अ priv. and द्वेष.

अद्वेषिन्
अद्वेषिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-षी-षिणी-षि) Harmless, inoffen<BR>sive. E. अ neg. and द्वेषिन्.

अद्वैत
अद्वैत I. Tatpur. n. (-तम्) <BR>	1 Unity, not duality. <BR>	2 The iden<BR>tity of Brahman (n.) and the Universe or of the divine es<BR>sence and the human soul; the real truth. <BR>	3 The name of <BR>an Upanishad of the Atharvaveda. E. अ neg. and द्वैत. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Without a second, <BR>only, alone; esp. as an epithet of आत्मन् and ब्रह्मन् (n.) <BR>or ब्रह्मलोक. E. अ priv. and द्वैत.

अद्वैतवादिन्
अद्वैतवादिन् Tatpur. m. (-दी) A unitarian, one who main<BR>tains the existence of but one principle in the Universe. <BR>E. अद्वैत and वादिन्. See अद्वयवादिन्.

अद्वैतानन्द
अद्वैतानन्द Bahuvr. m. (-न्दः) The proper name of one of the <BR>founders of the Vaiṣṇava sect in Bengal; he lived about <BR>the end of the 15th century. Also अद्वयानन्द. E. अद्वैत and <BR>आनन्द.

अध
अध ind. (निपात) An inceptive particle which occurs only <BR>in the Vedas. It is used very much in the same manner as <BR>अथ of which it is apparently a variety and corresponds <BR>chiefly with <BR>	1 Now, hereafter. <BR>	2 Moreover, so much the <BR>more. <BR>	3 Therefore. It occurs frequently in its protracted <BR>form अधा which seems to be the more original one. E. <BR>See अथ.

अधःकर
अधःकर Tatpur. m. (-रः) The lower part of the hand, the <BR>metacarpus or the hand from the wrist to the root of the <BR>fingers. E. अधस् and कर.

अधःकाय
अधःकाय Tatpur. m. (-यः) The lower part of the body, the <BR>lower extremities. E. अधस् and काय.

अधःखनन
अधःखनन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Undermining. E. अधस् and खनन.

अधःपद्म
अधःपद्म Tatpur. n. (-द्मम्) (In architecture.) A division of the <BR>शिखर (q. v.) or cupola, the lower cima recta. E. अधस् and पद्म.

अधःपात
अधःपात Tatpur. m. (-तः) Falling down, literally and me<BR>taphorically. E. अधस् and पात.

अधःपुष्पी
अधःपुष्पी Bahuvr. f. (-ष्पी) <BR>	1 A plant (Pimpinella anisum). <BR>See अवाक्पुष्पी. <BR>	2 Another plant (Elephantopus scaber) <BR>or perhaps Hieracium. See गोजिह्वा. E. अधस् and पुष्प, <BR>fem. aff. ङीष्, lit. having its flowers hanging downwards.

अधःप्रवाह
अधःप्रवाह Tatpur. m. (-हः) Flowing or streaming down<BR>wards. E. अधस् and प्रवाह.

अधःप्रस्तर
अधःप्रस्तर Tatpur. m. (-रः) A seat or bed, made of grass, <BR>esp. for the use of persons in the state of impurity or आ- <BR>शौच q. v. E. अधस् and प्रस्तर.

अधःशय
अधःशय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Sleeping on the <BR>ground. E. अधस् and शय.

अधःशय्य
अधःशय्य I. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-य्यः-य्या-य्यम्) Sleeping on the <BR>ground, on a kind of couch different from a bed-stead. <BR>II. Tatpur. f. (-य्या) The sleeping in the manner described. <BR>E. अधस् and शय्या.

अधःशिरस्
अधःशिरस् Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-राः-राः-रः) and II. n. (-रः) <BR>The same as अधोमुख I. and IV. q. v. E. अधस् and शिरस्.

अधःस्थ
अधःस्थ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) <BR>	1 Below. <BR>	2 Inferior. <BR>E. अधस् and स्थ.

अधःस्थित
अधःस्थित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Standing beneath. <BR>E. अधस् and स्थित.

अधःस्वस्तिक
अधःस्वस्तिक Tatpur. n. (-कम्) (In astronomy.) The nadir. <BR>Also अधरस्वस्तिक. E. अधस् and स्वस्तिक.

अधउपासन
अधउपासन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Copulation, sexual union. E. <BR>अधस् and उपासन.

अधन
अधन Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Poor, without wealth. <BR>E. अ priv. and धन.

अधम
अधम I. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) <BR>	1 Very low or inferior in <BR>place or degree. <BR>	2 Vile, despicable. (In the vituperative <BR>sense it stands often as the latter part of a Tatpur. com<BR>pound; f. i. पापाधम, नराधम.) <BR>II. m. (-मः) (In rhetoric, according to some.) A para<BR>mour of a low description, one without fear, pity or shame &c. <BR>III. f. (-मा) (In rhetoric, according to some.) A mistress <BR>of a low description, one ungrateful, whimsical, acting <BR>unkindly towards her lover &c. E. अव्, uṇ. aff. अम, with <BR>व् changed to ध; or according to others a Tatpur. com<BR>posed of अ neg. and धम (from ध्मा); but a preferable <BR>etym. is that from अधस्, taddh. aff. म, with elision of <BR>स्; or better from अध् (the thematic form common to अधम, <BR>अधर, अधस्, अधस्तात्), aff. अम.

अधमभृत
अधमभृत Karmadh. m. (-तः). See the following. E. अधम and भृत.

अधमभृतक
अधमभृतक Karmadh. m. (-कः) The lowest order of hired <BR>servants, a porter, a bearer of burdens. (See also भृतक, <BR>उत्तमभृतक and मध्यमभृतक.) E. अधम and भृतक.

अधमर्ण
अधमर्ण Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा-र्णम्) A debtor. E. अधम and ऋण.

अधमर्णिक
अधमर्णिक m. (-कः) A debtor. E. अधमर्ण, taddh. aff. ठक्.

अधमाङ्ग
अधमाङ्ग Karmadh. n. (-ङ्गम्) A foot. E. अधम and अङ्ग.

अधमाचार
अधमाचार Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Wicked in prac<BR>tice, low, vile. E. अधम and आचार.

अधमार्ध
अधमार्ध Karmadh. n. (-र्धम्) The inferior or lower part. Cf. <BR>उत्तमार्ध E. अधम and अर्ध.

अधमार्ध्य
अधमार्ध्य m. f. n. (-र्ध्यः-र्ध्या-र्ध्यम्) Belonging to the inferior <BR>or lower part. Cf. उत्तमार्ध्य. E. अधमार्ध, taddh. aff. यत्.

अधर
अधर I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) <BR>	1 Lower, inferior, in place. <BR>(In this sense the word is declined like the sarvanāman यत् <BR>&c. (q. v.), but in the abl. and loc. sing. of the masc. and <BR>neuter and in the nom. plur. of the masc. it forms optionally <BR>अधरस्मात् or अधरात्, अधरस्मिन् or अधरे, अधरे or अ- <BR>धराः; it may form Tatpur. compositions with nouns having <BR>the sense of the singular and considered then as depending <BR>upon अधर, which is the former part of the compound, in <BR>the genitive; for instance अधरकायः is explained, अधरं <BR>कायस्य.) Adverbially used are अधरात्, अधरस्मात्, अधरेण; <BR>qq. vv. <BR>	2 Low, vile. <BR>	3 Speechless, refuted, overcome in abuse <BR>or controversy. <BR>	4 Prior, preceding in time. See अधरेद्युस्. <BR>II. m. (-रः) The lower lip, the lip. <BR>III. f. (-रा) <BR>	1 The lower region. <BR>	2 The nadir (?). <BR>IV. m. n. (-रः-रम्) Pudendum muliebre. E. Probably <BR>from अध् (see E. of अधम), aff. अर; the derivation given <BR>by the native authorities, from अ neg. and धर is not correct.

अधरकण्ठ
अधरकण्ठ Tatpur. m. n. (-ण्ठः-ण्ठम्?) The lower part of the <BR>throat. E. अधर and कण्ठ. See under अधर.

अधरकाय
अधरकाय Tatpur. m. (-यः) The lower part of the body, <BR>the lower extremities. E. अधर and काय. See under <BR>अधर.

अधरतस्
अधरतस् ind. <BR>	1 Underneath. <BR>	2 The lower regions, the nadir, or <BR>in the lower regions, in the nadir. (Used in the sense of a no<BR>minative or locative, but in the latter with the restriction <BR>that the distance must not be far; or governing in the first <BR>meaning a noun in the genitive.) See अधरात् and अधरेण. <BR>Cf. अधराक्. E. अधर, taddh. aff. अतसुच्.

अधरपान
अधरपान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Kissing. E. अधर II. and पान.

अधरस्तात्
अधरस्तात् ind. Below, underneath. (The correctness of this <BR>form appears doubtful.) E. अधर, taddh. aff. अस्ताति.

अधरस्वस्तिक
अधरस्वस्तिक Tatpur. n. (-कम्) (In astronomy.) The nadir. <BR>Also अधःस्वस्तिक q. v. E. अधर and स्वस्तिक.

अधराक्
अधराक् Tatpur. ind. <BR>	1 Downwards, from below. <BR>	2 Westwards, <BR>from or in the west. <BR>	3 The lower regions or the nadir, from <BR>or in the lower regions or the nadir. (Used in the sense of a <BR>locative, ablative or nominative; or governing in the two first <BR>meanings a noun in the ablative. E. अधर and अञ्च् II. with <BR>luk of the taddh. aff. अस्ताति. See अधराञ्च्

अधराचीन
अधराचीन m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) (ved.) Going or being un<BR>derneath, westwards, going to or being in the lower regions, <BR>in the nadir. E. अधराञ्च्, taddh. aff. ख.

अधराच्य
अधराच्य m. f. n. (-च्यः-च्या-च्यम्) (ved.) The same as the <BR>preceding. E. अधराञ्च्, taddh. aff. यत्.

अधराञ्च्
अधराञ्च् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-राङ्-राची-राक्) (ved.) Going or <BR>being downwards, westwards, going to or being in the lower <BR>regions, in the nadir. E. अधर and अञ्च्.

अधरात्
अधरात् ind. The same as अधरतस्. (Used in the sense of a <BR>locative, ablative or nominative.) E. अधर, taddh. aff. आति.

अधरारणि
अधरारणि Tatpur. f. (-णिः) (ved.) The nether piece of the two <BR>pieces of wood, which, by attrition, produce the sacrificial fire. <BR>See अरणि and उत्तरारणि. E. अधर (q. v.) and अरणि.

अधरावलोप
अधरावलोप Tatpur. m. (-पः) Biting the lip. E. अधर II. and <BR>अवलोप.

अधरीकृत
अधरीकृत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Put down, overcome, <BR>vanquished. <BR>	2 Annulled, invalidated (as a document). E. <BR>अधर, taddh. aff. च्वि with कृ, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधरीण
अधरीण m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Reproached, censured. E. <BR>अधर, taddh. aff. ख.

अधरीभूत
अधरीभूत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Refuted, contra<BR>dicted, invalidated. E. अधर, taddh. aff. च्वि with भू, kṛt <BR>aff. क्त.

अधरेण
अधरेण ind. The same as अधरतस् or अधरात्. (Used in <BR>the sense of a locative or nominative, but in the first <BR>with the restriction that the distance must not be far; or <BR>governing in the first meaning a noun in the accusative or <BR>genitive.) E. अधर, taddh. aff. एनप्.

अधरेद्युस्
अधरेद्युस् ind. A previous day, the day before yesterday. E. <BR>अधर, irregular aff. एद्युस्; better a Tatpur, compound, <BR>from अधर (loc.) and द्युस् from दिव् or द्यु.

अधरोत्तर
अधरोत्तर Dwandwa I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) <BR>	1 Lower and <BR>higher. <BR>	2 Inferior and better. <BR>	3 Prior and posterior. <BR>II. n. sing. or plur. (-रम् or -रे) <BR>	1 The lower and higher, <BR>inferior and better, prior and posterior. <BR>	2 A state of con<BR>fusion, when things are tupsy-turvy. <BR>	3 Address and answer. <BR>E. अधर and उत्तर.

अधरोष्ठ
अधरोष्ठ Karmadh. m. (-ष्ठः) The lower lip. Also अधरौष्ठ. <BR>E. अधर and ओष्ठ.

अधर्म
अधर्म Tatpur. 1. m. (-र्मः) <BR>	1 Unrighteousness, injustice, all <BR>behaviour contrary to the Śruti and Smṛti, or religious <BR>and legal institutions. <BR>	2 (In philosophy.) According to the <BR>Nyāya and Vaiśeṣika: moral demerit, the result of doing <BR>what is forbidden, the peculiar cause of pain, one of the <BR>twenty-four qualities united with substance.--According <BR>to the Sāṅkhya, one of the changeable (वैकृतिक) dispo<BR>sitions (भाव) of the mind, which being the efficient cause, <BR>makes the soul migrate into an animal, a deer, a bird, a <BR>reptile, a vegetable, a mineral.--According to the Bud<BR>dhistic doctrine it is the consequence of upādāna or exertion <BR>of body or speech.--According to the Jainas it is that <BR>which causes the soul in general to continue embarrassed <BR>with body notwithstanding its capacity for ascent and na<BR>tural tendency to soar. <BR>	3 As a personification Adharma oc<BR>curs in the Purāṇas as one of the Prajāpatis or mind-born <BR>sons of Brahmā; his wife is Hinsā (mischief) on whom he <BR>begot Anṛta (falsehood) and Nikṛti (immorality) or ac<BR>cording to others, Mṛṣā (falsehood) and his children Dam<BR>bha (hypocrisy) and Māyā (deceit) who were adopted by <BR>Nirṛti (misfortune).--Adharma is also mentioned as one <BR>of the eighteen servants of the sun. <BR>2. f. (-र्मा) According to the Śāktas a kalā or part of <BR>the original or Mūla-prakṛti and personified as the bride <BR>of Mṛtyu or Death. E. अ neg. and धर्म.

अधर्मचारिन्
अधर्मचारिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Unrighteous, <BR>wicked. E. अधर्म and चारिन्.

अधर्मदण्डन
अधर्मदण्डन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Inflicting punishment without <BR>any lawful motive, unjust punishment. E. अधर्म and दण्डन.

अधर्ममय
अधर्ममय m. f. n. (-यः-यी-यम्) Consisting of injustice or <BR>unrighteousness, thoroughly unjust or unrighteous. E. अ- <BR>धर्म, taddh. aff. मयट्.

अधर्मात्मन्
अधर्मात्मन् Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्मा-त्मा-त्म) Wicked, unrighteous. <BR>E. अधर्म and आत्मन्.

अधर्मास्तिकाय
अधर्मास्तिकाय Tatpur. m. (-यः) The category or predicament <BR>of अधर्म, according to the Jainas (see अधर्म, 2.). E. अधर्म <BR>and अस्तिकाय.

अधर्मिन्
अधर्मिन् m. f. n. (-र्मी-र्मिणी-र्मि) Wicked, sinful, unrighteous. <BR>E. अधर्म, taddh. aff. इनि.

अधर्मिष्ठ
अधर्मिष्ठ m. f. n. (-ष्ठः-ष्ठा-ष्ठम्) Very wicked. E. अधर्मिन्, <BR>taddh. aff. इष्ठन्.

अधर्म्य
अधर्म्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्म्यः-र्म्या-र्म्यम्) Not conformable or <BR>according to justice or morality, wicked, unrighteous. E. <BR>अ neg. and धर्म्य.

अधवा
अधवा Bahuvr. f. (-वा) A widow. See विधवा. E. अ priv. and धव.

अधश्चर
अधश्चर Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Going down or below. <BR>II. m. (-रः) A thief. E. अधस् and चर. See the following.

अधश्चौर
अधश्चौर Tatpur. m. (-रः) A house-breaker, a thief. E. <BR>अधस् and चौर.

अधस्
अधस् ind. <BR>	1 Underneath, downwards or from below. <BR>	2 The lower <BR>regions, the nadir, or: from or in the lower regions, the nadir. <BR>(In these meanings it is used in the sense of a nominative, <BR>ablative or locative; or governs in the first meaning a noun in <BR>the genitive, more seldom in the ablative; the reiterated अधो <BR>ऽधस् implies proximity and is followed by the noun in the <BR>accusative, f. i. अधोऽधो ग्रामम् below the village, but in its <BR>neighbourhood; it may occur as the former and as the latter <BR>part of Tatpur. compounds.) <BR>	3 Pudendum muliebre. <BR>	4 Away, <BR>out(?). See अधस्तात्; cf. अधराक्. E. अध् (considered as a <BR>substitute of अधर, but more probably the thematic form <BR>common to अधम, अधर, अधस् and अधस्तात्), taddh. aff. असि.

अधस्तन
अधस्तन m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Below, underneath. E. अधस्, <BR>taddh. aff. ट्युल् and āgama तुट्.

अधस्तराम्
अधस्तराम् ind. Lower, very low. E. अधस्, taddh. aff. तरप् <BR>and आमु (or better the acc. fem. in the comparative of <BR>अधस् used as an adverb).

अधस्तात्
अधस्तात् ind. The same as अधस् in the three first meanings. <BR>It is used, like this word, in its two first meanings in the <BR>sense of a nominative, ablative and locative and may in its <BR>first meaning govern a noun in the genitive, more seldom in <BR>the ablative. See अधस्. E. अध् (considered as a substitute <BR>of अधर, but more probably the thematic form common to <BR>अधम, अधर, अधस् and अधस्तात्), taddh. aff. अस्ताति.

अधस्ताद्दिश्
अधस्ताद्दिश् Tatpur. f. (-क्) The lower region, the nadir. E. <BR>अधस्तात् and दिश्.

अधस्पद
अधस्पद Tatpur. n. (-दम्) The place under the feet. E. अ- <BR>धस् and पद.

अधा
अधा ind. See अध.

अधामार्गव
अधामार्गव m. (-वः) A plant (Achyranthes aspera). Also <BR>धामार्गव; and see अपामार्ग. E. unknown.

अधारणक
अधारणक Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Not supporting, <BR>not giving or not allowing to gain a livelihood, unpro<BR>fitable. E. अ priv. and धारण, samāsānta aff. कप्.

अधार्मिक
अधार्मिक Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Unjust, unrighteous, <BR>wicked. See also आधार्मिक. E. अ neg. and धार्मिक.

अधि
अधि ind. (see निपात, उपसर्ग, गति, कर्मप्रवचनीय) A par<BR>ticle implying superiority in place, power, rank, quality <BR>and quantity and generally used as a separable prepo<BR>sition or as a prefix to verbs, but in the Vedas also as <BR>an adverb. With nouns it may form Tatpur., Bahuvr. <BR>and Avyayībhāva compounds. It means. <BR>1. (as adverb, in the Vedas) very much, excessively. <BR>2. (as a separable preposition) <BR>	1 with a noun following <BR>or preceding in the locative, <BR>	a. above (in place), <BR>	b. over (in <BR>the sense of mastership, power &c.), <BR>	c. under (see अधीन <BR>and अधिक 4, cf. अधस्); <BR>	2 with a noun following or pre<BR>ceding in the accusative, <BR>	a. on, above (in place), <BR>	b. concerning, <BR>with respect to, <BR>	c. repeated it implies also proximity; f. i. <BR>अध्यधि ग्रामम् above the village but in its neighbourhood; <BR>	3 with a noun following or preceding in the ablative (in the <BR>Vedas), <BR>	a. on, above, <BR>	b. from above, <BR>	c. from (in this meaning <BR>it occurs also in the classical language, when it is supposed <BR>to be merely an expletive, the preceding ablative implying <BR>already the notion ‘from’), <BR>	d. in consequence of, on behalf of, <BR>	e. in presence of, before, in front of; <BR>	4 with a noun following <BR>or preceding in the genitive (in the Vedas), amidst, amongst. <BR>3. (as a prefix to verbs) Over, esp. in the sense of <BR>taking possession of, mastering &c. literally or metapho<BR>rically; but used also as an expletive esp. when followed by <BR>another preposition: f. i. with कृ to superintend, with इ to <BR>obtain, to study &c.; but it does not alter the meaning of <BR>आगम्, when forming with the latter अध्यागम्. <BR>4. (in composition) <BR>	1 (with Tatpur. or Bahuvr.) it implies <BR>superiority in place, rank, quantity &c., <BR>	2 (with Avyayībh.) <BR>	a. concerning, with respect to, <BR>	b. over. E. unknown.

अधि
अधि 1. m. (-धिः) Anxiety, mental pain; more usually आधि <BR>q. v. of which it seems to be an incorrect reading. E. see आधि. <BR>2. f. (-धिः) A woman in her courses. See also अवि. <BR>E. अद्, kṛt aff. इ and ध् substituted for द् or a Tatpur. <BR>अ neg. and धि (from धा). (The first etym. doubtful.)

अधिक
अधिक I. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) <BR>	1 Exceeding, in addition to <BR>(the reverse of न्यून; between both साधारण). <BR>	2 More, more <BR>than, superior (in place, power, rank, quality or quantity). <BR>	3 Very much, excessive, excellent. <BR>	4 Less, smaller, inferior (cf. <BR>अधि 2. 1. c.). अधिकम् used as adverb. (If अधिक has the first of <BR>these meanings, that by which the excess is caused, stands in <BR>the instrumental or (but seldom) in the locative or forms the <BR>first part of a Tatpur. compound of which अधिक is the latter; <BR>if it has the second meaning, the object compared with, stands <BR>in the instrumental, the ablative or in the genitive; if it has <BR>the last meaning, the object compared with stands in the abla<BR>tive. Cf. अध्यारूढ. With numerals अधिक may form Bahuvr. <BR>compounds, usually in the plural, if it is the former part of <BR>the compound; for instance अधिकचत्वारिंशाः (sc. संख्याः) i. e. <BR>more than forty. It is considered as dropped in Dwandwa <BR>compounds of numerals f. i. in पञ्चविंशति, equal to पञ्चाधि- <BR>कविंशति.) <BR>	5 Embolismic, intercalary (only in composition <BR>with and prefixed to the name or numeral of a luni-solar <BR>year, to the name of a month and to the name of a day; <BR>f. i. अधिकाश्विन. See also अधिकतिथि, अधिकदिन, अधि- <BR>कमास, अधिकसंवत्सर, and compare क्षय). <BR>	5 Subsequent, <BR>following (as a day, a chapter or a passage in a book &c.; <BR>used very much in the same manner as ऊर्ध्व). <BR>II. n. (-कम्) <BR>	1 The surplus, that which is exceeding. <BR>	2 (In Nyāya.) Superfluity in reasons or instances, giving <BR>more reasons or instances than are required or relevant in <BR>a syllogism. <BR>	3 (In rhetoric.) Hyperbole (of which two <BR>kinds are enumerated: hyperbole concerning the recipient <BR>(substance, subject &c.) and hyperbole concerning that <BR>which is to be received (accidents, predicate &c.). E. अधि, <BR>taddh. aff. कन्.

अधिकता
अधिकता f. (-ता) Excess, addition; also अधिकत्व n. (-त्वम्). <BR>E. अधिक, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

अधिकक्षयकारिन्
अधिकक्षयकारिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Causing <BR>excessive loss, wasting too much. E. अधिक-क्षय and कारिन्.

अधिकतिथि
अधिकतिथि Karmadh. m. f. (-थिः-थिः) An intercalary lunar <BR>day. When no tithi (q. v.) begins or ends in a solar day, <BR>the numeral of the preceding is repeated in the calendar, <BR>the first tithi being accounted the intercalated and the second <BR>the proper one. Compare क्षयतिथि. E. अधिक and तिथि.

अधिकदन्त
अधिकदन्त Karmadh. m. (-न्तः) A tooth growing over an<BR>other. See अधिदन्त and वर्धन. E. अधिक and दन्त.

अधिकदिन
अधिकदिन Karmadh. n. (-नम्) An intercalated day. See <BR>अधिकतिथि. Also अधिदिन. E. अधिक and दिन.

अधिकमांसार्मन्
अधिकमांसार्मन् Tatpur. n. (-र्म). See अधिमांसार्मन्. E. अ- <BR>धिक-मांस and अर्मन्.

अधिकमास
अधिकमास Karmadh. m. (-सः) An intercalated month. Also <BR>अधिमास. Compare क्षयमास. E. अधिक and मास.

अधिकरण
अधिकरण I. Tatpur. n. (-णम्) <BR>	1 Superiority, supremacy, govern<BR>ment. <BR>	2 Title, right. <BR>	3 Town meeting, court of justice. <BR>	4 Sup<BR>port, receptacle. <BR>	5 Substance (द्रव्य, as the recipient of quali<BR>ties &c.). <BR>	6 (In grammar.) Comprehension, location, gener<BR>ally the sense of the seventh or locative case, but occa<BR>sionally also that of the third or instrumental and of the <BR>sixth or genitive case. <BR>	7 (In grammar.) Government, re<BR>gimen; see एकाधिकरण, युगपदधिकरण, समानाधिकरण. <BR>	8 (In philosophy.) A case or topic; esp. in the Mīmānsā <BR>and Vedānta; in the former it comprehends usually five <BR>parts or members, the subject (विषय), the doubt (संशय), <BR>the first side (or objectionable) argument (पूर्वपक्ष), the fol<BR>lowing (or right) argument (उत्तरपक्ष) and the conclusion <BR>(सिद्धान्त or राद्धान्त). Sometimes, however, the second <BR>part is inherent in the third and the fifth in the fourth. <BR>In both philosophies an adhikaraṇa is a subdivision of a <BR>pāda, which is the division of an adhyāya. E. कृ with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. ल्युट्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. (-णः-णी). See अधिकार II. E. अधि and <BR>करण; in the fem. with aff. ङीप्.

अधिकरणमण्डप
अधिकरणमण्डप Tatpur. m. n. (-पः-पम्) A hall of the town <BR>council, a hall of justice(?). E. अधिकरण and मण्डप.

अधिकरणसिद्धान्त
अधिकरणसिद्धान्त Tatpur. m. (-न्तः) (In the Nyāya philoso<BR>phy.) A truth or conclusion which implies another truth or <BR>conclusion; one of the four kinds of सिद्धान्त. See also सर्व- <BR>तन्त्रसिद्धान्त, प्रतितन्त्रसिद्धान्त and अभ्युपगमसिद्धान्त. E. अ- <BR>धिकरण and सिद्धान्त, a paramount truth.

अधिकरणिक
अधिकरणिक. See आधिकरणिक.

अधिकरणैतावत्त्व
अधिकरणैतावत्त्व Tatpur. n. (-त्त्वम्) Quantity. E. अधिकरण <BR>(substance) and एतावत्त्व ‘the fixed measure of a substance’.

अधिकर्द्धि
अधिकर्द्धि Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्द्धिः-र्द्धिः-र्द्धि) Prosperous, every <BR>way happy. E. अधिक and ऋद्धि.

अधिकर्मकर
अधिकर्मकर Tatpur. m. (-रः) The same as the following. <BR>E. अधि and कर्मकर.

अधिकर्मकृत्
अधिकर्मकृत् Tatpur. m. (-त्) A servant who is set over or <BR>superintends the working men; one of the four kinds of <BR>servants called कर्मकार or कर्मकर qq. vv. See also शुश्रूषक. <BR>E. अधि and कर्मकृत्.

अधिकर्मकृत
अधिकर्मकृत Tatpur. m. (-तः) The master or chief of a fa<BR>mily, one who superintends all family affairs. E. अधि- <BR>कर्मन् and कृत.

अधिकर्मन्
अधिकर्मन् Tatpur. n. (-र्म) Superintendence, supervision. <BR>E. कृ with अधि, kṛt aff. मनिन्.

अधिकर्मिक
अधिकर्मिक m. (-कः) Clerk or prefect of the market or fair. <BR>E. अधिकर्मन्, taddh. aff. ठन्.

अधिकल्पिन्
अधिकल्पिन् Tatpur. m. (-ल्पी) (ved.) An exceedingly shrewd <BR>gambler, one skilled in superior tricks or combinations(?). <BR>E. अधि and कल्पिन्.

अधिकवाक्योक्ति
अधिकवाक्योक्ति Tatpur. f. (-क्तिः) Exaggeration, hyperbole. <BR>E. अधिक-वाक्य and उक्ति.

अधिकषाष्टिक
अधिकषाष्टिक m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Bought with, made of &c. <BR>more than sixty. E. अधिक-षष्टि, taddh. aff. ठञ्.

अधिकसंवत्सर
अधिकसंवत्सर Karmadh. m. (-रः) An intercalated year. E. <BR>अधिक and संवत्सर.

अधिकसाप्ततिक
अधिकसाप्ततिक m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Bought with, made of &c. <BR>more than seventy. E. अधिक-सप्तति, taddh. aff. ठञ्.

अधिकाङ्ग
अधिकाङ्ग Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-ङ्गः-ङ्गी or -ङ्गा-ङ्गम्) Having <BR>more members than natural or common. <BR>II. n. (-ङ्गम्) The girdle over the coat of mail, worn <BR>as a kind of scarf. E. अधिक and अङ्ग; in the fem. with <BR>aff. ङीष् or टाप्.

अधिकार
अधिकार I. Tatp. m. (-रः) <BR>	1 Superintendence, supremacy, autho<BR>rity. <BR>	2 Rule, government. <BR>	3 Duty, office. <BR>	4 Right, title, owner<BR>ship. <BR>	5 The use of royal insignia. <BR>	6 (In the Mīmānsā philo<BR>sophy.) The right of action, i. e. the right to institute a <BR>sacrifice and to claim the results which are derived from <BR>it; it is subject to different regulations and restrictions and <BR>forms the subject of the sixth adhyāya of the Mīmānsā. <BR>See also कर्माधिकार. <BR>	7 A topic in a book; especially <BR>in grammatical works where it means a precept, rule or <BR>word, heading and applying to a number of particular rules <BR>which follow. Also written अधीकार. E. कृ with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. घञ्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. (-रः-री) One who has many duties to per<BR>form, very busy. E. अधि and कार; in the fem. with aff. ङीष्.

अधिकारस्थ
अधिकारस्थ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) Established in <BR>an office or charge. E. अधिकार and स्थ.

अधिकारिता
अधिकारिता f. (-ता) <BR>	1 Ownership, lordship. <BR>	2 Right, title &c. <BR>See अधिकारिन्. Also अधिकारित्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधि- <BR>कारिन्, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

अधिकारिन्
अधिकारिन् I. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) (In law.) Possessing <BR>a right or title. <BR>II. m. (-री) <BR>	1 A superintendent, a ruler, a director. <BR>	2 One holding an office. <BR>	3 A master, an owner. <BR>	4 (In the Mī<BR>mānsā.) One entitled to institute a sacrifice; see अधिकार. <BR>	5 (In the Vedānta.) A person who is perfect in the principles <BR>and practice of the Vedānta. <BR>	6 Man (in general). E. अधि- <BR>कार, taddh. aff. इनि.

अधिकार्थवचन
अधिकार्थवचन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Exaggeration, hyperbole. <BR>E. अधिक-अर्थ and वचन.

अधिकार्म
अधिकार्म Tatpur. n. (-र्मम्). Perhaps the name of a place or <BR>country. E. अधिक and अर्म.

अधिकृत
अधिकृत Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Superintended, <BR>governed. <BR>	2 Claimed or held as a right. <BR>	3 Set as a rule or <BR>authority. <BR>	4 Set over, superintendent. <BR>II. m. (-तः) <BR>	1 A superintendent in general. <BR>	2 Inspector <BR>of receipts and disbursements, an auditor of public ac<BR>compts. E. कृ with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिकृति
अधिकृति Tatpur. f. (-तिः) A possession, a right, a privilege. <BR>See अधिकरण. E. कृ with अधि, kṛt aff. क्तिन्.

अधिक्रम
अधिक्रम Tatpur. m. (-मः) Invasion, assailing. E. क्रम् with <BR>अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अधिक्षित्
अधिक्षित् Tatpur. m. (-त्) (ved.) Lord, ruler. E. क्षि with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. क्विप्.

अधिक्षिप्त
अधिक्षिप्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्) <BR>	1 Censured, reviled, <BR>detracted from. <BR>	2 Thrown or cast down. <BR>	3 Dismissed, sent, <BR>dispatched. <BR>	4 Placed, fixed. E. क्षिप् with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिक्षेप
अधिक्षेप Tatpur. m. (-पः) <BR>	1 Detraction, censure. <BR>	2 Dismissal, <BR>dispatch. E. क्षिप् with अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अधिगत
अधिगत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Obtained. <BR>	2 Gone <BR>through or over, lit. or fig. as read, studied. E. गम् with <BR>अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिगन्तव्य
अधिगन्तव्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be reached, attain<BR>able, acquirable, lit. or fig. E. गम् with अधि, kṛtya aff. तव्य.

अधिगन्तृ
अधिगन्तृ Tatpur. m. (-न्ता) One who obtains or acquires. E. <BR>गम् with अधि, kṛt aff. तृच्.

अधिगम
अधिगम Tatpur. m. (-मः) <BR>	1 Obtaining, attaining, acquiring. <BR>	2 Attainment, apprehension, going through or over, lit. or <BR>fig. <BR>	3 Profit, gain, interest on capital or risk. E. गम् with <BR>अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अधिगमन
अधिगमन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) <BR>	1 Obtaining, attaining, acquiring. <BR>	2 Attainment, apprehension, going through or over, lit. or <BR>fig. as reading, studying. E. गम् with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिगमनीय
अधिगमनीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be reached, <BR>attainable, acquirable, lit. or fig. E. गम् with अधि, kṛtya <BR>aff. अनीयर्.

अधिगम्य
अधिगम्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-म्यः-म्या-म्यम्) Attainable, to be reached <BR>or acquired, lit. or fig. E. गम् with अधि, kṛtya aff. यत्.

अधिगव
अधिगव Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वी-वम्) (ved.) On the cow, <BR>coming from the cow (as milk &c.). E. अधि and गो, <BR>samāsānta aff. टच्.

अधिगुण
अधिगुण Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Of superior quali<BR>ties. E. अधि and गुण.

अधिज
अधिज Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) <BR>	1 Superior by birth. <BR>	2 Born from, produced on(?). E. जन् with अधि, kṛt aff. ड.

अधिजनन
अधिजनन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Birth. E. जन् with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिजिह्व
अधिजिह्व Bahuvr. m. (-ह्वः) One of the diseases of the throat, <BR>described as ‘a swelling at the root of the tongue like a second <BR>tongue’ (probably a swelling of the epiglottis)--therefore <BR>called also द्विजिह्व--and produced by the phlegm and blood; <BR>when it suppurates, considered as incurable. Also अधि- <BR>जिह्विका. E. अधि and जिह्वा.

अधिजिह्विका
अधिजिह्विका Bahuvr. f. (-का) The same as the preceding. <BR>E. अधिजिह्व, samāsānta aff. कप्.

अधिज्य
अधिज्य Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ज्यः-ज्या-ज्यम्) Strung (as a bow). <BR>E. अधि and ज्या.

अधिज्योतिषम्
अधिज्योतिषम् Avyayībh. Concerning or relating to the lu<BR>minous part of creation; a chapter in the Upanishads treat<BR>ing thereon, comprises the following subjects: fire, sun, <BR>water and the substance of lightning. E. अधि and ज्योतिष.

अधित्यका
अधित्यका f. (-का) Land on the upper part of a mountain. <BR>E. अधि, taddh. aff. त्यकन्.

अधिदन्त
अधिदन्त Tatpur. m. (-न्तः) A tooth growing over another. <BR>See अधिकदन्त and वर्धन. E. अधि and दन्त.

अधिदिन
अधिदिन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The same as अधिकदिन. E. अ- <BR>धि and दिन.

अधिदेव
अधिदेव I. Tatpur. m. (-वः) <BR>	1 A supreme or tutelary deity. <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-वम्) Concerning the gods. (In derivatives <BR>with a taddh. aff. which has an anubandha ञ्, ण् or क्, both <BR>parts of this word have vṛddhi, f. i. आधिदैविक q. v.) E. <BR>अधि and देव.

अधिदेवतम्
अधिदेवतम् Avyayībh. Concerning the divinities or the gods. <BR>E. अधि and देवता.

अधिदेवता
अधिदेवता Tatpur. f. (-ता) A tutelary or presiding divinity. <BR>E. अधि and देवता.

अधिदेवन
अधिदेवन n. (-नम्) The ground in a hall, on which gambling <BR>with dice takes place. E. दिव्, with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिदैव
अधिदैव I. Tatpur. n. (-वम्) and <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-वम्). See the following. E. अधि and दैव.

अधिदैवत
अधिदैवत I. Tatpur. n. (-तम्) <BR>	1 The supreme or tutelary <BR>deity. <BR>	2 The active principle in creation, the regulating <BR>power which resides in water, fire, sky, air, the regions <BR>&c. See also अधिभूत, अध्यात्म. <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-तम्) Concerning <BR>	1 the deity or <BR>	2 the active <BR>principle in creation. E. अधि and दैवत.

अधिप
अधिप Tatpur. m. (-पः) <BR>	1 An owner, a lord or master. <BR>	2 A <BR>king. <BR>	3 (In astrology.) The regent of a sign of the zodiac. <BR>E. पा with अधि, kṛt aff. क.

अधिपति
अधिपति Tatpur. m. (-तिः) <BR>	1 A master, an owner, a ruler. <BR>	2 A <BR>king. (A noun depending upon it in these meanings stands in <BR>the gen. or loc., f. i. गवामधिपति or गोष्वधिपति.) <BR>	3 (In me<BR>dicine.) ‘That part of the trunk which is inside of the <BR>upper part of the head, at the passage of the vessel along <BR>the lateral sinus; wounds inflicted there produce instan<BR>taneous death’. E. पा with अधि, uṇ. aff. डति.

अधिपतिवती
अधिपतिवती f. (-ती) The name of certain female divinities <BR>(in the Vedas). See पत्नी. E. अधिपति, taddh. aff. मतुप्, <BR>the change of म् in the affix to व् being restricted, in this <BR>word, to the vaidik meaning of it.

अधिपत्नी
अधिपत्नी Tatpur. f. (-त्नी) A mistress, a protectress. E. <BR>अधिपति, fem. aff. ङीप्, and न् ādeśa for the final इ.

अधिपथम्
अधिपथम् Avyayībh. Over or across a road. E. अधि and <BR>पथिन्, samāsānta aff. अ.

अधिपा
अधिपा Tatpur. m. (-पाः) (ved.) A master, a lord, a pro<BR>tector. E. पा with अधि, kṛt aff. विच्.

अधिपांशुल
अधिपांशुल Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Where dust is lying <BR>on or has risen from, dusty. Also written अधिपांसुल. E. <BR>अधि and पांसुल.

अधिपुरुष
अधिपुरुष Tatpur. m. (-षः) The supreme or presiding spirit. <BR>E. अधि and पुरुष.

अधिप्रजम्
अधिप्रजम् Avyayībh. Concerning or relating to the continua<BR>tion of the world by procreation; a chapter in the Upa<BR>nishads treating thereon comprises the subjects: mother, <BR>father, posterity and generation. E. अधि and प्रजा.

अधिप्रष्टि
अधिप्रष्टि Avyayībh. (ved.) Over the Praṣṭi (q. v.). See the <BR>following. E. अधि and प्रष्टि.

अधिप्रष्टियुग
अधिप्रष्टियुग Tatpur. m. (-गः) (ved.) The yoke over the <BR>Praṣṭi horse, to which a fourth horse was put (in a cere<BR>mony connected with the Vājapeya sacrifice; two horses <BR>being put before a cart and a third in front of the two, <BR>so as to form with them a kind of triangle or tripod <BR>(प्रष्टि q. v.), wherefore the third horse was called meta<BR>phorically the Praṣṭi). E. अधिप्रष्टि and युग.

अधिभू
अधिभू Tatpur. m. (-भूः) A master, a ruler. E. भू with अधि, kṛt <BR>aff. क्विप्.

अधिभूत
अधिभूत I. Tatpur. n. (-तम्) A subtile or invisible element, <BR>one which is the cause of the gross or visible elements <BR>(also as an attribute of the supreme soul that pervades and <BR>regulates all elements or existence). <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-तम्) Concerning or relating to the bhūta <BR>or elements; a chapter in the Upanishads includes under <BR>this topic, earth, atmosphere, material heaven, regions, <BR>intermediate regions, fire, air, sun, moon, lunar mansions, <BR>water, annual plants, trees, ether, soul. (In derivatives <BR>with a taddh. aff. which has an anubandha ञ्, ण् or क्, <BR>both parts of this word assume vṛddhi, f. i. आधिभौतिक.) <BR>E. अधि and भूत.

अधिमन्थ
अधिमन्थ Tatpur. m. (-न्थः) (In medicine.) Severe ophthal<BR>mia which is described as having the following symptoms: <BR>‘acute pains as if the eyes were torn; throbbing which ex<BR>tends to half of the head’; it consists of four varieties ac<BR>cording to its being produced by derangement of the air, <BR>bile, phlegm or blood. Also अधीमन्थ. E. अधि and मन्थ.

अधिमन्थन
अधिमन्थन Tatpur. m. n. (-नः-नम्) (ved.) A piece of wood from <BR>the paring of the sacrificial post, placed over the araṇi <BR>(q. v.) to kindle a fire by attrition. E. मन्थ् with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. ल्युट्; scil. शकल.

अधिमन्थित
अधिमन्थित m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Affected with the disease <BR>called अधिमन्थ q. v. E. अधिमन्थय् (अधिमन्थ, denom. aff. <BR>णिच्), kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिमांस
अधिमांस Tatpur. m. (-सः) (In medicine.) A disease of the <BR>gums, described as ‘a great and painful swelling round the <BR>wisdom-tooth with the discharge of saliva; produced by <BR>diseased phlegm’. Also अधिमांसक. E. अधि and मांस.

अधिमांसक
अधिमांसक m. (-कः). The same as the preceding. E. अधि- <BR>मांस, taddh. aff. कन्.

अधिमांसार्मन्
अधिमांसार्मन् Tatpur. n. (-र्म) (In medicine.) A disease of the <BR>white part on the conjunctiva of the eye; it is described as ‘a <BR>large, soft (fleshy growth), either liver-coloured or brown’. <BR>Also अधिकमांसार्मन्. E. अधिमांस (scil. ज) and अर्मन्; <BR>‘the disease अर्मन् produced by the fleshy excrescence’.

अधिमात्र
अधिमात्र I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Excessive, above <BR>measure. Cf. अतिमात्र. <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-त्रम्) Above syllabic measurement. (In <BR>the doctrine of the Upanishads the mysterious syllable ओम् <BR>is said to be exempt from the general rules of prosody. <BR>See also अध्यक्षर.) E. अधि and मात्रा.

अधिमात्रकारुणिक
अधिमात्रकारुणिक Tatpur. m. (-कः) The name of a Mahā<BR>brahman (q. v.) according to the mythology of the Buddhists. <BR>E. अधिमात्र and कारुणिक, lit. ‘excessively kind or com<BR>passionate’.

अधिमास
अधिमास Tatpur. m. (-सः) An intercalary month, formed of the <BR>aggregate days omitted in reckoning the lunar year, in com<BR>parison with the solar. See also अधिकमास. E. अधि and मास.

अधिमुक्ति
अधिमुक्ति Tatpur. f. (-क्ति) (In Buddhistic literature.) Com<BR>prehension, intelligence, natural disposition (of the soul). E. <BR>मुच् with अधि, kṛt aff. क्तिन्.

अधिमुक्तिक
अधिमुक्तिक m. (-कः) A name of Mahākāla (q. v.), according <BR>to the mythology of the Buddhists. E. अधिमुक्ति, taddh. <BR>aff. कन्(?).

अधिमुक्तिसार
अधिमुक्तिसार Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) (In Buddhistic <BR>literature.) Being quite comprehension, being thoroughly <BR>addicted to comprehending. E. अधिमुक्ति and सार.

अधिमुह्य
अधिमुह्य Tatpur. m. (-ह्यः) A name of Śākyamuni in <BR>one of his thirty-four anterior births. E. मुह् with अधि, <BR>kṛtya aff. यत्(?) or अधि and मुह्य. The word is doubtful.

अधियज्ञ
अधियज्ञ I. Tatpur. m. (-ज्ञः) <BR>	1 The supreme sacrifice, the <BR>sacrifice ϰατ᾽ἐξοχήν. <BR>	2 An influence superior to or pre<BR>siding over sacrifice. <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-ज्ञम्) Concerning or with respect to sa<BR>crifice. E. अधि and यज्ञ.

अधियाङ्ग
अधियाङ्ग Tatpur.(?) n. (-ङ्गम्). The same as अधिकाङ्ग of <BR>which it is given as a various reading. E. doubtful, per<BR>haps instead of अध्याङ्ग (अधि and आङ्ग), or of अधिकाङ्ग, <BR>with य् in the place of क्.

अधिरथ
अधिरथ Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-थः-था-थम्) Being on or <BR>above a car. <BR>II. m. (-थः) <BR>	1 A charioteer. <BR>	2 The proper name of a <BR>charioteer who was a prince and descendant of Anu and <BR>of Anga, a son of Satyakarman and foster father of Karṇa. <BR>E. अधि and रथ.

अधिरथि
अधिरथि m. (-थिः). See उदरथि of which it occurs as a <BR>various reading.

अधिराज्
अधिराज् Tatpur. m. (-राट्) A supreme king or ruler. E. <BR>अधि and राज्.

अधिराज
अधिराज Tatpur. m. (-जः). The same as the preceding. E. <BR>अधि and राजन्, samāsānta aff. टच्.

अधिराजन्
अधिराजन् Tatpur. m. (-जा). The same as अधिराज्. E. <BR>अधि and राजन्.

अधिराज्य
अधिराज्य Tatpur. n. (-ज्यम्) <BR>	1 Supreme sway. <BR>	2 Empire. <BR>	3 The name of a country, also read अधिराष्ट्र and अधि- <BR>वाज्य. E. अधि and राज्य.

अधिराज्यभाज्
अधिराज्यभाज् Tatpur. m. (-क्) An emperor, a paramount <BR>sovereign. E. अधिराज्य and भाज्.

अधिराष्ट्र
अधिराष्ट्र Tatpur. n. (-ष्ट्रम्). See अधिराज्य. E. अधि and राष्ट्र.

अधिरुक्म
अधिरुक्म Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्मः-क्मा-क्मम्) Wearing gold. <BR>E. अधि and रुक्म.

अधिरूढ
अधिरूढ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) Ascended or gone over, <BR>lit. or fig., act. or pass., person. or impersonally. E. रुह् <BR>with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिरोपण
अधिरोपण Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Causing to ascend, placing over. <BR>E. रुह् with अधि, in the caus., kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिरोपित
अधिरोपित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Placed over, lit. <BR>or fig. E. रुह् with अधि, in the caus., kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिरोह
अधिरोह Tatpur. m. (-हः) Surmounting, ascending, over<BR>topping. E. रुह् with अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अधिरोहण
अधिरोहण Tatpur. I. n. (-णम्) Ascending, surmounting, over<BR>topping. <BR>II. f. (-णी) A ladder, a staircase. See also अधिरोहिणी. <BR>E. रुह् with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिरोहिन्
अधिरोहिन् Tatp. I. m. f. n. (-ही-हिणी-हि) Who rises on or above. <BR>II. f. (-णी) A ladder, a staircase. See अधिरोहणी. E. <BR>रुह् with अधि, kṛt aff. णिनि(?).

अधिलोकम्
अधिलोकम् Avyayībh. Concerning or relating to the world. <BR>A chapter in the Upanishads treating thereon comprises <BR>the subjects: earth, sky, æther, wind. E. अधि and लोक.

अधिवक्तृ
अधिवक्तृ Tatpur. m. (-क्ता) I. A partisan, an advocate. E. वच् <BR>with अधि, kṛt aff. तृच्. <BR>II. One who speaks in a superior manner, very eloquent. <BR>E. अधि and वक्तृ.

अधिवचन
अधिवचन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) I. Advocating, speaking in <BR>favour of another. E. वच् with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्. <BR>II. A name, an appellation. E. अधि and वचन.

अधिवस्त्र
अधिवस्त्र Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्त्रः-स्त्रा-स्त्रम्) Wearing cloth or <BR>raiment. E. अधि and वस्त्र.

अधिवाज्य
अधिवाज्य n. (-ज्यम्) The name of a country; see अधिराज्य <BR>which seems to be the more correct reading of this word.

अधिवास
अधिवास Tatpur. m. (-सः) I. <BR>	1 One who dwells above others. <BR>	2 One who dwells near others, a neighbour. <BR>	3 An in<BR>habitant. <BR>	4 An abode, a place or situation. E. वस् (to <BR>dwell &c.) with अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्. <BR>II. A cover, an upper garment. Also अधीवास. E. वस् <BR>(to cover with dress) with अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्. <BR>III. Continuance, perseverance, esp. fig.: fixing one's <BR>self at a person's door in order to enforce compliance with <BR>some demand. E. वस् (वसु) with अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्. <BR>IV. <BR>	1 Perfuming or dressing the person &c.; (as materials and <BR>objects of toilet by which this is done, are enumerated the fol<BR>lowing: मृत्तिका, गन्धः, शिला, धान्यम्, दूर्वा, पुष्पम्, फलम्, <BR>दधि, घृतम्, स्वस्तिकम्, सिन्दूरम्, शङ्खः, कज्जलम्, रोचना, श्वे- <BR>तसर्षपः, स्वर्णम्, रौप्यम्, ताम्रम्, चामरम्, दर्पणम्, दीपः, प्रश- <BR>स्तपात्रम्). <BR>	2 See अधिवासन. E. वास् with अधि, kṛt aff. अच्.

अधिवासन
अधिवासन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) I. <BR>	1 Perfuming or dressing the per<BR>son &c. (see अधिवास IV. 1.). <BR>	2 A religious ceremony, pre<BR>liminary to any great Hindu festival: touching a vessel <BR>containing perfumes, flowers and other things previously <BR>presented to an idol, or offering perfumes &c. to it. E. वास् <BR>with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्. <BR>II. <BR>	1 A summoning and fixing of the presence of a divinity upon <BR>an image &c., when he is wanted for any solemnity. <BR>	2 The <BR>placing of a new image in water &c. the day before the divinity <BR>is to be summoned to inhabit it. <BR>	3 The same as अधिवास III. <BR>E. वस् (वसु) with अधि, in the caus., kṛt aff. युच्(?).

अधिवासभूमि
अधिवासभूमि Tatpur. f. (-मिः) A dwelling place. E. अधिवास <BR>and भूमि.

अधिवासित
अधिवासित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) I. Invested with. E. <BR>वस् (to cover with dress) with अधि, in the caus., kṛt aff. क्त. <BR>II. Perfumed, scented. E. वास् with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिवासिता
अधिवासिता f. (-ता) Residence, staying or abiding in one <BR>place. Also अधिवासित्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधिवासिन्, taddh. <BR>aff. तल् or त्व.

अधिवासिन्
अधिवासिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Staying or <BR>abiding in one place. E. वस् with अधि, kṛt aff. णिनि(?).

अधिवाहन
अधिवाहन Bahuvr. m. (-नः) A proper name; acc. to some, <BR>a son of Anga. E. अधि and वाहन.

अधिविद्यम्
अधिविद्यम् Avyayībh. Concerning or relating to knowledge. A <BR>chapter in the Upanishads treating thereon comprises the sub<BR>jects: teacher, pupil, science and expounding. E. अधि and विद्या.

अधिविन्ना
अधिविन्ना Tatpur. f. (-न्ना) (In law.) A wife whose husband has <BR>subsequently married others; a superseded wife. E. विद् (विदॢ) <BR>with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त, or according to another etym. a Bahuvr. <BR>of अधि and विन्न, taken either in the sense of विन्ना or विन्नम्.

अधिवेत्तव्या
अधिवेत्तव्या Tatpur. f. (-व्या) A wife deserving or proper to be <BR>superseded by her husband marrying another. Also अधिवेद्या <BR>or अधिवेदनीया. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kṛtya aff. तव्य.

अधिवेत्तृ
अधिवेत्तृ Tatpur. m. (-त्ता) A man marrying another than <BR>his first wife. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kṛt aff. तृच्.

अधिवेदन
अधिवेदन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Marrying again, whilst a former <BR>wife is living. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिवेदनीया
अधिवेदनीया Tatpur. f. (-या). The same as अधिवेत्तव्या. E. <BR>विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kṛtya aff. अनीयर्.

अधिवेदम्
अधिवेदम् Avyayībh. Concerning or with respect to the Veda. <BR>E. अधि and वेद.

अधिवेद्या
अधिवेद्या Tatpur. f. (-द्या). The same as अधिवेत्तव्या. E. विद् <BR>(विदॢ) with अधि, kṛtya aff. यत्.

अधिशयित
अधिशयित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Lain or slept over or <BR>upon; used either in an active or passive sense, personally <BR>or impersonally. E. शी with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिश्रयण
अधिश्रयण Tatpur. I. n. (-णम्) Placing over the fire a pot &c. <BR>(the reverse of अवश्रयण q. v.); also as a sacrificial act which <BR>occurs in several sacrifices, the Darśapūrṇamāsa, Vājapeya &c. <BR>II. f. (-णी) A furnace or fire-place. E. श्रि with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. ल्युट्, in the fem. with ङीप्.

अधिश्रयणीय
अधिश्रयणीय m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Relating to the अधि- <BR>श्रयण q. v. E. अधिश्रयण, taddh. aff. छ.

अधिश्रित
अधिश्रित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Placed over the fire. <BR>E. श्रि with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिषवण
अधिषवण Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (ved.) The name of two wooden <BR>boards, on which the juice of the Soma plant was expressed <BR>and where the Somābhiṣava (q. v.) was placed, in sacrifices <BR>as the Jyotiṣṭoma or those sharing in the principal rites <BR>of it. E. सू with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिष्ठातृ
अधिष्ठातृ Tatp. I. m. f. n. (-ता-त्री-तृ) Governing, directing, ruling. <BR>II. m. (-ता) <BR>	1 A ruler, a governor, a superintendent. <BR>	2 (According to the doctrine of the Pāśupatas) Īśvara, <BR>the superintending or ruling providence. (In the feminine <BR>esp. in conjunction with देवता, a ruling or tutelary divinity.) <BR>E. स्था with अधि, kṛt aff. तृच्.

अधिष्ठान
अधिष्ठान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) <BR>	1 Abiding, resting upon. <BR>	2 Site, <BR>situation. <BR>	3 A town. <BR>	4 (In architecture.) Base, basement. <BR>	5 Power, dignity, superintendence. <BR>	6 Prescribed rule, fixed <BR>practice. <BR>	7 A wheel. <BR>	8 Approaching. <BR>	9 (In Buddhistic litera<BR>ture.) Benediction. E. स्था with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अधिष्ठानशरीर
अधिष्ठानशरीर Karmadh. n. (-रम्) (In Sāṅkhya phil.) According <BR>to some, an intermediate body between the लिङ्गशरीर and स्थूल- <BR>शरीर (qq. vv.), one that is supposed to enable the subtle body <BR>to assume the corporeity of gross body. E. अधिष्ठान and शरीर.

अधिष्ठायक
अधिष्ठायक Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यकः-यिका-यकम्) Superintending, <BR>governing. E. स्था with अधि, kṛt aff. ण्वुल् and āgama युक्.

अधिष्ठित
अधिष्ठित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Fixed, determined, estab<BR>lished; literally or figuratively, as a house or a practice. <BR>	2 Inha<BR>bited, occupied. <BR>	3 Supervised, superintended, guarded. <BR>	4 Ap<BR>pointed. <BR>	5 Superintending, inhabiting, occupying. Used act. or <BR>pass., person. or impersonally. E. स्था with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधिस्त्री
अधिस्त्री I. Tatpur. f. (-स्त्री) A superior or excellent woman. <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-स्त्रि) Used in the same sense as the lo<BR>cative of स्त्री. E. अधि and स्त्री.

अधिहरि
अधिहरि Avyayībh. Used in the same sense as the locative <BR>of हरि. E. अधि and हरि.

अधीकार
अधीकार Tatpur. m. (-रः). See अधिकार.

अधीगर्थ
अधीगर्थ Bahuvr. m. (-र्थः) (In grammatical terminology.) <BR>A radical having the sense of remembering. E. इक् (the <BR>technical form of इ in the sense of remembering) with अधि, <BR>and अर्थ; scil. धातु.

अधीत
अधीत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Read, obtained &c. E. <BR>इ (इङ् or इक्) with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अधीतवेद
अधीतवेद Bahuvr. m. (-दः) A Brahman, who has read the Vedas; <BR>a student who has finished his course of study. E. अधीत and वेद.

अधीति
अधीति Tatpur. f. (-तिः) <BR>	1 Study, perusal. <BR>	2 (ved.) Recollec<BR>tion, desire. E. इ (<BR>	1 इङ्, <BR>	2 इक्) with अधि, kṛt aff. क्तिन्.

अधीतिन्
अधीतिन् m. f. n. (-ती-तिनी-ति) Well read in, conversant <BR>with, versed in (with a noun in the locative; f. i. अधीती <BR>व्याकरणे, versed in grammar). E. अधीत, taddh. aff. इनि.

अधीन
अधीन Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) <BR>	1 Dependant. <BR>	2 Docile. E. <BR>अधि and इन ‘having a master over one's self’. This word <BR>and the etymology as mentioned, are given by the native <BR>lexicographers; but according to the best grammatical autho<BR>rities अधीन would not exist as a real word. Words as रा- <BR>जाधीन, ब्राह्मणाधीन and the like, are explained by them as <BR>coming from राजाधि (राजन् and अधि), ब्राह्मणाधि (ब्राह्मण <BR>and अधि) with taddh. aff. ख, or by others as derived from रा- <BR>जन्, ब्राह्मण with taddh. aff. सधीनन्; it would seem therefore <BR>that the use of अधीन as an independant word is grammatically <BR>not correct. But see अध्यधीन and अनधीनक.

अधीनता
अधीनता f. (-ता) Subjection, dependance, slavery: so अधी- <BR>नत्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधीन, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व. The gram<BR>matical correctness of this word is questionable; see the E. <BR>of the preceding.

अधीमन्थ
अधीमन्थ Tatpur. m. (-न्थः). The same as अधिमन्थ q. v.; the <BR>vowel in अधि being lengthened.

अधीयत्
अधीयत् Tatpur. I. m. (-यन्) A student who reads the Veda &c. <BR>with facility or ease. See अधीयान. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. शतृ. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-यन्-यती-यत्) Remembering. E. इ (इक्) <BR>with अधि, kṛt aff. शतृ.

अधीयान
अधीयान m. (-नः) A student, one going over or reading the <BR>Vedas &c. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛt aff. शानच्.

अधीर
अधीर Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) <BR>	1 Unsteady, unstable <BR>(lit. or met.). <BR>	2 Perplexed, confused, not possessed of self<BR>command. <BR>	3 Unwise. <BR>II. f. (-रा) <BR>	1 Lightning. <BR>	2 (In rhetoric.) A cross or ca<BR>pricious mistress, one not possessed of self-command; with <BR>two varieties, the मध्या or adolescent dame who will ‘as<BR>sail her lover with harsh speeches’ and the प्रगल्भा or <BR>प्रौढा or mature dame who will ‘scold and beat him’. <BR>See also धीरा and धीराधीरा. E. अ neg. and धीर.

अधीरता
अधीरता f. (-ता) Fickleness, unsteadiness; also अधीरत्व n. <BR>(-त्वम्). E. अधीर, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

अधीवास
अधीवास Tatpur. m. (-सः). The same as अधिवास II., the इ <BR>in अधि being made long.

अधीश
अधीश Tatpur. m. (-शः) A master, a lord. E. अधि and ईश.

अधीश्वर
अधीश्वर Tatpur. m. (-रः) <BR>	1 An emperor, a king paramount <BR>over all the neighbouring princes. <BR>	2 An Arhat, according <BR>to the Jainas. E. अधि and ईश्वर.

अधीष्ट
अधीष्ट Tatpur. I. m. (-ष्टः) One requested or honourably engaged <BR>to assume a duty, as a teacher &c. (not one hired for money). <BR>II. n. (-ष्टम्) An honourable occupation. E. इष् with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. क्त.

अधुना
अधुना ind. Now, at present. E. अश् (i. e. अ, considered as <BR>a substitute of इदम्), taddh. aff. अधुना.

अधुनातन
अधुनातन m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Of or belonging to the <BR>present. E. अधुना, taddh. aff. ट्यु and āgama तुट्.

अधुर
अधुर Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Having no load (as a <BR>cart). E. अ priv. and धुर्, samāsānta aff. अ.

अधृत
अधृत Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unheld, undetained. <BR>II. m. (-तः) A name of Viṣṇu. E. अ neg. and धृत.

अधृति
अधृति I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः) <BR>	1 Laxity, want of firm hold. <BR>	2 Want of steadiness or firmness. (In rhetoric described as <BR>one of the conditions connected with the Rasa Śṛṅgāra <BR>q. v.) E. अ neg. and धृति. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति) Having no steadiness <BR>or firmness. E. अ priv. and धृति.

अधृष्ट
अधृष्ट Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) <BR>	1 Ashamed, modest, <BR>humble. <BR>	2 Not overcome, invincible. E. अ neg. and धृष्ट.

अधृष्य
अधृष्य Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) <BR>	1 Proud, vain. <BR>	2 Irresistible, invincible. <BR>II. f. (-ष्या) The name of a river. E. अ neg. and धृष्य.

अधेनु
अधेनु Tatpur. f. (-नुः) A cow that does not yield milk. E. <BR>अ deter. and धेनु.

अधैर्य
अधैर्य I. Tatpur. n. (-र्यम्) Instability, want of firmness. E. <BR>अ neg. and धैर्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्) Unsteady, feeble, ir<BR>resolute. E. अ priv. and धैर्य.

अधोशुक
अधोऽशुक Tatpur. n. (-कम्) A lower garment. E. अधस् and अंशुक.

अधोअक्ष
अधोअक्ष Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) (ved.) Being under the <BR>axle of a car or under a car. See अधोऽक्ष. E. अधस् and अक्ष.

अधोक्ष
अधोऽक्ष Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्). The same as अधो- <BR>अक्ष. E. अधस् and अक्ष.

अधोक्षज
अधोऽक्षज Tatpur. m. (-जः) <BR>	1 A name of Kṛṣṇa. <BR>	2 The sign <BR>Śravaṇā. Also written अधोक्षज. E. अधस्-अक्ष and ज; <BR>‘Kṛṣṇa, as a child, killed, when lying under a car, Pūtanā, <BR>a female fiend who was hovering over it in the shape of a <BR>bird, and thus, as it were, was born again (under the car)’; <BR>or according to others, from अधोक्ष, the name of a Ṛṣi, <BR>and ज, ‘a son of Adhoksha’; or, ‘because he is produced by <BR>or to such as have subdued or cast down their passions, <BR>i. e. because he becomes visible to them’; or a Bahuvr. from <BR>अधस् and अक्षज (n. knowledge derived from the senses; <BR>m. pl. living beings), ‘because he has subdued all untrue <BR>knowledge or because he is superior to all living beings’.

अधोगत
अधोगत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Descended, gone <BR>down, lit. or fig. E. अधस् and गत.

अधोगति
अधोगति I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः) Going downwards, lit. or fig. <BR>as degradation, going into hell &c. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति) Descending, going down<BR>wards, lit. or fig. E. अधस् and गति. In the same sense <BR>अधोगम Tatpur. m. (-मः) and अधोगमन Tatpur. n. (-नम्).

अधोगामिन्
अधोगामिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि) Descending, <BR>going downwards. See the preceding. E. अधस् and गामिन्.

अधोघण्ठा
अधोघण्ठा Bahuvr. f. (-ण्टा) A plant (Acheranthes aspera). <BR>See अपामार्ग. E. अधस् and घण्टा.

अधोङ्ग
अधोऽङ्ग Tatpur. n. (-ङ्गम्) <BR>	1 The anus. <BR>	2 Pudendum muliebre; <BR>also written अधोङ्ग. E. अधस् and अङ्ग.

अधोजानु
अधोजानु Avyayībh. Under the knee, lower than the knee. <BR>E. अधस् and जानु.

अधोजिह्विका
अधोजिह्विका Tatpur. f. (-का) The uvula or soft palate. E. <BR>अधस् and जिह्विका.

अधोदारु
अधोदारु Tatpur. m. n. (-रुः-रु) The under timber (of a <BR>pillar &c.). E. अधस् and दारु.

अधोदिश्
अधोदिश् Tatpur. f. (-दिक्) <BR>	1 The lower region. <BR>	2 The <BR>Nadir. E. अधस् and दिश्.

अधोदृष्टि
अधोदृष्टि I. Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) A downcast look. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ष्टिः-ष्टिः-ष्टि) Downcast, one who <BR>looks down. E. अधस् and दृष्टि.

अधोदेश
अधोदेश Tatpur. m. (-शः) <BR>	1 The bottom, the lowest part. <BR>	2 The lower part of the body. E. अधस् and देश.

अधोद्वार
अधोद्वार Tatpur. n. (-रम्) <BR>	1 The anus. <BR>	2 Pudendum muliebre. <BR>E. अधस् and द्वार.

अधोनाभम्
अधोनाभम् Avyayībh. Under the navel. E. अधस् and नाभि, <BR>samāsānta aff. अ.

अधोपहास
अधोपहास Tatpur. m. (-सः) Copulation, coition. E. This <BR>word occurs only in the Upan. and seems to be an irre<BR>gular compound formed of the phrase अध उप ह आस, <BR>‘she was or lay under (him)’.

अधोबन्धन
अधोबन्धन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) An under girth or strap. E. <BR>अधस् and बन्धन.

अधोभक्त
अधोभक्त Tatpur. n. (-क्तम्) (In medicine.) A medicament <BR>which is to be taken after eating; one of the ten kinds of <BR>medicaments classified according to the time of their appli<BR>cation; see besides निर्भक्त, प्राग्भक्त, मध्येभक्त, अन्तराभक्त, <BR>सभक्त, सामुद्ग, मुहुर्मुहुर्ग्रास (which is twofold) and ग्रा- <BR>सान्तर. E. अधस् and भक्त, scil. औषध.

अधोभव
अधोभव Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Placed below, inferior. <BR>E. अधस् and भव.

अधोभाग
अधोभाग Tatpur. m. (-गः) <BR>	1 The bottom, the lowest part. <BR>	2 The lower part of the body. E. अधस् and भाग.

अधोभागदोषहर
अधोभागदोषहर Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Removing or <BR>curing diseases of the lower part of the body (as a me<BR>dicine). E. अधोभाग-दोष and हर.

अधोभुवन
अधोभुवन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The world below, the regions <BR>below the earth. E. अधस् and भुवन.

अधोभूमि
अधोभूमि Tatpur. f. (-मिः) A place or land below (such as <BR>land at the foot of a mountain &c.). E. अधस् and भूमि.

अधोमर्मन्
अधोमर्मन् Tatpur. n. (-र्म) The anus. E. अधस् and मर्मन्.

अधोमुख
अधोमुख Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-खः-खा or खी-खम्) <BR>	1 Downlooked, <BR>looking downwards. <BR>	2 Inverted, turned upside down, headlong. <BR>II. m. (-खः) A name of Viṣṇu. <BR>III. f. (-खा) A plant (Premna esculenta). See गोजिह्वा. <BR>IV. n. (-खम्) A division of Naraka or hell. See अधःशिरस्. <BR>E. अधस् and मुख; in the fem. with aff. टाप् or ङीष्.

अधोयन्त्र
अधोयन्त्र Tatpur. n. (-न्त्रम्) A still, or the lower of two vessels <BR>luted together for distilling, sublimation &c. E. अधस् and यन्त्र.

अधोरक्तपित्त
अधोरक्तपित्त Tatpur. n. (-त्तम्) (In medicine.) See अधोऽस्रपित्त. <BR>E. अधस् and रक्तपित्त.

अधोराम
अधोराम Tatpur. m. (-मः) (ved.) White--(or according to <BR>others, dark)--coloured on the lower part of the body, an <BR>epithet of the goat, one of the twelve ऐकादशिन (q. v.) <BR>animals in the Aśvamedha sacrifice. E. अधस् and राम.

अधोलम्ब
अधोलम्ब Tatpur. m. (-म्बः) The perpendicular. Also अव- <BR>लम्ब, वलम्ब and लम्ब. E. अधस् and लम्ब.

अधोलोक
अधोलोक Tatpur. m. (-कः) The regions below the earth. E. <BR>अधस् and लोक.

अधोवदन
अधोवदन Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्). The same as अधो- <BR>मुख q. v. E. अधस् and वदन.

अधोवश
अधोवश Tatpur. m. (-शः) <BR>	1 The bottom of a thing. <BR>	2 Pu<BR>dendum muliebre. E. अधस् and वश.

अधोवायु
अधोवायु Tatpur. m. (-युः) <BR>	1 The vital air that passes down<BR>wards, one of the five vital airs. <BR>	2 Ventris crepitus. E. <BR>अधस् and वायु.

अधोस्रपित्त
अधोऽस्रपित्त Tatpur. n. (-त्तम्) (In medicine.) A kind of ple<BR>thora, ‘when blood is discharged from the anus and urethra’. <BR>Also written अधोस्रपित्त. E. अधस् and अस्रपित्त.

अध्यक्ष
अध्यक्ष Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) <BR>	1 Perceptible, present <BR>to the senses. <BR>	2 Superintending, presiding over. <BR>II. m. (-क्षः) <BR>	1 A superintendent in general, one of receipts <BR>and disbursements. <BR>	2 A plant (a species of Mimusops). See <BR>क्षीरिका and फलाध्यक्ष. E. अधि and अक्ष, or more correctly, as <BR>also mentioned in the native etym., अक्ष् with अधि, kṛt aff. अच्.

अध्यक्षरम्
अध्यक्षरम् Avyayībh. Above all other letters (in importance <BR>or in place; being often put at the head of various writings, <BR>as the mysterious syllable ओम्). E. अधि and अक्षर.

अध्यग्नि
अध्यग्नि Avyayībh. (In law.) Property given to the wife at <BR>the time of her marriage, one of the six items of woman's <BR>peculiar property. See स्त्रीधन. E. अधि and अग्नि; lit. <BR>(presented) over the (nuptial) fire.

अध्यग्निकृत
अध्यग्निकृत Tatpur. n. (-तम्). The same as the preceding. E. <BR>अध्यग्नि and कृत; sc. स्त्रीधन (q. v.).

अध्यग्न्युपागत
अध्यग्न्युपागत Tatpur. n. (-तम्). The same as the preceding. <BR>E. अध्यग्नि and उपागत; sc. स्त्रीधन (q. v.).

अध्यञ्च्
अध्यञ्च् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ध्यङ्-धीची-ध्यक्) Superior, best. E. <BR>अञ्च् (I. 1.) with अधि, kṛt aff. क्विन्, in the fem. with aff. <BR>ङीप्. For the declension of this word see अञ्च् II.

अध्यण्डा
अध्यण्डा Bahuvr. f. (-ण्डा) <BR>	1 Cowach. See अव्यङ्गा and कपिकच्छु. <BR>	2 According to others a synonyme of भूम्यामलकी. E. अधि <BR>and अण्ड ‘having excellent seed’(?).

अध्यधिक्षेप
अध्यधिक्षेप Tatpur. m. (-पः) Excessive censure. E. अधि and <BR>अधिक्षेप.

अध्यधीन
अध्यधीन Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Very dependant, <BR>slave by birth. E. अधि and अधीन, or अध्यधि, taddh. aff. <BR>ख; see the E. of अधीन.

अध्ययन
अध्ययन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Study, reading, especially of the <BR>sacred books; one of the six duties of a Brahman. E. इ <BR>(इङ्) with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अध्ययनतपस्
अध्ययनतपस् Dwandwa n. du. (-सी) Study and penance. <BR>(Only used in the dual.) E. अध्ययन and तपस्.

अध्ययनपुण्य
अध्ययनपुण्य Tatpur. n. (-ण्यम्) Religions merit or purity <BR>which is in the study of the sacred works. E. अध्ययन (in <BR>the sense of the locative) and पुण्य.

अध्ययनीय
अध्ययनीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be read or <BR>studied. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛtya aff. अनीयर्.

अध्यर्ध
अध्यर्ध Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्धः-र्धा-र्धम्) One and a half, having <BR>an extra half. See also सार्ध. (In derivatives of compounds <BR>the first part of which is अध्यर्ध and which have the meaning of <BR>‘measuring or weighing, worth, containing, bought for, pro<BR>duced from, consisting of &c.’, the affix which would be re<BR>quired, is dropped in many instances; see f. i. अध्यर्धकंस, <BR>अध्यर्धशूर्प &c.) E. अधि and अर्ध.

अध्यर्धक
अध्यर्धक m. f. n. (-र्धकः-र्धिका-र्धकम्) Bought for or worth, <BR>containing, produced from &c. one and a half. E. अध्यर्ध, <BR>taddh. aff. कन्.

अध्यर्धकंस
अध्यर्धकंस (accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-सः-सम्) One <BR>Kansa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-सः-सी-सम्) Containing, measuring, consist<BR>ing of, bought for &c. one Kansa (q. v.) and a half. E. <BR>अध्यर्ध and कंस; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. टिठन् <BR>is considered as dropped.

अध्यर्धकाकिणीक
अध्यर्धकाकिणीक (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) <BR>Weighing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Kākiṇī <BR>(q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-काकिणी (accord. to some, <BR>Dwigu), taddh. aff. ईकन्.

अध्यर्धकार्षापण
अध्यर्धकार्षापण (accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-णः-णम्) <BR>One Kārṣāpaṇa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-णः-णी-णम्) Weighing, worth, consisting of, <BR>bought for &c. one Kārṣāpaṇa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध <BR>and कार्षापण; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. टिठन् is <BR>considered as dropped. See also अध्यर्धकार्षापणिक.

अध्यर्धकार्षापणिक
अध्यर्धकार्षापणिक (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-की- <BR>कम्) Weighing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one <BR>Kārṣāpaṇa (q. v.) and a half. See also अध्यर्धकार्षापण II. <BR>E. अध्यर्धकार्षापण (I.), taddh. aff. टिठन्.

अध्यर्धखारीक
अध्यर्धखारीक (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) <BR>Measuring, containing, consisting of, bought for &c. one <BR>Khārī (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-खारी (accord. to some, <BR>Dwigu), taddh. aff. ईकन्.

अध्यर्धपण्य
अध्यर्धपण्य (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-ण्यः-ण्या-ण्यम्) <BR>Measuring or weighing, consisting of, bought for &c. one <BR>Paṇa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-पण (accord. to some, <BR>Dwigu), taddh. aff. यत्.

अध्यर्धपाद्य
अध्यर्धपाद्य (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) <BR>Measuring &c. one foot and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-पाद (accord. <BR>to some, Dwigu), taddh. aff. यत्.

अध्यर्धप्रतिक
अध्यर्धप्रतिक (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्). The <BR>same as अध्यर्धकार्षापण II. E. अध्यर्ध-प्रति (acc. to some, Dwigu) <BR>(considered as a substitute of कार्षापण), taddh. aff. टिठन्.

अध्यर्धमाष्य
अध्यर्धमाष्य (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) Weigh<BR>ing, consisting of, bought for &c. one Māṣa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>E. अध्यर्धमाष (accord. to some, Dwigu), taddh. aff. यत्.

अध्यर्धविंशतिकीन
अध्यर्धविंशतिकीन m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Measuring, worth, <BR>consisting of, bought for &c. twenty and a half (i. e. <BR>thirty). E. अध्यर्ध-विंशतिक, taddh. aff. ख.

अध्यर्धशत
अध्यर्धशत I. Dwandwa(?) n. (-तम्) Hundred and fifty. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Measuring, worth, consist<BR>ing of, bought for &c. hundred and fifty. E. अध्यर्ध and <BR>शत; in the meaning II. the aff. यत् is considered as dropped. <BR>See also अध्यर्धशत्य.

अध्यर्धशतमान
अध्यर्धशतमान (accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-नः-नम्) <BR>One Śatamāna (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, <BR>bought for &c. one Śatamāna (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध <BR>and शतमान; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. अण् is con<BR>sidered as dropped. See also अध्यर्धशातमान.

अध्यर्धशत्य
अध्यर्धशत्य m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) Measuring, worth, con<BR>sisting of, bought for &c. hundred and fifty. See also <BR>अध्यर्धशत. E. अध्यर्धशत (I.), taddh. aff. यत्.

अध्यर्धशाण
अध्यर्धशाण (accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. (-णः) One Śāṇa (q. v.) <BR>and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-णः-णी-णम्) Weighing, worth, consisting <BR>of, bought for &c. one Śāṇa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध <BR>and शाण; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. ठञ् is con<BR>sidered as dropped. See also the following.

अध्यर्धशाण्य
अध्यर्धशाण्य (acc. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-ण्यः-ण्या-ण्यम्) Weigh<BR>ing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Śāṇa (q. v.) and a <BR>half. See also the preceding. E. अध्यर्धशाण (I.), taddh. aff. यत्.

अध्यर्धशातमान
अध्यर्धशातमान (accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) <BR>Measuring, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Śatamāna <BR>and a half. See also अध्यर्धशतमान. E. अध्यर्धशतमान (I.), taddh. <BR>aff. अण्, with Vṛddhi in the latter part of the compound.

अध्यर्धशूर्प
अध्यर्धशूर्प (accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-र्पः-र्पम्) One Śūrpa <BR>and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-र्पः-र्पी-र्पम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, <BR>bought for &c. one Śūrpa and a half. E. अध्यर्ध and शूर्प; in <BR>the meaning II. the taddh. aff. अञ् or ठक् is considered as <BR>dropped.

अध्यर्धसहस्र
अध्यर्धसहस्र I. Dwandwa(?) n. (-स्रम्) Thousand and a half <BR>(i. e. thousand five hundred). <BR>II. m. f. n. (-स्रः-स्रा-स्रम्) Measuring, consisting of, worth, <BR>bought fort &c. thousand five hundred. E. अध्यर्ध and सहस्र; <BR>in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. अण् is considered as <BR>dropped. See also अध्यर्धसाहस्र.

अध्यर्धसाहस्र
अध्यर्धसाहस्र m. f. n. (-स्रः-स्री-स्रम्) Measuring, consisting of, worth, <BR>bought for &c. thousand five hundred. E. अध्यर्धसहस्र (I.), <BR>taddh. aff. अण् with Vṛddhi in the latter part of the compound.

अध्यर्धसुवर्ण
अध्यर्धसुवर्ण (accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-र्णः-र्णम्) <BR>One Suvarṇa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णी-र्णम्) Weighing, consisting of, worth, <BR>bought for &c. one Suvarṇa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध <BR>and सुवर्ण; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. ठक् is con<BR>sidered as dropped. See also the following.

अध्यर्धसौवर्णिक
अध्यर्धसौवर्णिक m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Weighing, produced <BR>from, worth, bought for &c. one Suvarṇa (q. v.) and a <BR>half. See also the preceding. E. अध्यर्धसुवर्ण (I.), taddh. aff. <BR>ठक्, with Vṛddhi in the latter part of the compound.

अध्यर्बुद
अध्यर्बुद Tatpur. n. (-दम्) An indolent swelling, the growth <BR>of which begins in the embryo and which is considered in<BR>curable. According to the native commentaries it is a he<BR>reditary disease and in so far always also द्विरर्बुद (q. v.), <BR>though the latter is distinct from it in some respects. E. <BR>अधि and अर्बुद; ‘an Arbuda or indolent swelling which <BR>reaches beyond (scil.) birth’, i. e. which takes place prior <BR>to birth.

अध्यवसान
अध्यवसान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) <BR>	1 Determining, ascertaining. <BR>	2 Effort, <BR>energy. <BR>	3 (In rhetoric.) The simple enunciation of elliptic <BR>or figurative speech without qualifying it by epithets &c., <BR>as it were, leaving it on its own effort; such sentences as <BR>श्वेतो धावति ‘the white (horse) gallops’, कुन्ताः प्रविशन्ति <BR>‘(men with) lances enter’ (see also under अजहत्स्वार्था), or <BR>कलिङ्गः साहसिकः ‘the (inhabitant of) Kalinga is impetuous’ <BR>(see also under जहत्स्वार्था) would be lakṣaṇās or elliptic <BR>expressions by अध्यवसान, while अश्वः श्वेतो धावति the <BR>white horse gallops, एते कुन्ताः प्रविशन्ति these (men with) <BR>lances enter, कलिङ्गः पुरुषो युध्यते the man (inhabitant of) <BR>Kalinga fights would be qualified or lakṣaṇās by आरोप <BR>q. v. (See also under लक्षणा.) Or मुखं द्वितीयश्चन्द्रः, (her) <BR>face is another moon, would be an अतिशयोक्ति (q. v.) or <BR>hyperbole in virtue of अध्यवसान, the comparison as it <BR>were resting on its own merit. E. सो with अव and अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अध्यवसाय
अध्यवसाय Tatpur. m. (-यः) <BR>	1 Ascertainment, determining. <BR>	2 As<BR>siduous application, effort, energy. <BR>	3 (In philosophy.) The <BR>specific function of बुद्धि or intellect (q. v.), apprehension <BR>by intellect, its taking hold of an object either by ascertain<BR>ment or volition. <BR>	4 (In rhetoric.) The same as अध्यवसान. <BR>E. सो with अव and अधि, kṛt aff. ण and āgama युक्.

अध्यवसायित
अध्यवसायित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Undertaken, at<BR>tempted as a difficult task. E. सो with अव and अधि, in <BR>the caus., kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्यवसायिन्
अध्यवसायिन् m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Resolute, determined. <BR>E. अध्यवसाय, taddh. aff. इनि.

अध्यवसित
अध्यवसित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Determined, as<BR>certained. <BR>	2 Apprehended by intellect. See अध्यवसाय. E. <BR>सो with अव and अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्यशन
अध्यशन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Eating too often, taking food <BR>before that previously eaten is digested. E. अधि and <BR>अशन.

अध्यस्त
अध्यस्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्तः-स्ता-स्तम्) <BR>	1 Placed over. <BR>	2 Sub<BR>stituted, supposed erroneously, misconceived: as a snake <BR>when that so perceived is actually a piece of rope. E. अस् <BR>with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्यस्थि
अध्यस्थि Tatpur. n. (-स्थि) A bone grown over another bone. <BR>E. अधि and अस्थि.

अध्यात्म
अध्यात्म I. Tatpur. n. (-त्मम्) The supreme soul or आत्मन् <BR>(q. v.), sometimes considered as identical with प्राण (q. v.) <BR>and, in the sectarian doctrine, especially with Nārāyaṇa <BR>or Viṣṇu. <BR>II. Avyayībh. (-त्मम्) Concerning or relating to soul, life <BR>&c.; see आत्मन्. A chapter in the Upan. treating thereon con<BR>tains the following subjects: the lower jaw, the upper jaw, <BR>speech and tongue; another passage comprises under this <BR>topic <BR>	1 the vital airs: prāṇa, apāna, vyāna, udāna, samāna, <BR>	2 the organs of sensation: eyes, ears, manas, speech, skin <BR>(tvach) and <BR>	3 the elementary parts of the body: skin (char<BR>man), flesh, tendons, bones, marrow. E. अधि and आत्मन्, <BR>samāsānta aff. टच्.

अध्यात्मज्ञान
अध्यात्मज्ञान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The knowledge of the supreme <BR>spirit or of the nature of ātman or soul. E. अध्यात्म (I. or <BR>II.) and ज्ञान.

अध्यात्मदृश्
अध्यात्मदृश् Tatpur. m. (-दृक्) A holy sage, one who knows <BR>the nature of or what concerns ātman or the soul. E. <BR>अध्यात्म (II.) and दृश्.

अध्यात्मरति
अध्यात्मरति Bahuvr. m. (-तिः) An anchorite, one who de<BR>lights in meditating on the nature of or what concerns <BR>ātman or the soul. E. अध्यात्म (II.) and रति.

अध्यात्मविद्
अध्यात्मविद् Tatpur. m. (-त्) One who knows the supreme <BR>spirit or the nature of ātman or soul. E. अध्यात्म (I. or II.) <BR>and विद्.

अध्यात्मविद्या
अध्यात्मविद्या Tatpur. f. (-द्या). The same as अध्यात्मज्ञान. <BR>E. अध्यात्म and विद्या.

अध्यात्मिक
अध्यात्मिक m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्). See आध्यात्मिक which is <BR>the more correct form of this word.

अध्यापक
अध्यापक Tatpur. m. (-कः) <BR>	1 A teacher, esp. one who instructs <BR>in the sacred books. <BR>	2 (According to a legend in the Calcutta <BR>edition of the Harivanśa.) One of the sixteen Ṛtvijs (q. v.) <BR>or priests, who was produced together with the Neṣṭṛ from <BR>the thighs of Purushottama. The reading of the commen<BR>tary, however, is अच्छावाक (q. v.) and the list of priests <BR>mentioned there is differently given in the manuscripts; अ- <BR>ध्यापक does not usually occur as the name of a Ṛtvij. (In <BR>the first meaning अध्यापक may be the latter part of Tatpur. <BR>compounds, the former of which stands in the sense of the <BR>genitive (f. i. ब्राह्मणाध्यापक one who instructs a Brāhmana) <BR>and as the latter part of several Karmadh. compounds; see <BR>f. i. कुमाराध्यापक, कठाध्यापक.) E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, in <BR>the caus., kṛt aff. ण्वुल्.

अध्यापकोदित
अध्यापकोदित Karmadh. m. (-तः) One who is called or spoken <BR>of as a teacher. E. अध्यापक and उदित.

अध्यापन
अध्यापन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Instructing, teaching the sacred <BR>books, one of the six duties of a Brahman. E. इ (इङ्) with <BR>अधि; in the caus., kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अध्यापयितृ
अध्यापयितृ Tatpur. m. (-ता). The same as अध्यापक 1. E. <BR>इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛt aff. तृच्.

अध्याप्य
अध्याप्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्यः-प्या-प्यम्) Fit to, capable of <BR>being instructed (esp. in the sacred writings). E. इ (इङ्) <BR>with अधि, in the caus., kṛtya aff. यत्.

अध्याय
अध्याय Tatpur. m. (-यः) I. <BR>	1 A section of a book (f. i. of the <BR>Ṛgveda, Yajurveda, Aitareyabrāhmaṇa, Pāniṇis grammar <BR>&c.). <BR>	2 Reading, studying. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्. <BR>II. One who reads or studies (in this sense only as the <BR>latter part of a compound; f. i. वेदाध्यायः one who reads <BR>the Veda). E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛt aff. अण्.

अध्यायिन्
अध्यायिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Reading, studying. <BR>E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛt aff. णिनि.

अध्यारूढ
अध्यारूढ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) <BR>	1 Mounted on, placed <BR>above; used either in an active or passive sense, person. or <BR>impersonally. <BR>	2 Exceeding, more (with a noun in the in<BR>strum.) <BR>	3 Inferior, less (with a noun in the ablative). E. रुह् <BR>with आ and अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्यारोप
अध्यारोप Tatpur. m. (-पः) Fixing in or upon, transferring; <BR>but more especially used in philosophy, in the sense of <BR>transferring or attributing erroneously the predicates, nature <BR>&c. of one object to another, as those of a serpent to those <BR>of a rope &c. See अध्यास. E. रुह्, in the caus., with आ <BR>and अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अध्यारोपन
अध्यारोपन Tatpur. n. (-नम्). The same as the preceding. <BR>E. रुह्, in the caus., with आ and अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अध्यारोपित
अध्यारोपित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Transferred or <BR>attributed erroneously. <BR>	2 Hyperbolical, exaggerated. E. रुह्, <BR>in the caus., with आ and अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्यावाप
अध्यावाप Tatpur. m. (-पः) Throwing or casting upon. E. <BR>वप् with आ and अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अध्यावाहन
अध्यावाहन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) A second calling, a second in<BR>vitation. See the following word of which it is the thema<BR>tic form. E. अधि and आवाहन.

अध्यावाहनिक
अध्यावाहनिक n. (-कम्) An item of a married woman's pro<BR>perty. See स्त्रीधन. It is explained as the gift she takes <BR>home from her father's house, when paying a visit to her <BR>friends. E. अध्यावाहन, taddh. aff. ठन्.

अध्यास
अध्यास Tatpur. m. (-सः) <BR>	1 Putting, throwing in or upon. <BR>	2 (In <BR>philosophy.) Transferring or attributing erroneously the <BR>predicates, nature &c. of one object to another, as of a ser<BR>pent to a rope &c. See अध्यारोप. <BR>	3 (In vaidik grammar.) <BR>The appendage to a vaidik verse; according to some the <BR>same as एकपदा q. v. E. अस्, to throw, in the caus., with <BR>अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अध्यासन
अध्यासन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) <BR>	1 Sitting on or upon. <BR>	2 Presiding over, <BR>ruling, inhabiting as chief. E. आस् with अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अध्यासयोग
अध्यासयोग Tatpur. m. (-गः) In Buddhistic doctrine, one of <BR>the 108 धर्मालोकमुख (q. v.), perhaps: excessive or profound <BR>meditation. E. अध्यास and योग.

अध्यासित
अध्यासित m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Seated in or on. <BR>	2 Presiding <BR>over. <BR>	3 Inhabited. E. आस्, in the caus., with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्यासिन्
अध्यासिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Sitting on or upon. <BR>E. आस् with अधि, kṛt aff. णिनि.

अध्याहरण
अध्याहरण Tatpur. n. (-णम्). The same as अध्याहार. E. हृ <BR>with आ and अधि, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अध्याहरणीय
अध्याहरणीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्). The same as <BR>अध्याहार्य q. v. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kṛtya aff. अनीयर्.

अध्याहर्तव्य
अध्याहर्तव्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्). The same as <BR>अध्याहार्य q. v. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kṛtya aff. तव्य.

अध्याहार
अध्याहार Tatpur. m. (-रः) <BR>	1 Adding a word or words to com<BR>plete a sentence, supplying an ellipsis. <BR>	2 Reasoning, discuss<BR>ing. See अध्याहरण. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kṛt aff. घञ्.

अध्याहार्य
अध्याहार्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्) <BR>	1 To be discussed or <BR>argued. <BR>	2 To be added in order to complete a sentence, to <BR>supply an ellipsis, as a word or words. E. हृ with आ and <BR>अधि, kṛtya aff. ण्यत्.

अध्याहृत
अध्याहृत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Discussed, argued. <BR>	2 Added to complete a sentence, to supply an ellipsis, as <BR>a word or words. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्युषित
अध्युषित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Inhabited. <BR>	2 Arrived <BR>at, obtained. (See समयाध्युषित.) E. वस् with अधि, kṛt <BR>aff. क्त and āgama इट्.

अध्युष्ट
अध्युष्ट Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Bound or tied over, coiled <BR>up. See the following. E. उच्छ् with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त.

अध्युष्टवलय
अध्युष्टवलय Bahuvr. m. (-यः) Having the ringlets coiled, <BR>wound into rings. This word occurs in the poem Ānanda<BR>laharī as the epithet of a serpent, to indicate that it is in <BR>profound sleep, forming, then, three ringlets and a half; <BR>the god Śiva is likened to a serpent coiled up in this man<BR>ner, its half ringlet being compared to his Śakti or female <BR>energy and the three others to the god as representing the <BR>Trimūrti. E. अध्युष्ट and वलय.

अध्युष्ट्र
अध्युष्ट्र Bahuvr. m. (-ष्ट्रः) A litter drawn or carried by a camel. <BR>E. अधि and उष्ट्र.

अध्यूढ
अध्यूढ Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) <BR>	1 Borne or placed over, <BR>elevated. <BR>	2 Very prosperous, thriving. <BR>	3 Much, excessive. <BR>II. m. (-ढः) A name of Śiva. <BR>III. f. (-ढा) A superseded wife, one whose husband has <BR>married others. E. वह् with अधि, kṛt aff. क्त. The com<BR>mentaries explain I. 2. as derived from अधि, in the sense <BR>of अधिक and ऊढ; II. as the god by whom the world has <BR>been upheld ‘first’ and III. also as derived from अधि, in <BR>the sense of ‘first’ and ऊढा married.

अध्यूध्नी
अध्यूध्नी Bahuvr. f. (-ध्नी) The penis (or according to another <BR>interpretation perhaps, the urethra). This word occurs esp. <BR>in the ritual works, in passages treating on the Agnisho<BR>mīyapaśu (q. v.) and the ceremonies connected with it. E. <BR>अधि and ऊधस्, samāsānta ādeśa अनङ् and fem. aff. ङीष्, <BR>scil. इडा; literally: the tubular vessel above the scrotum.

अध्यूषिताश्व
अध्यूषिताश्व Bahuvr. m. (-श्वः) The name of a prince, a <BR>descendant of Daśaratha. According to others his name <BR>would be अभ्युत्थिताश्व or दूषिताश्व or विधृति. E. अध्यू- <BR>षित (very diseased, from अधि and ऊषित) and अश्व.

अध्यूषिवस्
अध्यूषिवस् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-षिवान्-षुषी-षिवस्) Having in<BR>habited (in the sense of लुङ्, लङ् and लिट् qq. vv.). E. वस् <BR>with अधि, kṛt aff. क्वसु.

अध्यूहन
अध्यूहन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Covering over, esp. with ashes and <BR>coals. (Used principally in ritual works.) E. ऊह् with अधि, <BR>kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अध्येतव्य
अध्येतव्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्). The same as अ- <BR>ध्ययनीय. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛtya aff. तव्य.

अध्येतृ
अध्येतृ Tatpur. m. (-ता) A student, one who reads or studies. <BR>E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kṛt aff. तृच्.

अध्येय
अध्येय m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्). The same as अध्येतव्य. E. इ <BR>(इङ्) with अधि, kṛtya aff. यत्.

अध्येषण
अध्येषण Tatpur. f. n. (-णा-णम्) Solicitation, asking, request. <BR>E. इष् with अधि, kṛt aff. युच्.

अध्येष्यमाण
अध्येष्यमाण Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Parposing or be<BR>ginning to read, to study. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, in the <BR>future (ऌट्), kṛt aff. शानच् and āgama मुक्.

अध्रि
अध्रि Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ध्रिः-ध्रिः-ध्रि) (ved.) Unrestrained, <BR>irresistible. See the following. E. अ neg. and ध्रि.

अध्रिगु
अध्रिगु Bahuvr. m. (-गुः--n. pl. -गावः) (ved.) <BR>	1 Of un<BR>restrained or irresistible course; esp. as an epithet of Indra, <BR>Agni, Soma, the Rudras and the Aśvins. <BR>	2 The name of <BR>a heavenly śamitṛ (q. v.) or killer of the sacrificial animal. <BR>	3 The name of a Praishamantra (q. v.) used in the cere<BR>mony of the killing of the Agnīṣomīyapaśu (q. v.), and <BR>beginning with the words दैव्याः शमितार आरभध्वमुत म- <BR>नुष्या उपनयत मेध्याः &c. E. अध्रि and गो.

अध्रिज
अध्रिज Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) (ved.) Irresistible. E. <BR>doubtful; perhaps अ neg. and ध्रिज (from ध्रिज्).

अध्रिपुष्कलिका
अध्रिपुष्कलिका Bahuvr.(?) f. (-का) The name of a plant, a <BR>species of Nāgavalli (Piper betel). E. अध्रि and पुष्कलिका.

अध्रियमाण
अध्रियमाण Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) <BR>	1 Not held &c. <BR>See धृ. <BR>	2 (In law.) Not alive, not surviving. E. अ neg. <BR>and ध्रियमाण.

अध्रुव
अध्रुव Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) <BR>	1 Not permanent, not <BR>fixed, transient, perishable. <BR>	2 Uncertain, doubtful. <BR>	3 Not <BR>vital, not essential for life (as a limb or part of the body). <BR>E. अ neg. and ध्रुव.

अध्रुष
अध्रुष Tatpur.(?) m. (-षः) (In medicine.) A disease of the <BR>palate (see तालुरोग), described as ‘a hard swelling, of a <BR>red colour, produced by (diseased) blood and accompanied <BR>with pain and fever’. E. unknown.

अध्व
अध्व. See अध्वन्.

अध्वग
अध्वग Tatp. I. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Travelling, being on the road. <BR>II. m. (-गः) <BR>	1 A traveller. <BR>	2 A camel. <BR>	3 The sun. <BR>III. f. (-गा) <BR>	1 A traveller. <BR>	2 A name of the river Ganges. <BR>E. अध्वन् and ग.

अध्वगत्
अध्वगत् Tatpur. m. (-गत्) A traveller. E. अध्वन् and गत्.

अध्वगत्यन्त
अध्वगत्यन्त Tatpur. m. (-न्तः) The same as the following, of <BR>which it occurs as a various reading. E. अध्वन् and गति- <BR>अन्त (sc. क्रोश or योजन &c.).

अध्वगन्तव्य
अध्वगन्तव्य Karmadh. m. (-व्यः) Measure of distance, as a Krośa, <BR>a Yojana &c. E. अध्वन् and गन्तव्य; an irregular compound, <BR>instead of गन्तव्याध्वन्.

अध्वगभोग्य
अध्वगभोग्य Tatpur. m. (-ग्यः) The name of a tree (Spondias <BR>mangifera). See आम्रात. E. अध्वग and भोग्य; lit. ‘to be <BR>enjoyed by travellers’.

अध्वगमन
अध्वगमन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Journeying, travelling. E. अध्वन् <BR>and गमन.

अध्वगामिन्
अध्वगामिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि) Travelling. E. <BR>अध्वन् and गामिन्.

अध्वजा
अध्वजा Tatpur. f. (-जा) The name of a plant. See स्वर्णुली. <BR>E. अध्वन् and ज.

अध्वन्
अध्वन् m. (-ध्वा) <BR>	1 Sky, atmosphere (only in the Vedas). <BR>	2 A road. <BR>	3 Time. <BR>	4 A place (perhaps, a place where four <BR>roads meet). <BR>	5 A branch or school of the Vedas or sacred <BR>literature.--In some Tatpurusha compounds the former <BR>part of which is an उपसर्ग (q. v.), this word occurs in the <BR>form of अध्व; i. e. the compound assumes the samāsānta <BR>aff. अच्; e. g. प्राध्व, निरध्व, प्रत्यध्व.--(The two last <BR>meanings of this word are rather unsettled through the <BR>variety of readings in the native dictionaries from which <BR>they are taken; some read अध्वा…संस्थाने स्यादवस्कन्धे, <BR>others संस्थाने साश्रवस्कन्धे; the best reading, however, that <BR>which has been adopted in the present translation, seems <BR>to be this: संस्थाने शास्त्रवत्स्कन्धे.) E. doubtful; according <BR>to some, अद्, uṇ. aff. क्वनिप्, with ध् substituted for द् <BR>‘because it eats up the strength of the traveller’; or ac<BR>cording to others, अत्, uṇ. aff. क्वनिप्, with ध् instead of त्.

अध्वनीन
अध्वनीन m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) <BR>	1 Marching fast or fleet. <BR>	2 (m.) A <BR>traveller. E. अध्वन्, taddh. aff. ख. According to some used <BR>in all the three genders.

अध्वन्य
अध्वन्य m. f. n. (-न्यः-न्या-न्यम्) <BR>	1 Marching fast or fleet. <BR>	2 (m.) A <BR>traveller. E. अध्वन्, taddh. aff. यत्. According to some <BR>used in all the three genders.

अध्वपति
अध्वपति Tatpur. m. (-तिः) An epithet of the sun, in the <BR>Vedas. Literally: ‘the lord of the roads’ or perhaps better <BR>‘the lord of the atmosphere’. E. अध्वन् and पति.

अध्वर
अध्वर Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) <BR>	1 Not crooked, <BR>honest proper (ved.) <BR>	2 Not perishable, lasting (in its con<BR>sequences, as a sacrifice; ved.). <BR>	3 Intent, attentive. (It is <BR>doubtful whether this word in the two meanings ‘not crook<BR>ed’ and ‘not perishable’, occurs in the femin. gender, as <BR>it is used in the Vedas either absolutely as a neuter or as <BR>epithet of यज्ञ in the mascul. Nor is the latter meaning <BR>‘intent, attentive’, a usual one, though it is given in <BR>several of the native dictionaries.) <BR>II. m. (-रः) <BR>	1 Sacrifice in general, but in the ritual works <BR>mostly used as the denomination of the greater sacrifices <BR>or those performed with the juice of the Soma plant; see <BR>also सौम्याध्वर and अध्वरकाण्ड. <BR>	2 The name of a Vasu <BR>(q. v.). <BR>	3 The proper name of the chief of a renowned fa<BR>mily. See आध्वरायण. <BR>III. n. (-रम्) Sky, atmosphere (ved.). E. अ priv. and <BR>ध्वर ‘having no crookedness, dishonesty &c.’ or according <BR>to others ‘preventing, not allowing of injury’; another <BR>etym. makes this word, but erroneously, a Tatpur. from <BR>अध्वन् and र ‘giving or affording the road (scil. to heaven)’.

अध्वरकर्मन्
अध्वरकर्मन् Tatpur. n. (-र्मः) The proceedings with an <BR>Adhwara-sacrifice (ved.). See the preceding. E. अध्वर <BR>and कर्मन्.

अध्वरकल्पा
अध्वरकल्पा Tatpur. f. (-ल्पा) One of the Kāmyeṣṭis (q. v.) <BR>or voluntary iṣṭis with three yāgas (q. v.) in the morning, <BR>in the middle of the day and in the evening, which may <BR>be instituted by a man of either of the three first classes. <BR>E. अध्वर and कल्प.

अध्वरकाण्ड
अध्वरकाण्ड Tatpur. n. (-ण्डम्) The book on the Adhwaras; <BR>the name of the third book of the Śatapaṭhabrāhmaṇa <BR>(q. v.) which treats on the Adhwaras or the greater sa<BR>crifices performed especially with the juice of the Soma <BR>plant, the Agniṣṭoma &c. E. अध्वर and काण्ड.

अध्वरकृत्
अध्वरकृत् Tatpur. m. (-त्) Making an Adhwara-sacrifice; <BR>also used as a vaidik epithet of स्प्य (q. v.) in the sense of <BR>‘instrumental for the performing of the sacrifice’. E. अध्वर <BR>and कृत्.

अध्वरग
अध्वरग Tatpur. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Belonging or appro<BR>priated to an Adhwara-sacrifice, as the Soma. E. अध्वर and ग.

अध्वरथ
अध्वरथ Tatpur. m. (-थः) A travelling carriage or cart. E. <BR>अध्वन् and रथ.

अध्वरदीक्षणीया
अध्वरदीक्षणीया Tatpur. f. (-या) That part of an Adhwara-sacri<BR>fice which is called दीक्षणीया q. v. E. अध्वर and दीक्षणीया.

अध्वरप्रायश्चित्ति
अध्वरप्रायश्चित्ति Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) The penance connected <BR>with an Adhwara-sacrifice. E. अध्वर and प्रायश्चित्ति.

अध्वरयु
अध्वरयु Tatpur. m. (-युः) Joining or performing the sacrifice. <BR>This word occurs as a grammatical explanation of अध्वर्यु <BR>q. v. E. अध्वर and यु.

अध्वरश्री
अध्वरश्री Tatpur. m. (-श्रीः) (ved.) Serving or honouring <BR>the sacrifice, an epithet of Agni, the Aśvins, the Maruts. <BR>E. अध्वर and श्री (serving).

अध्वरसमिष्टयजुस्
अध्वरसमिष्टयजुस् Tatpur. n. (-जुः) The offerings called स- <BR>मिष्टयजुस् q. v., connected with the Adhwara-sacrifice. E. <BR>अध्वर and समिष्टयजुस्.

अध्वरस्थ
अध्वरस्थ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) Standing for an <BR>Adhwara-sacrifice. E. अध्वर and स्थ.

अध्वरीय्
अध्वरीय् denom. par. (अध्वरीयति) To be desirous of having <BR>a sacrifice instituted for one's self. (ved.) Comp. अध्वर्य्. <BR>E. अध्वर, denom. aff. क्यच्.

अध्वरेष्ठा
अध्वरेष्ठा Tatpur. m. (-ष्ठाः) (ved.) Engaged in a sacrifice. E. <BR>अध्वर (in the locative) and स्था.

अध्वर्य्
अध्वर्य् denom. par. (अध्वर्यति) To be desirous of having a sa<BR>crifice instituted for one's self (used in this sense in the Rig<BR>veda). Comp. अध्वरीय्. E. अध्वर, denom. aff. व्यच् with <BR>elision of the final vowel.

अध्वर्यु
अध्वर्यु m. (-र्युः) <BR>	1 One desirous of having a sacrifice insti<BR>tuted for one's self (used in this sense in the Rigveda). <BR>	2 A <BR>priest in general (ved.) <BR>	3 (In the ritual and the epic litera<BR>ture.) A special priest, one conversant with and performing <BR>the ritual observances connected with the Yajurveda; he is <BR>one of the sixteen Ṛtvijs required for the performing of the <BR>great Soma sacrifices (see ऋत्विज्) and, amongst them, <BR>one of the four leading priests (see besides ब्रह्मन्, उद्गातृ <BR>and होतृ) who receive the whole dakṣiṇā (q. v.); his pu<BR>rushas or assistant priests are the प्रतिप्रस्थातृ, नेष्ट्ट and <BR>उन्नेतृ who are called, like himself, the दीक्षयितृ (q. v.) because <BR>they initiate, viz. the अध्वर्यु the three other leading priests, <BR>the प्रतिप्रस्थातृ the अर्धिन्- (q. v.), the नेष्टृ the तृतीयिन्- <BR>(q. v.) and the उन्नेतृ the पादिन्- (q. v.) priests. The Mi<BR>mānsā decides in doubtful cases, viz. whenever a sacrifice <BR>mentioned in and making part of the ritual of the Yajur<BR>veda, is mentioned also and forms part of another Veda, <BR>whether the Adhwaryu has another priest to share in <BR>his functions or whether he has to abstain from the pro<BR>ceedings altogether. The ten चमसाध्वर्यु (q. v.), who, <BR>are also assistants or purushas of the Adhwaryu, are dis<BR>tinct from and do not bear the name of Ṛtvij.--According <BR>to a legend in the Harivanśa, Nārāyaṇa created the first <BR>Adhwaryu from his arms. The dual अध्वर्यु is the collective <BR>denomination of the अध्वर्यु and प्रतिप्रस्थातृ, his principal <BR>assistant; the plur. अध्वर्यवः of the अध्वर्यु and his three <BR>assistants, and in general of those devoted to the study or <BR>the practice of the Yajurveda. <BR>	4 The Yajurveda (also in the <BR>plur. अध्वर्यवः). E. अध्वर्य्, kṛt aff. उ.

अध्वर्युकाण्ड
अध्वर्युकाण्ड Tatpur. n. (-ण्डम्) A collection of mantras or <BR>prayers for the special use of the Adhwaryu (q. v.). Also <BR>called आध्वर्यवकाण्ड. E. अध्वर्यु and काण्ड.

अध्वर्युक्रतु
अध्वर्युक्रतु Tatpur. m. (-तुः) The Kratu (q. v.)--sacri<BR>fices contained in the Yajurveda or to be performed by <BR>the Adhwaryu. E. अध्वर्यु (in the meanings of 3. or 2.) <BR>and क्रतु.

अध्वर्युवेद
अध्वर्युवेद Karmadh. or Tatpur. m. (-दः) The Yajurveda. <BR>E. अध्वर्यु (in the meanings of 4. or 3.) and वेद.

अध्वशल्य
अध्वशल्य Tatpur. m. (-ल्यः) A tree (Achyranthes aspera). See <BR>अपामार्ग. E. अध्वन् and शल्य.

अध्वस्मन्
अध्वस्मन् Bahuvr. m. (f.?) n. (-स्मा-म) (ved.) <BR>	1 Not perishing, <BR>not falling, everlasting. <BR>	2 Not causing to perish or to fall. <BR>E. अ priv. and ध्वस्मन्.

अध्वान्त
अध्वान्त Tatpur. n. (-न्तम्) Gloom, twilight. E. अ neg. and <BR>ध्वान्त.

अध्वान्तशात्रव
अध्वान्तशात्रव Tatpur. m. (-वः) A plant (Bignonia Indica). <BR>See पत्रोर्ण and श्योनाक. E. अध्वान्त and शात्रव, blossoming <BR>in the shade.

अन्
I. अन्. See अ III.

अन्
II. अन्. Considered as a substitute of इद् in इदम् in some <BR>cases, viz. अनेन, अनया and अनयोः. See इदम् and अन.

अन्
III. अन् I. (अन-अदादि-रुदादि-उदात्त-परस्मैपदिन्) r. 2d cl. <BR>par. (अनिति- imp. आनीत् or आनत्-आन-अनिता-अनिष्यति- <BR>आनीत्.--Desid. अनिनिषति.--Caus. आनयति) and <BR>II. (अन-दिवादि-उदात्त-अनुदात्तेत्) r. 4th cl. ātm. (अ- <BR>न्यते &c.) Also read अण् q. v. <BR>	1 To breathe, to live. <BR>	2 (ved.) <BR>To go. (In composition with परा and प्र, the न् of the <BR>radical is changed to ण्.) With अप- To breathe away (in <BR>farting), to produce the action of the vital air अपान (q. v.); <BR>अभ्यप- The same (अभि implying moreover the direction <BR>towards); अव- To breathe out, to breathe forth; उद्- <BR>To breathe up, to produce the action of the vital air उदान <BR>(q. v.); अभ्युद्- The same (अभि implying also the direction <BR>towards); परा-(पराणिति-पराणिणत्-पराणिणिषति)(?); <BR>परि-(पर्यनिति)(?); प्र- (प्राणिति. Des. प्राणिणिषति.) <BR>	1 To <BR>breathe, to respire, to produce the action of the vital air <BR>प्राण q. v. <BR>	2 To live. <BR>	3 (In the Upanishads, but doubtful.) <BR>To smell (see also प्राण and अतिग्रह). Caus. (प्राणयति- <BR>प्राणिणत्) To revive; अनुप्र- To breathe or to live in con<BR>formity with (a following noun depends upon it in the ac<BR>cusative); अभिप्र- To breathe into, to make one's breath <BR>enter into (the mouth of another); वि- To breathe, to pro<BR>duce the action of the vital air व्यान (q. v.); अभिवि- The <BR>same with the meaning of ‘towards’; सम्- <BR>	1 To breathe, <BR>to live. <BR>	2 To produce the action of the vital air समान (q. v.).

अन
I. अन ind. Not. E. g. अनोपमा ते बुद्धिः, explained by a <BR>commentator: ‘thy intellect is unequalled’. See also अना, <BR>and comp. अनानुकृत्य, अनानुद &c.

अन
II. अन. Considered by some as a substitute of इदम् in some <BR>cases; viz. अनेन, अनया and अनयोः. See इदम् and अन्.

अन
III. अन m. (-नः) Spiration; it is explained as the action <BR>which is common to the five vital airs प्राण, अपान, उदान, <BR>व्यान and समान (qq. vv.). Compare अनिल. E. अन्, kṛt <BR>aff. अच्.

अनंश
अनंश Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) <BR>	1 Portionless, not en<BR>titled to a share or portion. <BR>	2 (In law.) One excluded from <BR>participation in an inheritance viz. a eunuch, a degraded <BR>man, a blind or deaf person, a fool, an idiot, a dumb <BR>person or one deprived of one of his limbs or senses, a <BR>cripple &c. See also अनंशिन् and निरंशक.

अनंशत्व
अनंशत्व n. (-त्वम्) (In law.) The not being entitled to a <BR>share &c. See the preceding. Also अनंशता f. (-ता). E. <BR>अनंश, taddh. aff. त्व or तल्.

अनंशिन्
अनंशिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शी-शिनी-शि). The same as अ- <BR>नंश q. v. E. अ neg. and अंशिन्.

अनंशित्व
अनंशित्व n. (-त्वम्) or अनंशिता f. (-ता). The same as अनं- <BR>शत्व. E. अनंशिन्, taddh. aff. त्व or तल्.

अनंशुमत्फला
अनंशुमत्फला Tatpur. f. (-ला) A plantain (Musa paradisiaca). <BR>See अंशुमत्फला and कदली. E. अ compar.(?) and अंशु- <BR>मत्फला.

अनक
अनक m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Inferior, low. See अणक of <BR>which it is given as a various reading. E. See that of <BR>अणक; another is that from अण (अण् to sound, kṛt aff. <BR>अच्) and the taddh. aff. of depreciation कन्.

अनकदुन्दुभ
अनकदुन्दुभ Bahuvr. m. (-भः) The name of the father of Va<BR>sudeva. E. अनक and दुन्दुभ. (This word is doubtful and <BR>perhaps formed only by the commentaries, to explain the <BR>patronymic आनकदुन्दुभि q. v. See also the following.)

अनकदुन्दुभि
अनकदुन्दुभि Bahuvr. m. (-भिः) A name of Vasudeva, the <BR>father of Kṛṣṇa. More usually written आनकदुन्दुभि, <BR>but given also with the short initial by some commentators <BR>of the Amarakosha. E. अनक (instead of आनक) and दुन्दु- <BR>भि ‘because the gods beat the Anaka-drums in his house <BR>when Kṛṣṇa was born’.

अनकस्मात्
अनकस्मात् Tatpur. ind. <BR>	1 Not without a cause. <BR>	2 Not im<BR>mediately, not instantly. <BR>	3 Not suddenly, not at once. E. <BR>अ neg. and अकस्मात्.

अनक्ष्
अनक्ष् Bahuvr. m. (-नक्) (ved.) Blind. E. अ priv. and अक्ष् <BR>(from the denomin. of अक्षि, with kṛt aff. क्विप्).

अनक्ष
अनक्ष Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षी-क्षम्) Eyeless, blind. E. <BR>अ priv. and अक्षि, samāsānta aff. षच्.

अनक्षर
अनक्षर Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Containing, utter<BR>ing &c. what is blamable or what aught not to be said. <BR>II. n. (-रम्) Blamable or improper speech. E. अ deter. <BR>and अक्षर.

अनक्षि
अनक्षि Tatpur. n. (-क्षि) A bad or disfigured eye. E. अ neg. <BR>and अक्षि.

अनगार
अनगार Bahuvr. m. (-रः) An anchorite, a man who has re<BR>tired from the world. See अग्रह. E. अ priv. and अगार <BR>‘having no house i. e. living in the wood’.

अनगारिका
अनगारिका f. (-का) A wandering life, the life of a men<BR>dicant. E. अनगार, taddh. aff. ठच्(?); scil. वृत्ति.

अनग्न
अनग्न Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्नः-ग्ना-ग्नम्) Not naked. E. अ neg. <BR>and नग्न.

अनग्नता
अनग्नता f. (-ता) The not being naked. E. The former, taddh. <BR>aff. तल्.

अनग्नि
अनग्नि I. Tatpur. m. (-ग्निः) Any thing not or different from <BR>fire. E. अ neg. and अग्नि. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ग्निः-ग्निः-ग्नि) <BR>	1 Having no sacrificial <BR>fire or being deprived of the arrangement of a sacrificial <BR>fire place (see अग्निचयन), as a sacrifice. <BR>	2 Impious, irre<BR>ligious (as one not performing the observances which require <BR>a sacrificial fire; also an epithet of the Manes अग्निष्वात्त <BR>q. v.). <BR>	3 Unmarried(?). <BR>	4 Having no domestic fire, no fire <BR>for worldly purposes (as an anchorite who has given up <BR>his house and retired to the wood). <BR>	5 Having a bad di<BR>gestion. E. अ priv. or (in 5.) deterior. and अग्नि.

अनग्नित्र
अनग्नित्र Tatpur. m. f. (-त्रः-त्रा) (ved.) <BR>	1 Not having Agni <BR>or the divinity of fire as protector, unprotected by Agni. <BR>Or according to another interpretation, <BR>	2 not maintain<BR>ing a sacrificial fire, impious, wicked. E. अ neg. and <BR>अग्नि-त्र.

अनग्निदग्ध
अनग्निदग्ध Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ग्धः-ग्धा-ग्धम्) <BR>	1 Not burnt <BR>in or with fire. <BR>	2 Not burnt on the funeral pyre, not hav<BR>ing received the obsequies in conformity with the religious <BR>rites. <BR>II. m. pl. (-ग्धाः) The name of a particular class of Pi<BR>tṛs or Manes, of those apparently who when alive did <BR>not observe religious rites. See अग्निदग्ध and the following. <BR>E. अ neg. and अग्निदग्ध.

अनग्निष्वात्त
अनग्निष्वात्त Tatpur. m. pl. (-त्ताः) The name of a particular <BR>class of Pitṛs or Manes. This word is explained by a <BR>commentator of the Yajurveda: ‘not tasted by (स्वात्त) i. e. <BR>not burnt by fire, not having received the obsequies in con<BR>formity with the religious rites’ and it appears therefore as <BR>a synonyme of अनग्निदग्ध, as well as the converse of अग्नि- <BR>ष्वात्त which, according to the same commentator, would <BR>be a synonyme of अग्निदग्ध. Anagniṣvātta does not occur <BR>in the list of the Pitṛs which are given in the law books <BR>and in the Purāṇas, while अग्निदग्ध and अग्निष्वात्त (qq. vv.) <BR>are named there as distinct classes and explained in a <BR>different manner. The etymology given, which identifies <BR>स्वात्त and स्वादित, seems moreover objectionable. E. अ <BR>and अग्निष्वात्त.

अनघ
अनघ Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-घः-घा-घम्) <BR>	1 Sinless, pure. <BR>	2 Clean, clear. <BR>	3 Handsome, pleasing. <BR>II. m. (-घः) <BR>	1 A name of Śiva. <BR>	2 The name of a Gan<BR>dharva. <BR>	3 The name of a Sādhya. <BR>	4 The name of a prince, <BR>son of Surodha and Upadānavī. <BR>	5 The name of a son of <BR>Vasiṣṭha and Ūrjā. <BR>	6 White mustard; see गौरसर्षप. A <BR>less correct reading of this word in the latter sense is अ- <BR>नद्य. E. अ priv. and अघ.

अनङ्कुश
अनङ्कुश Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Unruly, licentious. <BR>E. अ priv. and अङ्कुश.

अनङ्ग
अनङ्ग I. Tatpur. n. (-ङ्गम्) What is different from or other <BR>than the अङ्ग q. v. E. अ neg. and अङ्ग. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-ङ्गः-ङ्गा-ङ्गम्) Bodiless, in<BR>corporeal. <BR>2. m. (-ङ्गः) A name of Kāma, the god of Love; so <BR>called, ‘because he was reduced to ashes, by the eye <BR>of Śiva, for having disturbed his devotions and rendered <BR>him enamoured of Pārvatī’. <BR>3. n. (-ङ्गम्) <BR>	1 Sky, æther. <BR>	2 The same as मनस् q. v. <BR>E. अ priv. and अङ्ग.

अनङ्गक
अनङ्गक Bahuvr. n. (-कम्). The same as मनस् q. v. E. अ <BR>priv. and अङ्ग, samāsānta aff. कप्. See अनङ्ग II. 3. 2.; or <BR>अनङ्ग, taddh. aff. कन्.

अनङ्गक्रीडा
अनङ्गक्रीडा Tatpur. f. (-डा) A metre regulated by quantity; <BR>it is a species of the द्विच्छन्दिक (q. v.) and consists of a <BR>couplet with sixteen long syllables in the first and thirty <BR>two short syllables in the second verse. Also called सौ- <BR>म्या. E. अनङ्ग and क्रीडा.

अनङ्गदेवी
अनङ्गदेवी Tatpur. f. (-वी) The proper name of a wife of <BR>Mahlaṇa, a king of Kashmir. E. अनङ्ग and देवी.

अनङ्गपाल
अनङ्गपाल Tatpur. m. (-लः) The proper name of a chamber<BR>lain of Ananta, king of Kashmir. E. अनङ्ग and पाल.

अनङ्गमेजय
अनङ्गमेजय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not shaking <BR>the body. E. अ neg. and अङ्गमेजय (अङ्ग and एज् caus., <BR>kṛt aff. खश्).

अनङ्गलेखा
अनङ्गलेखा Tatpur. f. (-खा) A proper name: the daughter <BR>of Balāditya, a king of Kashmir, and wife of Durlaba<BR>vardhana, his successor. E. अनङ्ग and लेखा.

अनङ्गशेखर
अनङ्गशेखर Tatpur. m. (-रः) The name of a metre regulated <BR>by number and quantity, a species of the class Danḍaka <BR>(q. v.) and consisting of four verses with fifteen Iambi in <BR>each verse. E. अनङ्ग and शेखर.

अनङ्गसेना
अनङ्गसेना Tatpur. f. (-ना) The proper name of a courtesan <BR>in a drama. E. अनङ्ग and सेना.

अनङ्गापीड
अनङ्गापीड Tatpur. m. (-डः) The proper name of a king of <BR>Kashmir, the sixteenth king of the dynasty of Karkota. <BR>E. अनङ्ग and आपीड.

अनङ्गासुहृद्
अनङ्गासुहृद् Tatpur. m. (-हृत्) A name of Śiva. E. अनङ्ग <BR>and असुहृद् ‘the foe of Kāma’; see अनङ्ग.

अनच्छ
अनच्छ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-च्छः-च्छा-च्छम्) Turbid, muddy. E. <BR>अ neg. and अच्छ.

अनजका
अनजका Tatpur. f. (-का) A bad or miserable young female <BR>goat. Also अनजिका. E. अ deter. and अजका.

अनजिका
अनजिका Tatpur. f. (-का). See the preceding. E. अ deter. <BR>and अजिका.

अनञ्जन
अनञ्जन Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Free from colly<BR>rium &c. See the meanings of अञ्जन. <BR>II. n. (-नम्) Æther, atmosphere. E. अ priv. and अञ्जन.

अनडुज्जिह्वा
अनडुज्जिह्वा Tatpur. f. (-ह्वा) The name of a plant (Ele<BR>phantopus scaber). See गोजिह्वा. E. अनडुह् and जिह्वा.

अनडुत्क
अनडुत्क m. f. n. (-त्कः-त्का-त्कम्) Having bulls or oxen <BR>(<BR>	1 as a country (according to others the reading would then <BR>be आनडुहक q. v., from आनडुह); <BR>	2 seemingly the latter <BR>part of the thematic form of a Bahuvrīhi compound, con<BR>cluding with अनडुह्, f. i. प्रियानडुत्क). E. अनडुह्, <BR>	1 taddh. <BR>aff. क, <BR>	2 the compound with samāsānta aff. कप्.

अनडुद्द
अनडुद्द Tatpur. m. (-द्दः) The donor of a bull or ox. E. <BR>अनडुह् and द.

अनडुह्
अनडुह् Tatpur. m. (sing. -ड्वान्, -ड्वन्, -ड्वाहम्, -डुहा, -डुहे, <BR>-डुहः, -डुहि; du. -ड्वाहौ, -डुद्भ्याम्, -डुहोः; plur. -ड्वाहः, <BR>-डुहः, -डुद्भिः, -डुद्भ्यः, -डुत्सु) f. (-डुही or -ड्वाही) <BR>	1 A bull <BR>or ox, especially one fit to draw a cart or to bear a weight. <BR>	2 The sign of the zodiac, Taurus. <BR>	3 (According to a vaidik <BR>commentator also used in the adjective sense:) fit or able <BR>to draw a cart, as an epithet of a goat; but this expla<BR>nation seems doubtful.--(The use of the femin. अनड्वाही <BR>would be restricted, according to one authority, to the <BR>Vedas, while others do not make any distinction between <BR>this form and अनडुही. In Avyayībh. compounds, the com<BR>pound terminating with अनडुह् assumes the samāsānta aff. <BR>टच् (see अनडुह) and in Bahuvr. compounds, the samā<BR>sānta aff. कप् (see अनडुत्क); in the latter, however, it <BR>may also retain its original form, with the following de<BR>clension in the neuter: sing. अनडुत्, du. अनडुही and plur. <BR>अनड्वांहि.) E. अनस्, with स् changed to ड्, and वह् (from <BR>वह्, kṛt aff. क्विप्) with samprasāraṇa of व्; in the fem. <BR>with aff. ङीष्.

अनडुह
अनडुह I. m. (-हः) The proper name of the chief of a gotra <BR>or family. See आनडुह्य. E. अनडुह्, taddh. aff. अच्(?). <BR>II. Seemingly the latter part of the thematic form of an <BR>Avyayībh. compound concluding with अनडुह्, f. i. प्रत्यनडुहम्; <BR>such a compound assuming the samāsānta aff. टच्.

अनडुही
अनडुही Tatpur. f. (-ही) A cow. Also अनड्वाही. E. See <BR>अनडुह्.

अनड्वाही
अनड्वाही Tatpur. f. (-ही) A cow. Also अनडुही. E. See <BR>अनडुह्.

अनणु
अनणु Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-णुः-णुः or -ण्वी-णु) Not minute, <BR>not atomic, coarse (the reverse of अणु or अस्थूल). <BR>II. m. (-णुः) Coarse grain, as chiches (Cicer arietinum) <BR>&c. or, according to others, as wheat, barley &c.; (the <BR>reverse of अणु q. v.). E. अ neg. and अणु.

अनत
अनत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Erect, not bowed <BR>down, stiff. <BR>	2 Proud, haughty. E. अ neg. and नत.

अनतिक्रम
अनतिक्रम Tatpur. m. (-मः) <BR>	1 Not overstepping certain limits, <BR>not surpassing certain qualities &c., moderation. <BR>	2 Pro<BR>priety, decorum. E. अ neg. and अतिक्रम.

अनतिक्रमणीय
अनतिक्रमणीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not to be sur<BR>passed, overstepped or transgressed, inviolable, inevitable, <BR>unavoidable. E. अ neg. and अतिक्रमणीय.

अनतिक्रान्त
अनतिक्रान्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) <BR>	1 Unsurpassed, <BR>unexceeded. <BR>	2 Untransgressed &c. See अतिक्रान्त. E. अ <BR>neg. and अतिक्रान्त.

अनतिदृश्य
अनतिदृश्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्) (ved.) Not pellucid, <BR>untransparent. E. अ and अतिदृश्य (from दृश् with अति, <BR>kṛtya aff. यत्); but more probably, ‘very invisible, very <BR>indiscernible’ from अ neg. and अति-दृश्य, instead of अत्य- <BR>दृश्य. A similar transposition occurs in the vaidik word <BR>अनत्युद्य.

अनतिद्भुत
अनतिद्भुत Tatpur. m. (-तः) (ved.) Not surpassed, not ex<BR>celled. E. अ neg. and अतिद्भुत; the latter part of the com<BR>pound apparently being a synonyme of अतिभूत and re<BR>sembling, as regards its formation, the word अद्भुत (q. v.).

अनतिप्रश्न्य
अनतिप्रश्न्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्न्यः-श्न्या-श्न्यम्) Not belonging <BR>or referring to a question which goes beyond its proper <BR>bounds, to a question concerning a transcendental object. <BR>E. अ neg. and अतिप्रश्न्य.

अनतिप्रौढ
अनतिप्रौढ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) Not full-grown, <BR>young (as a plant &c.). E. अ neg. and अति-प्रौढ.

अनतिरिक्त
अनतिरिक्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) Not exceeded in <BR>quantity or quality. E. अ neg. and अतिरिक्त.

अनतिविलम्बिन्
अनतिविलम्बिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-म्बी-म्बिनी-म्बि) Not very <BR>dilatory, not very slow. E. अ neg. and अतिविलम्बिन्.

अनतिवृत्ति
अनतिवृत्ति Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) Not going beyond, the being in <BR>conformity or in proportion with. See पदार्थानतिवृत्ति. E. <BR>अ neg. and अतिवृत्ति.

अनत्यन्तगति
अनत्यन्तगति Tatpur. f. (-तिः) (In grammar.) The sense of <BR>‘not completely’, ‘not very much’, the sense of diminu<BR>tiveness. E. अ neg. अत्यन्त and गति. See अत्यन्तगति.

अनत्यय
अनत्यय Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Having no loss, no <BR>end &c., eternal, continual. See the meanings of अत्यय. <BR>E. अ priv. and अत्यय.

अनत्युद्य
अनत्युद्य Tatpur. m. (-द्यः) (ved.) Utterly unnameable, quite <BR>unfit to be spoken of. E. अ neg. and अति-उद्य; as it ap<BR>pears, a transposition of अत्यनुद्य, similar to that which <BR>has probably taken place in अनतिदृश्य (q. v.).

अनदत्
अनदत् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-दन्-दती-दत्) Not eating. E. अ <BR>neg. and अदत् I.

अनद्धा
अनद्धा Tatpur. ind. (ved.) Not clearly, not truly, perhaps. <BR>Also with the particles उ and इव, अनद्धो and अनद्धेव. E. अ <BR>neg. and अद्धा.

अनद्धापुरुष
अनद्धापुरुष Tatpur. m. (-षः) (ved.) No man in the true sense <BR>of the word, ‘one who does not serve the ends of the gods, <BR>of the pitṛs, or of men’. E. अनद्धा and पुरुष.

अनद्य
अनद्य Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) Not fit to be eaten. <BR>II. m. (-द्यः) White mustard. See अनघ which is the more <BR>correct reading of this word. E. अ neg. and अद्य.

अनद्यतन
अनद्यतन Bahuvr. m. (-नः) (In grammar.) The time which <BR>does not belong to the current day. See अद्यतन. It is either <BR>भूतानद्यतनः the past or भविष्यदनद्यतनः the future time, if <BR>such a period does not include the current day. E. अ priv. <BR>and अद्यतन, sc. काल.

अनधिकार
अनधिकार Tatpur. m. (-रः) Absence of right, claim, in<BR>terest or concern. E. अ neg. and अधिकार.

अनधिकारचर्चा
अनधिकारचर्चा Tatpur. f. (-र्चा) Officiousness, meddling with <BR>other people's business. E. अनधिकार and चर्चा.

अनधिकारिन्
अनधिकारिन् Tatpur. m. (-री) One who has no right or <BR>claim &c. See the meanings of अधिकारिन्. E. अ neg. <BR>and अधिकारिन्.

अनधिकृत
अनधिकृत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not set over, or <BR>appointed &c. See the meanings of अधिकृत. E. अ neg. <BR>and अधिकृत.

अनधिगत
अनधिगत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Not acquired. <BR>	2 Not <BR>learnt or studied. E. अ neg. and अधिगत.

अनधीनक
अनधीनक m. f. n. (-नकः-निका-नकम्) Independant. E. अ- <BR>अधीन, taddh. aff. कन्.

अनध्यक्ष
अनध्यक्ष m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) I. Tatpur. Imperceptible, <BR>unperceived, absent. See अप्रत्यक्ष. E. अ neg. and अध्यक्ष. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Having no superintendent. E. अ priv. and <BR>अध्यक्ष.

अनध्ययन
अनध्ययन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Want or intermission of reading <BR>or study, especially of the Vedas. E. अ neg. and अध्ययन.

अनध्याय
अनध्याय Bahuvr. m. (-यः) Time on which it is improper <BR>and forbidden to read or to study the Vedas; also used in <BR>the sense of ‘a holy-day’ or ‘vacation’. E. अ priv. and <BR>अध्याय, sc. काल.

अनध्यायदिवस
अनध्यायदिवस Karmadh. m. (-सः) A day on which it is <BR>improper to study. See the preceding. E. अनध्याय and <BR>दिवस.

अनन
अनन n. (-नम्) Breathing, living. E. अन्, kṛt aff. ल्युट्.

अननङ्गमेजय
अननङ्गमेजय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not allowing the body <BR>to remain unshaken or quiet. E. अ neg. and अनङ्गमेजय.

अननुभाषण
अननुभाषण Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (In the Nyāya philosophy.) <BR>Not repeating the argument for discussion, i. e. a tacit <BR>agreement with it or assent to the assertion of the person <BR>who has proposed it; viz. if, after the argument for dis<BR>cussion has been announced, it has not been repeated by <BR>any one--the sign of taking it up--the proposer has to <BR>proclaim it three times; if then it does not meet with the <BR>anubhāṣana, it is considered as proved or as accepted as <BR>such. E. अ neg. and अनुभाषण.

अननुषङ्गिन्
अननुषङ्गिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ङ्गी-ङ्गिणी-ङ्गि) Not attached <BR>to, indifferent (as to pleasure &c.). E. अ neg. and अनु- <BR>षङ्गिन्.

अननुष्ठान
अननुष्ठान Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Non-observance (of duties &c.), <BR>neglect, want of propriety. See the meanings of अनुष्ठान. <BR>E. अ neg. and अनुष्ठान.

अननूक्त
अननूक्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) <BR>	1 Not spoken-after <BR>or accordingly. <BR>	2 Not read or studied (as the Veda). E. <BR>अ neg. and अनूक्त.

अनन्त
अनन्त Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Endless in time <BR>and space: eternal, unbounded, innumerable &c. <BR>II. m. (-न्तः) <BR>	1 A name of Viṣṇu or Kṛṣṇa. <BR>	2 A name <BR>of Baladeva, the elder brother of Kṛṣṇa. <BR>	3 A name of <BR>Śiva. <BR>	4 A name of Rudra, in an Upanishad of the Athar<BR>vaveda. <BR>	5 A name of Śeṣa, the chief of the Nāgas or ser<BR>pent race that inhabit the infernal regions: the couch and <BR>constant attendant of Viṣṇu. <BR>	6 A name of Vāsuki, another <BR>king of the serpents, the brother of the former. <BR>	7 A name <BR>of one of the Viśvadevas. <BR>	8 The name of the fourteenth of <BR>the twenty-four Arhats or Jaina deified saints of the present <BR>Avasarpiṇī; see also अनन्तजित्. <BR>	9 The name of a king of <BR>Kashmir; see also अनन्तदेव. <BR>	10 A proper name common to <BR>several authors &c. <BR>	11 The name of a plant, Vitex trifolia <BR>(Lin.); see सिन्दवार. <BR>	12 Talc (see अभ्रक; in this sense the <BR>word is given by some as a neuter). <BR>	13 (In arithmetic.) <BR>Infinite quantity: a fraction having a cypher for its deno<BR>minator; see also अनन्तराशि and खहर. <BR>	14 The name of <BR>the twenty-third of the lunar asterisms; see श्रवण. <BR>	15 A <BR>silken cord with fourteen knots which the Hindus tie round <BR>the right arm at the festival of Anantachaturdaśī. <BR>III. f. (-न्ता) <BR>	1 The earth. <BR>	2 (In arithmetic sometimes <BR>used to denominate) the numeral one. <BR>	3 A name of Pār<BR>vatī, the wife of Śiva. <BR>	4 A name of Tārā, a Buddhist <BR>deity. <BR>	5 The proper name of the wife of Janamejaya. <BR>	6 The <BR>name of the following plants: <BR>	a. Hedysarum alhagi; see <BR>यवास or रोदनी. <BR>	b. Echytes frutescens; see श्यामा or गो- <BR>पी. <BR>	c. A sort of potherb; see विशल्या or शक्रपुष्पी. <BR>	d. Agrostis <BR>linearis (Koen.) or Panicum dactylon; see दूर्वा or भार्गवी, <BR>श्वेतदूर्वा and नीलदूर्वा. <BR>	e. Phyllanthus emblica (emblic my<BR>robolan); see आमलकी. <BR>	f. Menispermum glabrum or cordi<BR>folium; see गुडूची. <BR>	g. Gloriosa superba; see लाङ्गली. <BR>	h. See <BR>हेममानी. <BR>	i. Premna spinosa; see असिमन्थ. <BR>	k. Piper longum <BR>(Long pepper); see पिप्पली or कणा. <BR>	l. Terminalia chebula <BR>(yellow myrobolan); see हरीतकी. <BR>	m. Asclepias pseudosar<BR>sa; see शारिवा. <BR>	n. Justicia adhatoda(?). <BR>	o. Bromelia Ana<BR>nas(?). <BR>	p. Echytes dichotoma(?). <BR>	q. According to some <BR>also the same as अनन्तमूल q. v. <BR>IV. n. (-न्तम्) <BR>	1 Sky, atmosphere, æther. <BR>	2 Talc; (also <BR>given in the latter sense as a masculine). E. अ priv. and <BR>अन्त.

अनन्तक
अनन्तक I. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Endless, eternal, unlimited. <BR>II. n. (-कम्) (In the Jaina doctrine.) The collective ex<BR>pression for what is eternal viz. matter and soul; but in<BR>cluding also, according to a commentary, planets or accord<BR>ing to another, æther, regions &c. E. अनन्त, taddh. aff. <BR>कन्, or rather a Bahuvr. composed of अ neg. and अन्त, <BR>samāsānta aff. कप्.

अनन्तकर
अनन्तकर Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Making endless or <BR>unlimited. E. अनन्त and कर.

अनन्तग
अनन्तग Tatpur. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Going continually, <BR>moving perpetually. E. अनन्त and ग.

अनन्तचतुर्दशी
अनन्तचतुर्दशी Tatpur. f. (-शी) The fourteenth lunation of <BR>the light half i. e. the day of the full moon of the month <BR>Bhādra (August-September), when Viṣṇu under the <BR>form of the serpent Ananta is worshipped. E. अनन्त and <BR>चतुर्दशी.

अनन्तचारित्र
अनन्तचारित्र Bahuvr. m. (-त्रः) The proper name of a Bo<BR>dhisattva, Mahāsattva, or a superior Bauddha saint. E. <BR>अनन्त and चारित्र.

अनन्तजित्
अनन्तजित् Tatpur. m. (-जित्) The name of the fourteenth <BR>of the twenty-four Arhats or Jaina deified saints of the <BR>present Avasarpiṇī; also called अनन्त. E. अनन्त and जित् <BR>‘who conquers, who gains eternity’.

अनन्तता
अनन्तता f. (-ता) Eternity: also अनन्तत्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अनन्त, <BR>taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

अनन्तदृष्टि
अनन्तदृष्टि Bahuvr. m. (-ष्टिः) A name of Śiva. E. अनन्त <BR>and दृष्टि.

अनन्तदेव
अनन्तदेव Karmadh. m. (-वः) The proper name of a king of <BR>Kashmir, the son of Harirāja; also a proper name be<BR>longing to several authors &c. See also अनन्त. E. अनन्त <BR>and देव.

अनन्तनेमि
अनन्तनेमि Bahuvr.(?) m. (-मिः) The proper name of a king <BR>of Mālava, a contemporary of Śākyamuni. E. अनन्त and <BR>नेमि.

अनन्तपाल
अनन्तपाल Tatpur. m. (-लः) The proper name of a warrior <BR>chief serving under Harsha, king of Kashmir. E. अनन्त <BR>and पाल.

अनन्तमति
अनन्तमति Bahuvr. m. (-तिः) The proper name of a Bodhi<BR>sattva or Bauddha saint, the son of the Tathāgata Chan<BR>drasūryapradīpa. E. अनन्त and मति.

अनन्तमूल
अनन्तमूल Bahuvr. m. (-लः) The name of a plant (Periploca <BR>Indica or Asclepias pseudosarsa or Asclepias asthmatica); <BR>see also अनन्ता and शारिवा. E. अनन्त and मूल.

अनन्तर
अनन्तर Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) <BR>	1 Having nothing in<BR>termediate, having no interval or defect, uninterrupted, <BR>entire; in the Upanishads also as an epithet of Brahman (n.) <BR>or the supreme soul, of which it is said that it has nothing <BR>before it nor after it, nor between ‘before’ and ‘after’ <BR>it nor besides it, or that it exists without interruption <BR>or defect, entire. <BR>	2 Next, immediately following or pre<BR>ceding. <BR>	3 Next of kin, in succession, in caste. <BR>	4 Close, <BR>compact.--अनन्तरम् immediately, afterwards; it is fol<BR>lowed or preceded sometimes by a noun depending upon <BR>it in the ablative or genitive. E. अ priv. and अनन्तर.

अनन्तरज
अनन्तरज Tatpur. m. (-जः) The son of a man of the three <BR>first castes, married to a woman of a caste inferior in order <BR>to his own, but not to a Sūdra woman viz. of a Brāhmaṇa <BR>by a Kṣatriyā or Vaiśyā and of a Kṣatriyā by a Vaiśyā. <BR>The three kinds of sons got by parents of the same caste <BR>are called सजातिज and both, comprising six kinds, have <BR>the privileges of a Dvija or twice-born man. (This is <BR>the explanation given by a commentator of Manu and, <BR>according to him, अनन्तरज would have a different mean<BR>ing than अनन्तरजात, though both words appear to be <BR>synonymes.) E. अनन्तर and ज.

अनन्तरजात
अनन्तरजात Tatpur. m. (-तः) The son of a father married to <BR>a woman of a caste next in order to his own, viz. of a <BR>Brāhmaṇa by a Kṣatriyā, of a Kshatriya by a Vaiśyā, <BR>of a Vaiśya by a Sūdrā. E. अनन्तर and जात.

अनन्तरायम्
अनन्तरायम् Bahuvr. ind. Without interruption. E. अ priv. <BR>and अन्तराय.

अनन्तराशि
अनन्तराशि Karmadh. m. (-शिः) (In arithmetic.) Infinite <BR>quantity: a fraction having a cypher for its denominator. <BR>See also अनन्त II. 13. and खहर. E. अनन्त and राशि.

अनन्तरित
अनन्तरित m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Uninterrupted, not separated <BR>by. E. Denom. of अनन्तर, kṛt aff. क्त.

अनन्तरीय
अनन्तरीय m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Belonging to what is next, <BR>next in succession, caste &c. See the meanings of अनन्तर. <BR>E. अनन्तर, taddh. aff. छ.

अनन्तरूप
अनन्तरूप Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Having innumerable <BR>forms or shapes, multiform. E. अनन्त and रूप.

अनन्तर्हित
अनन्तर्हित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Not separated, <BR>not interposed. <BR>	2 Not concealed, not hidden. E. अ neg. <BR>and अन्तर्हित.

अनन्तवत्
अनन्तवत् I. m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Endowed with infinity, <BR>eternal. <BR>II. m. (-वान्) A name or epithet of one of the four pā<BR>das or feet of Brahman (in the symbolical language of the <BR>Upanishads), consisting of four Kalās or parts, viz. earth, <BR>intermediate space, heaven and ocean. The other three <BR>feet are called प्रकाशवत्, ज्योतिष्मत् and आयतनवत् <BR>(qq. vv.).

अनन्तवर्मन्
अनन्तवर्मन् Bahuvr. m. (-र्मा) The proper name of a king. <BR>E. अनन्त and वर्मन्.

अनन्तवात
अनन्तवात Karmadh. m. (-तः) (In medicine.) One of the <BR>diseases of the head (see शिरोरोग). It is described in the <BR>following manner: ‘when the three humours (air, bile and <BR>phlegm) are deranged in the vessels of the back of the <BR>neck they make it very feverish and painful and it sup<BR>presses the humours particularly in the region of the eyes, <BR>eyebrows and temples; it then produces shaking in the <BR>sides of the cheeks, cramp of the jaws and morbid affec<BR>tions of the eyes’. E. अनन्त and वात.

अनन्तविक्रमिन्
अनन्तविक्रमिन् m. (-मी) The proper name of a Bodhisattva <BR>or Bauddha saint. E. अनन्त-विक्रम, taddh. aff. इनि.

अनन्तविजय
अनन्तविजय Bahuvr. m. (-यः) The name of the shell of Yu<BR>dhiṣṭhira. E. अनन्त and विजय.

अनन्तवीर्य
अनन्तवीर्य Bahuvr. m. (-र्यः) The proper name of the twenty<BR>third Jaina Arhat or deified saint of a future age or Utsar<BR>piṇī. E. अनन्त and वीर्य.

अनन्तव्रत
अनन्तव्रत Tatpur. n. (-तम्) The name of a festival ob<BR>served on the day of the full moon in Bhādra (August <BR>September) in honour of Viṣṇu under the form of the <BR>serpent Ananta (q. v.). See अनन्तचतुर्दशी. E. अनन्त <BR>and व्रत.

अनन्तशक्ति
अनन्तशक्ति Bahuvr. m. (-क्तिः) The proper name of a son of <BR>the king Amaraśakti. E. अनन्त and शक्ति.

अनन्तशयन
अनन्तशयन Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The name of Travancore. E. <BR>अनन्त and शयन.

अनन्तशीर्षा
अनन्तशीर्षा Bahuvr. f. (-र्षा) The proper name of the wife <BR>of Vāsuki, a king of the serpents. E. अनन्त and शीर्ष; <BR>literally: ‘having innumerous heads’.

अनन्तशुष्म
अनन्तशुष्म Bahuvr. m. (-ष्मः) (ved.) Of infinite power or <BR>strength; an epithet of the Maruts. E. अनन्त and शुष्म.

अनन्त्य
अनन्त्य Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-न्त्यः-न्त्या-न्त्यम्) Infinite, eternal, <BR>unbounded. <BR>II. n. (-न्त्यम्) Infinity, eternity, immortality. cf. आनन्त्य. <BR>E. अ priv. and अन्त्य.

अनन्द
अनन्द Bahuvr. m. pl. (-न्दाः) (In the Upanishads) the name <BR>of a world where those are doomed to reside after their <BR>death, who have not acquired spiritual knowledge or who <BR>have made to a priest a sacrificial gift of an old or de<BR>fective cow &c. E. अ priv. and नन्द; literally: ‘having or <BR>giving no pleasure or joy’.

अनन्न
अनन्न Tatpur. n. (-न्नम्) No-food, no-corn, bad food, bad <BR>corn &c. See the meanings of अन्न. E. अ deter. and अन्न.

अनन्य
अनन्य m. f. n. (-न्यः-न्या-न्यम्) I. Tatpur. Not different, same, <BR>identical. E. अ neg. and अन्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. <BR>	1 Without another, one, sole. <BR>	2 Fixed on <BR>one object, having no other object or occupation. E. अ <BR>priv. and अन्य.

अनन्यगति
अनन्यगति I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः) No other refuge, asylum or <BR>hope, one only refuge &c. E. अ neg. and अन्य-गति. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति) Having but one refuge, <BR>asylum or hope. E. अ priv. and अन्य-गति.

अनन्यगतिक
अनन्यगतिक Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Having but one <BR>refuge, asylum or hope. E. अनन्यगति II, samāsānta <BR>aff. कप्.

अनन्यचिन्त
अनन्यचिन्त Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Having the <BR>thoughts fixed on one only object. E. अनन्य and चिन्ता.

अनन्यज
अनन्यज Tatpur. m. (-जः) A name of Kāma or Love. E. अ <BR>neg. and अन्य-ज ‘produced by nothing else than the manas <BR>or heart’.

अनन्यता
अनन्यता f. (-ता) or अनन्यत्व n. (-त्वम्) <BR>	1 Sameness, identity. <BR>	2 Singleness. E. अनन्य I. and II., taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

अनन्यदेव
अनन्यदेव Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Having no other <BR>gods. E. अ priv. and अन्य-देव.

अनन्यनिष्पाद्य
अनन्यनिष्पाद्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) What cannot <BR>be done or accomplished by any one else. E. अ neg. and <BR>अन्य-निष्पाद्य.

अनन्यपूर्व
अनन्यपूर्व Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-र्वः-र्वा-र्वम्) Intact, never in the <BR>prior possession of another. <BR>II. f. (-र्वा) A girl not previously wedded, a virgin. E. <BR>अ neg. and अन्य-पूर्व. Also with taddh. aff. कन्, अनन्य- <BR>पूर्वक m. f. n. (-र्वकः-र्विका-र्वकम्).

अनन्यप्रतिक्रिय
अनन्यप्रतिक्रिय Bahuvr. m. (-यः-या-यम्) Having no other <BR>remedy. E. अ priv. and अन्य-प्रतिक्रिया.

अनन्यभव
अनन्यभव Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Produced or effected <BR>by no one or nothing else, by one particular person or <BR>thing. E. अनन्य and भव.

अनन्यमनस्
अनन्यमनस् Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नाः-नाः-नः) Intent, attentive, <BR>having the mind fixed on one subject, not absent. E. अनन्य <BR>and मनस्.

अनन्यमनस्क
अनन्यमनस्क Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्कः-स्का-स्कम्). The same as <BR>the preceding. E. अनन्यमनस्, samāsānta aff. कप्.

अनन्यमानस
अनन्यमानस Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-सः-सी-सम्). The same as <BR>अनन्यमनस्. E. अनन्य and मानस.

अनन्यवृत्ति
अनन्यवृत्ति Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तिः-त्तिः-त्ति) Having the mind <BR>fixed on one object, intent, attentive. E. अनन्य and वृत्ति.

अनन्यहृत
अनन्यहृत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not stolen or taken, <BR>safe. E. अ neg. and अन्य-हृत.

अनन्यादृश
अनन्यादृश Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शः-शी-शम्) Not like another, <BR>unusual, extraordinary. E. अ neg. and अन्यादृश.

अनन्यार्थ
अनन्यार्थ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्थः-र्था-र्थम्) What exists or is done <BR>&c. not for any one or any thing else, what exists &c. on <BR>its own behalf, principal, absolute (e. g. a sacrifice). The <BR>reverse of अन्यार्थ. E. अ and अन्यार्थ.

अनन्याश्रित
अनन्याश्रित Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not supported <BR>by or dependant upon another, independant. <BR>II. n. (-तम्) (In law.) Unencumbered property. E. अ <BR>and अन्य-आश्रित.

अनन्वय
अनन्वय Tatpur. m. (-यः) (In rhetoric.) One of the Ālaṅkā<BR>ras or figures of speech: comparing an object to itself, with <BR>respect to its being the only one of its class as to the qua<BR>lities expressed and therefore not liable to comparison with <BR>any thing else; e. g. the moon shines like a moon i. e. like <BR>a very moon, a moon indeed. E. अ neg. and अन्वय, literally: <BR>‘want of connexion sc. with other objects’.

अनन्वित
अनन्वित Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Unconnected with, <BR>inconsistent, incoherent. <BR>	2 Devoid of, not possessing. E. <BR>अ neg. and अन्वित.

अनप
अनप Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Destitute of water. E. अ <BR>priv. and अप्, samāsānta aff. अ.

अनपकरण
अनपकरण Tatpur. n. (-णम्). The same as the following. <BR>E. अ neg. and अपकरण.

अनपकर्मन्
अनपकर्मन् Tatpur. n. (-र्म) 1. Not doing ill, evil &c. (The re<BR>verse of अपकर्मन् q. v.) 2. (In law.) <BR>	1 Not delivering (a <BR>gift). <BR>	2 Not paying or acquitting (debts, wages). See also <BR>अनपकरण, अनपक्रिया, अनपाकरण, अनपाकर्मन्. E. अ <BR>neg. and अपकर्मन्.

अनपकार
अनपकार Tatpur. m. (-रः) Harmlessness, freedom from <BR>hatred &c. (The reverse of अपकार q. v.) E. अ neg. and <BR>अपकार.

अनपकारिन्
अनपकारिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Innocuous &c. <BR>(The reverse of अपकारिन्.) E. अ neg. and अपकारिन्.

अनपक्रिया
अनपक्रिया Tatpur. f. (-या). The same as अनपकर्मन् q. v. <BR>E. अ neg. and अपक्रिया.

अनपग
अनपग Tatpur. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Not departing, not <BR>being separated from. E. अ neg. and अपग.

अनपच्युत
अनपच्युत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Not fallen off, <BR>not diminished in power &c., irresistible; as an epithet of <BR>Soma, Indra &c. E. अ neg. and अपच्युत.

अनपजय्य
अनपजय्य Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-य्यः-य्या-य्यम्) (ved.) What has <BR>no possibility of being made un-conquered or un-victorious <BR>(as a victory). अनपजय्यम् used also adverbially: so as <BR>not to become un-victorious (e. g. to conquer so as not to <BR>have a barren victory, as not to have the ennemy rising <BR>again). E. अ priv. and अपजय्य.

अनपत्य
अनपत्य Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) <BR>	1 Childless, having no <BR>progeny. <BR>	2 (ved.) Prejudicial to progeny. <BR>	3 (ved. Tatpur.) <BR>What causes to fall, unpropitious(?). E. अ priv. and अपत्य.

अनपत्यक
अनपत्यक Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्). The same as अन- <BR>पत्य. E. अनपत्य, samāsānta aff. कप्.

अनपत्यता
अनपत्यता f. (-ता) Childlessness, want of progency. E. अन- <BR>पत्य, taddh. aff. तल्.

अनपत्यवत्
अनपत्यवत् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Childless, hav<BR>ing no progeny. E. अ neg. and अपत्यवत्.

अनपनिहित
अनपनिहित Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Having <BR>suffered no loss, entire, complete. E. अ priv. and अपनिहित.

अनपयति
अनपयति Tatpur.(?) ind. Early in the morning. E. अ neg. <BR>and अपयति (? the locative of अपयत्, from इ with अप, <BR>kṛt aff. शतृ), meaning perhaps: ‘when the sun has not <BR>yet gone far’.

अनपर
अनपर Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Having nothing that <BR>follows or comes after; esp. as an epithet of the neuter <BR>Brahman; opposed to अपूर्व. E. अ priv. and अपर.

अनपराद्ध
अनपराद्ध Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Having suffered no <BR>injury; अनपराद्धम् also used adverbially: without injury. <BR>E. अ priv. and अपराद्ध.

अनपराध
अनपराध I. Tatpur. m. (-धः) Not doing ill, innocuousness, <BR>innocence, sinlessness. E. अ neg. and अपराध. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्) <BR>	1 Innocuous, sinless. <BR>	2 Uninjured, complete. E. अ priv. and अपराध.

अनपराधत्व
अनपराधत्व n. (-त्वम्) Sinlessness, want of fault or defect. <BR>E. अनपराध II., taddh. aff. त्व.

अनपराधिन्
अनपराधिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-धी-धिनी-धि) Innocent, sin<BR>less. E. अ neg. and अपराधिन्.

अनपलाषुक
अनपलाषुक Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Not thirsty. E. <BR>अ neg. and अपलाषुक.

अनपवृज्य
अनपवृज्य Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ज्यः-ज्या-ज्यम्) (ved.) Free from <BR>impurity (hairs &c.), as a road. E. अ priv. and अपवृज्य <BR>what is to be shunned.

अनपव्ययत्
अनपव्ययत् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यन्-यन्ती-यत्) (ved.) Un<BR>remitting, able, powerful. E. अ neg. and अपव्ययत् (from <BR>व्यय् with अप, kṛt aff. शतृ).

अनपसर
अनपसर Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Having no valid <BR>reason, acting in an unjustifiable manner. E. अ priv. and <BR>अपसर, literally: having no way-out.

अनपस्फुर्
अनपस्फुर् Tatpur. f. (-स्फूः) (ved.) Not going or running <BR>away; an epithet of a cow. E. अ neg. and अपस्फुर्.

अनपस्फुर
अनपस्फुर Tatpur. f. (-रा) (ved.) The same as the pre<BR>ceding. E. अ neg. and अपस्फुर.

अनपस्फुरत्
अनपस्फुरत् Tatpur. m. f. (-रन्-रन्ती) (ved.) The same as <BR>अनपस्फुर्; also as an epithet of the udder of the cow &c. <BR>E. अ neg. and अपस्फुरत्.

अनपहतपाप्मन्
अनपहतपाप्मन् Tatpur. m. (-प्मा) (ved.) Not freed from sin <BR>or evil; an epithet of the Manes. E. अ neg. and अपहत- <BR>पाप्मन्.

अनपहृत
अनपहृत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not taken away, <BR>not stolen. E. अ neg. and अपहृत.

अनपाकरण
अनपाकरण Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (In law.) <BR>	1 Not delivering (a <BR>gift). <BR>	2 Not paying or acquitting (debts, wages). See अन- <BR>पकर्मन्, अनपक्रिया and the following. E. अ neg. and अ- <BR>पाकरण.

अनपाकर्मन्
अनपाकर्मन् Tatpur. n. (-र्म) (In law.) The same as the pre<BR>ceding. E. अ neg. and अपाकर्मन्.

अनपाय
अनपाय I. Tatpur. m. (-यः) Absence of loss or diminution, <BR>permanence. E. अ neg. and अपाय. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Undiminished, un<BR>ceasing. 2. m. (-यः) A name or epithet of Śiva. E. अ <BR>priv. and अपाय.

अनपायिन्
अनपायिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) <BR>	1 Firm, constant. <BR>	2 Durable, imperishable. E. अ neg. and अपायिन्.

अनपुंसक
अनपुंसक Tatpur. n. (-कम्) (In grammar.) Not a neuter <BR>i. e. the masculine or feminine gender or a noun in these <BR>two genders. E. अ neg. and नपुंसक.

अनपूपीय
अनपूपीय Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not fit for cakes. <BR>E. अ neg. and अपूपीय.

अनपूप्य
अनपूप्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्यः-प्या-प्यम्). The same as the <BR>preceding. E. अ neg. and अपूप्य.

अनपेक्ष
अनपेक्ष I. Tatpur. f. (-क्षा) Carelessness, indifference, dis<BR>regard. E. अ neg. and अपेक्षा. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) <BR>	1 Disregarding. <BR>	2 Un<BR>heeding, careless. <BR>	3 Not requiring another thing, not <BR>referring to another thing or word in a sentence &c., <BR>independent or absolute. See निरपेक्ष. E. अ priv. and <BR>अपेक्षा.

अनपेक्षत्व
अनपेक्षत्व n. (-त्वम्) The being अनपेक्ष (II.), but more espe<BR>cially in the sense 3. E. अनपेक्ष, taddh. aff. त्व.

अनपेक्षित
अनपेक्षित m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Disregarded. <BR>	2 Unheeded. <BR>E. अ neg. and अपेक्षित.

अनपेक्षिन्
अनपेक्षिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षी-क्षिणी-क्षि) <BR>	1 Disregarding. <BR>	2 Unheeding, careless. E. अ neg. and अपेक्षिन्.

अनपेत
अनपेत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Present, not passed <BR>or gone. <BR>	2 Not devoid of, possessed of. E. अ neg. and <BR>अपेत.

अनप्नस्
अनप्नस् Bahuvr. m. (-प्नाः) (ved.) Devoid of (pious) action, <BR>impious or (according to another interpretation) devoid of <BR>shape or form. E. अ priv. and अप्नस्.

अनफा
अनफा f. (-फा) A certain configuration of the planets; a <BR>transcription of the greek word ἀναφή.

अनभिज्ञ
अनभिज्ञ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ज्ञः-ज्ञा-ज्ञम्) Unacquainted, <BR>ignorant, unwise. E. अ neg. and अभिज्ञ.

अनभिद्रुह्
अनभिद्रुह् Tatpur. m. (-ध्रुक्) (ved.) Not doing injury; an <BR>epithet of the Aśvins. E. अ neg. and अभिद्रुह्.

अनभिभूत
अनभिभूत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Unsubdued, un<BR>surpassed. <BR>	2 Unobstructed. E. अ neg. and अभिभूत.

अनभिमत
अनभिमत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Disliked, disagree<BR>able, unpleasant &c. (The reverse of अभिमत.) E. अ neg. <BR>and अभिमत.

अनभिम्लातवर्ण
अनभिम्लातवर्ण Tatpur. m. (-र्णः) (ved.) Of unwithered co<BR>lour, very bright or splendent; an epithet of Apānnapāt. <BR>E. अ neg. and अभिम्लातवर्ण.

अनभिम्लान
अनभिम्लान Tatpur. m. (-नः) The proper name of a gotra<BR>or family-chief. E. अ priv. and अभिम्लान. See आन- <BR>भिम्लान.

अनभिरूप
अनभिरूप Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Not handsome, not <BR>pleasing. E. अ neg. and अभिरूप.

अनभिलाष
अनभिलाष Tatpur. m. (-षः) <BR>	1 Absence of desire, indifference. <BR>	2 Want of appetite, indigestion. E. अ neg. and अभिलाष.

अनभिलक्षित
अनभिलक्षित Tatpur. m. (-तः) Not marked, not bearing sings <BR>or symbols (e. g. of knowledge, of astrology or of other <BR>learned acquirements, as a Vānaprastha when asking for <BR>alms). E. अ neg. and अभिलक्षित.

अनभिलाषिन्
अनभिलाषिन् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-षी-षिणी-षि) Not desirous, <BR>indifferent. E. अ neg. and अभिलाषिन्.

अनभिव्यक्त
अनभिव्यक्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) Indistinct, dim. <BR>E. अ neg. and अभिव्यक्त.

अनभिशस्त
अनभिशस्त Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्तः-स्ता-स्तम्) (ved.) Blameless, <BR>irreproachable. E. अ neg. and अभिशस्त.

अनभिशस्ति
अनभिशस्ति Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्तिः-स्तिः-स्ति) (ved.) Blame<BR>less, irreproachable; an epithet of ājya or clarified butter. <BR>E. अ priv. and अभिशस्ति.

अनभिशस्तेनी
अनभिशस्तेनी Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नीः-नीः-नि) (ved.) Leading <BR>to what is blameless, to heaven &c. (The form अनभि- <BR>शस्तेन्यम् which is explained as the acc. masc. singul. with <BR>the meaning of the nom. neuter sing. is rather to be con<BR>sidered as an irregular formation of the neuter with the addi<BR>tion of अम् to the terminating नि.) E. अनभिशस्त (loc.) and नी.

अनभिशस्त्य
अनभिशस्त्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्त्यः-स्त्या-स्त्यम्) (ved.) Blame<BR>less, irreproachable. E. अ neg. and अभिशस्त्य.

अनभिषङ्ग
अनभिषङ्ग Tatpur. m. (-ङ्गः) Detachment, disconnection, free<BR>dom from affection or attachment. E. अ neg. and अभिषङ्ग.

अनभिसन्धिकृत
अनभिसन्धिकृत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Done unin<BR>tentionally, or by mistake. E. अ neg. and अभिसन्धि-कृत.

अनभिहित
अनभिहित Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) <BR>	1 Not named, <BR>not designated. <BR>	2 (ved.) Not tied with, not fastened with. <BR>II. m. (-तः) A proper name of a gotraor family-chief. <BR>His descendants are called अनभिहिताः or आनभिहितयः. <BR>Acc. to others the proper name aught to be अभिहित q. v. <BR>E. अ neg. and अभिहित.

अनभीशु
अनभीशु Bahuvr. m. (-शुः) (ved.) Without reins (more esp. <BR>without the rein called अभीशु q. v.), unrefrained; an <BR>epithet of the sun. E. अ priv. and अभीशु.

अनभ्यारूढ
अनभ्यारूढ Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) Not ascended, not <BR>reached. E. अ neg. and अभ्यारूढ.

अनभ्यास
अनभ्यास Tatpur. I. m. (-सः) Want of practise, exercise &c.; <BR>see अभ्यास. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-सः-सा-सम्) Not near, far, far away. Also <BR>written अनभ्याश. E. अ neg. and अभ्यास.

अनभ्यासमित्य
अनभ्यासमित्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) What must not <BR>be approached, what must be shunned from afar. Also <BR>written अनभ्याशमित्य. E. अनभ्यास with āgama मुम् (or <BR>taken adverbially) and इत्य.

अनभ्रक
अनभ्रक Bahuvr. m. pl. (-काः) A class of Bauddha gods who <BR>reside in the first or lowest stage of the fourth sphere of <BR>the Bauddha heaven. E. अ priv. and अभ्र, samāsānta aff. <BR>कप्, literally ‘without clouds’.

अनम
अनम Tatpur. m. (-मः) A Brahman, one who does not salute <BR>a Brahman, making obeisance to the gods only, and re<BR>turning salutations with his blessing. E. अ neg. and नम <BR>who salutes(?).

अनमस्य
अनमस्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्यः-स्या-स्यम्) Unworthy of being <BR>saluted. E. अ neg. and नमस्य.

अनमितम्पच
अनमितम्पच Tatpur. m. f. n. (-चः-चा-चम्) Miserly, niggardly. <BR>E. अ neg. and अ-मितम्पच. Others read instead of this <BR>word, where it occurs in the Amarak., मितम्पच.

अनमित्र
अनमित्र Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Free from enemies, <BR>without enemies. <BR>II. n. (-त्रम्) The being free from or without enemies. <BR>III. m. (-त्रः) A proper name of <BR>	1 A prince of the solar <BR>race, a descendant of Sagara, son of Nighna and brother <BR>of Raghu, the fifty-second king of Ayodhyā. <BR>	2 A son of <BR>the king Kroṣṭu or Kroṣtṛ by Gāndhāri and father of <BR>Śini or, according to others, a grandson of Vṛṣṇi, son <BR>of Sumitra by Mādrī and brother to Śini; or, again, a <BR>grandson of Dhṛṣṭa, son of Sumitra &c. E. अ priv. and <BR>अमित्र.

अनमीव
अनमीव Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) (ved.) <BR>	1 Free from <BR>disease, healthy. <BR>	2 Removing diseases, healthy (as food, <BR>plants, fire). <BR>II. n. (-वम्) Freedom from disease, good health. E. अ <BR>priv. and अमीवा.

अनम्बर
अनम्बर Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Naked, unclad, <BR>unclothed. <BR>II. m. (-रः) A Bauddha mendicant, going naked. See <BR>दिगम्बर. E. अ priv. and अम्बर.

अनय
अनय Tatpur. m. (-यः) I. Bad or improper conduct, as <BR>gambling &c. (see व्यसन). E. अ deter. and नय. <BR>II. <BR>	1 Ill-luck, bad fortune. <BR>	2 Calamity, distress. E. अ <BR>deter. and अय.

अनयङ्गत
अनयङ्गत Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Fallen into misfor<BR>tune. E. अनय II., āgama मुम् and गत.

अनरण्य
अनरण्य Bahuvr. m. (-ण्यः) The proper name of a king of <BR>Ayodhyā, of the solar race; according to one authority, a <BR>son of Vāna and father of Pṛthu, according to others, <BR>a son of Sambhūta and father of Pṛṣadaśva or, again, a <BR>son of Sarwakarman and father of Nighna. Those who <BR>make him a son of Sambhūta, relate that he was slain by <BR>Rāvaṇa.

अनरुस्
अनरुस् Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रुः-रुः-रु) (ved.) Not sore, not <BR>wounded, sound, healed. (As a Tatpur. this word occurs <BR>only in the Vedas; it would be a Bahuvr. according to the <BR>use of अरुस् in the classic language.) E. अ neg. and अरुस्, <BR>sore, wounded; (or as a Bahuvr. अ priv. and अरुस्, sore, <BR>wound).

अनर्गल
अनर्गल Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Unrestrained, self<BR>willed. E. अ priv. and अर्गल.

अनर्घ
अनर्घ Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्घः-र्घा-र्घम्) Invaluable, priceless. <BR>E. अ priv. and अर्घ.

अनर्घराघव
अनर्घराघव Tatpur. n. (-वम्) The name of a drama of Mu<BR>rāri, the subject of which are the events in the life of Rā<BR>ma, the descendant of Raghu. E. अनर्घ and राघव, sc. नाटक.

अनर्घ्य
अनर्घ्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्घ्यः-र्घ्या-र्घ्यम्) <BR>	1 Priceless, invaluable, <BR>not to be bought. <BR>	2 Different from what is valuable or re<BR>spectable. (In the first of these meanings the word is an <BR>oxytonon, in the latter a proparoxytonon; the first mean<BR>ing, however, is the usual one.) E. अ neg. and अर्घ्य.

अनर्घ्यता
अनर्घ्यता f. (-ता) or अनर्घ्यत्व n. (-त्वम्) Absence of price <BR>or cost, invaluableness. E. अनर्घ्य, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

अनर्थ
अनर्थ I. Tatpur. m. (-र्थः) <BR>	1 Want of meaning, nonsense. <BR>	2 A thing that is useless or obnoxious. <BR>	3 Disadvantage, <BR>misfortune, calamity. E. अ neg. and अर्थ. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्थः-र्था-र्थम्) <BR>	1 Meaningless, un<BR>meaning, nonsensical. <BR>	2 Fruitless, vain, unprofitable. <BR>	3 Un<BR>happy, unlucky. E. अ priv. and अर्थ.

अनर्थक
अनर्थक Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्थकः-र्थका-र्थकम्) <BR>	1 Not having <BR>the sense or meaning (of). <BR>	2 Not-significative (as a particle <BR>&c.). <BR>	3 Unmeaning, meaningless, nonsensical. <BR>	4 Fruitless, <BR>vain, unprofitable. <BR>	5 Unhappy, unlucky. E. अनर्थ II., sa<BR>māsānta aff. कप्.

अनर्थकर
अनर्थकर Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) <BR>	1 Following unpro<BR>fitable or idle pursuits. <BR>	2 Doing mischief, causing calami<BR>ties. E. अ neg. and अर्थकर or अनर्थ and कर.

अनर्थनाशिन्
अनर्थनाशिन् Tatpur. m. (-शी) A name or epithet of Śiva. <BR>E. अनर्थ and नाशिन् ‘destroying or removing calamity’.

अनर्थ्य
अनर्थ्य Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्थ्यः-र्थ्या-र्थ्यम्) Devoid of substance, <BR>useless, fit for no purpose &c.; the reverse of अर्थ्य q. v. <BR>E. अ neg. and अर्थ्य.

अनर्व
अनर्व Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्वः-र्वा-र्वम्) (ved.) <BR>	1 Not decaying, <BR>not passing away, imperishable, permanent. <BR>	2 Without <BR>impediment, not thwarted, unobstructed. See the following. <BR>E. अ priv. and अर्व.

अनर्वन्
अनर्वन् Bahuvr. m. (-र्वा) (ved.) <BR>	1 Not moving, fixed. <BR>	2 Not <BR>passing away, permanent. <BR>	3 Without an impediment, not <BR>thwarted, unobstructed. <BR>	4 Without an enemy or foe. See <BR>the preceding. (The declension of this word differs from <BR>that of अर्वन् in so far, as it does not assume the ādeśa तृ <BR>(i. e. त्) which is said to be the substitute of the न् in <BR>अर्वन् q. v.; e. g. अनर्वाणम्, अनर्वाणौ, अनर्वाणः.) E. अ <BR>priv. and अर्वन्.

अनर्विश्
अनर्विश् Tatpur. m. (-ट्) (ved.) I. A car-man, one going <BR>with or on a cart. E. अनस्, with र् instead of स्, and <BR>विश्. (Or according to another explanation, which ap<BR>pears, however, to be an artificial one), <BR>II. One who does not arrive where he is to go to, one <BR>not attaining the end or aim of his journey. E. अ neg. <BR>and अर् (from ऋ, kṛt aff. विच्) and विश् II.

अनर्शनि
अनर्शनि Tatpur. m. (-निः) (ved.) The name of a demon <BR>slain by Indra. E. doubtful; probably अ neg. and अर्शनि.

अनर्शराति
अनर्शराति Tatpur. m. (-तिः) (ved.) One whose gifts are not <BR>inauspicious or wicked, whose offerings do not cause pain. <BR>A various reading of this word in the Sāmaveda is अलर्षि- <BR>राति q. v. E. अ neg. and अर्श-राति (Bahuvr.).

अनर्ह
अनर्ह Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्हः-र्हा-र्हम्) <BR>	1 Not deserving. <BR>	2 Un<BR>worthy. <BR>	3 Not fit, unsuitable. E. अ neg. and अर्ह.

अनल
अनल m. (-लः) <BR>	1 Fire. <BR>	2 A name of Agni or the god of fire. <BR>	3 The name of one of the eight Vasus. <BR>	4 A name of Vasu<BR>deva. <BR>	5 The proper name of a Muni. <BR>	6 The proper name <BR>of a monkey (in the Rāmāyaṇa). <BR>	7 The fire of the stomach, <BR>digestive faculty. <BR>	8 Bile. <BR>	9 The name of several plants, <BR>viz. <BR>	a. Plumbago zeylanica (see चित्रक), <BR>	b. Plumbago rosea <BR>(see रक्तचित्रक), <BR>	c. Semicarpus anacardium (see भल्लातक). <BR>	10 Wind. <BR>	11 (In astronomy.) The name of the fiftieth year <BR>of Bṛhaspati's cycle of sixty years. <BR>	12 (In astronomy.) <BR>The name of the third lunar mansion or Kṛttikā(?). <BR>	13 (In <BR>arithmetic sometimes used to denote) the numeral three; see <BR>अग्नि(9.). E. अन्, in the causative, uṇ. aff. कलच्; (अनल <BR>belongs to the वृषादि).

अनलङ्करिष्णु
अनलङ्करिष्णु Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्णुः-ष्णुः-ष्णु) <BR>	1 Not fond of <BR>ornaments, dress &c. <BR>	2 Not making show of ornaments, <BR>not ornamented. E. अ neg. and अलङ्करिष्णु.

अनलदीपन
अनलदीपन Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Producing appetite, <BR>stomachic. See अग्निदीपन. E. अनल and दीपन.

अनलप्रभा
अनलप्रभा Tatpur. f. (-भा) The name of a plant (Halicaca<BR>bum cardiospermum); see ज्योतिष्मती. E. अनल and प्रभा <BR>‘fire-shine’.

अनलप्रिया
अनलप्रिया Tatpur. f. (-या) The wife of Agni. E. अनल and <BR>प्रिया.

अनलम्
अनलम् Tatpur. ind. Not enough, insufficient, unequal, un<BR>able. E. अ neg. and अलम्.

अनलवाट
अनलवाट Tatpur. m. (-टः) The name of ancient Pattana. <BR>E. अनल and वाट.

अनलस
अनलस Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सः-सा-सम्) <BR>	1 Not indolent or lazy. <BR>	2 Diligent, industrious. E. अ neg. and अलस.

अनलसाद
अनलसाद Tatpur. m. (-दः) Decrease of digestive faculty, <BR>loss of appetite; lit. decay of the stomachic fire. E. अनल 7. <BR>and साद.

अनलि
अनलि m. (-लिः) The name of a tree (Sesbana grandiflora); <BR>see अगस्तिद्रु. E. अनल, taddh. aff. इ(?).

अनल्प
अनल्प Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ल्पः-ल्पा-ल्पम्) Not a little, much. <BR>E. अ neg. and अल्प.

अनल्पघोष
अनल्पघोष Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्) Making much noise, <BR>vociferous. E. अनल्प and घोष.

अनवकाश
अनवकाश Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) <BR>	1 Having no op<BR>portunity &c.; see अवकाश. <BR>	2 Having no proper place, ir<BR>relevant, unessential; (as words of an instance &c. which <BR>have no bearing on the rule to be illustrated, opposed to <BR>those words of it which are essential for the purpose). E. <BR>अ priv. and अवकाश.

अनवकाशता
अनवकाशता f. (-ता) or अनवकाशत्व n. (-त्वम्) The being <BR>irrelevant or unessential. E. अनवकाश, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

अनवग्रह
अनवग्रह Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-हः-हा-हम्) Not to be obstructed <BR>or impeded, resistless. E. अ priv. and अवग्रह.

अनवच्छिन्न
अनवच्छिन्न Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्) <BR>	1 Not cut, not <BR>separated, uninterrupted. <BR>	2 Unbounded. <BR>	3 Immoderate, ex<BR>cessive. <BR>	4 (In Nyāya phil.) Undiscriminated. E. अ neg. <BR>and अवच्छिन्न.

अनवच्छिन्नहास
अनवच्छिन्नहास Karmadh. m. (-सः) Uninterrupted or excessive <BR>laughter. See अतिहास. E. अनवच्छिन्न and हास.

अनवतप्त
अनवतप्त Tatpur. m. (-प्तः) (In Buddhist mythology and <BR>legends.) <BR>	1 The name of a serpent-king. <BR>	2 The name of a <BR>renowned lake where the disciples of Śākyamuni held <BR>several of their meetings; probably the same as Rāvaṇa<BR>hrada. E. अ neg. and अवतप्त.

अनवत्
अनवत्. See the E. of the following.

अनवत्त्व
अनवत्त्व n. (-त्त्वम्) The being endowed with life, the pro<BR>perty or quality of what is living. E. अनवत् (endowed <BR>with life, breathing, living, from अन III., taddh. aff. मतुप्, <BR>but occurring only as the thematic form of this word), <BR>taddh. aff. त्व; used in a vaidik commentary, to explain <BR>one meaning of the word असुरत्व.

अनवद्य
अनवद्य Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) <BR>	1 Blameless, irre<BR>proachable. <BR>	2 Unobjectionable, allowable. <BR>II. f. (-द्या) The proper name of an Apsaras, the daugh<BR>ter of Prādhā.

अनवद्यरूप
अनवद्यरूप Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Of faultless form, <BR>beautiful. E. अनवद्य and रूप.

अनवद्याङ्ग
